v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

39#define TRACE(...) \
40 do { \

46// Return the evaluation of {condition} if {ValidationTag::validate} is true,
47// DCHECK that it is true and always return true otherwise.
48// Note that this needs to be a macro, because the "likely" annotation does not
49// survive inlining.
50#ifdef DEBUG
51#define VALIDATE(condition) \
52 (ValidationTag::validate ? V8_LIKELY(condition) \
53 : ValidateAssumeTrue(condition, #condition))
54
55V8_INLINE bool ValidateAssumeTrue(bool condition, const char* message) {
56 DCHECK_WITH_MSG(condition, message);
57 return true;
58}
59#else
60#define VALIDATE(condition) (!ValidationTag::validate || V8_LIKELY(condition))
61#endif
62
63#define CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(feat) \
64 DCHECK(this->module_->origin == kWasmOrigin); \
65 if (!VALIDATE(this->enabled_.has_##feat())) { \
66 this->DecodeError( \
67 "Invalid opcode 0x%02x (enable with --experimental-wasm-" #feat ")", \
68 opcode); \
69 return 0; \
70 } \
71 this->detected_->add_##feat()

73static constexpr LoadType GetLoadType(WasmOpcode opcode) {
74 // Hard-code the list of load types. The opcodes are highly unlikely to
75 // ever change, and we have some checks here to guard against that.
76 static_assert(sizeof(LoadType) == sizeof(uint8_t), "LoadType is compact");
77 constexpr uint8_t kMinOpcode = kExprI32LoadMem;
78 constexpr uint8_t kMaxOpcode = kExprI64LoadMem32U;
79 constexpr LoadType kLoadTypes[] = {
80 LoadType::kI32Load, LoadType::kI64Load, LoadType::kF32Load,
81 LoadType::kF64Load, LoadType::kI32Load8S, LoadType::kI32Load8U,
82 LoadType::kI32Load16S, LoadType::kI32Load16U, LoadType::kI64Load8S,
83 LoadType::kI64Load8U, LoadType::kI64Load16S, LoadType::kI64Load16U,
84 LoadType::kI64Load32S, LoadType::kI64Load32U};
85 static_assert(arraysize(kLoadTypes) == kMaxOpcode - kMinOpcode + 1);
86 DCHECK_LE(kMinOpcode, opcode);
87 DCHECK_GE(kMaxOpcode, opcode);
88 return kLoadTypes[opcode - kMinOpcode];
89}
90
91static constexpr StoreType GetStoreType(WasmOpcode opcode) {
92 // Hard-code the list of store types. The opcodes are highly unlikely to
93 // ever change, and we have some checks here to guard against that.
94 static_assert(sizeof(StoreType) == sizeof(uint8_t), "StoreType is compact");
95 constexpr uint8_t kMinOpcode = kExprI32StoreMem;
96 constexpr uint8_t kMaxOpcode = kExprI64StoreMem32;
97 constexpr StoreType kStoreTypes[] = {
98 StoreType::kI32Store, StoreType::kI64Store, StoreType::kF32Store,
99 StoreType::kF64Store, StoreType::kI32Store8, StoreType::kI32Store16,
100 StoreType::kI64Store8, StoreType::kI64Store16, StoreType::kI64Store32};
101 static_assert(arraysize(kStoreTypes) == kMaxOpcode - kMinOpcode + 1);
102 DCHECK_LE(kMinOpcode, opcode);
103 DCHECK_GE(kMaxOpcode, opcode);
104 return kStoreTypes[opcode - kMinOpcode];
105}

177// Decoder error with explicit PC and optional format arguments.
178// Depending on the validation tag and the number of arguments, this forwards to
179// a V8_NOINLINE and V8_PRESERVE_MOST method of the decoder.
180template <typename ValidationTag, typename... Args>
181V8_INLINE void DecodeError(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, const char* str,
182 Args&&... args) {
183 // Decode errors can only happen if we are validating; the compiler should
184 // know this e.g. from the VALIDATE macro, but this assumption tells it again
185 // that this path is impossible.
186 V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
187 if constexpr (sizeof...(Args) == 0) {
188 decoder->error(pc, str);
189 } else {
190 decoder->errorf(pc, str, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
191 }
192}
193
194// Decoder error without explicit PC and with optional format arguments.
195// Depending on the validation tag and the number of arguments, this forwards to
196// a V8_NOINLINE and V8_PRESERVE_MOST method of the decoder.
197template <typename ValidationTag, typename... Args>
198V8_INLINE void DecodeError(Decoder* decoder, const char* str, Args&&... args) {
199 // Decode errors can only happen if we are validating; the compiler should
200 // know this e.g. from the VALIDATE macro, but this assumption tells it again
201 // that this path is impossible.
202 V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
203 if constexpr (sizeof...(Args) == 0) {
204 decoder->error(str);
205 } else {
206 decoder->errorf(str, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
207 }
208}

212template <typename ValidationTag>
213std::pair<HeapType, uint32_t> read_heap_type(Decoder* decoder,
214 const uint8_t* pc,
215 WasmEnabledFeatures enabled) {
216 auto [heap_index, length] =
217 decoder->read_i33v<ValidationTag>(pc, "heap type");
218 if (heap_index < 0) {
219 int64_t min_1_byte_leb128 = -64;
220 if (!VALIDATE(heap_index >= min_1_byte_leb128)) {
221 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Unknown heap type %" PRId64,
222 heap_index);
223 return {HeapType(HeapType::kBottom), length};
224 }
225 uint8_t uint_7_mask = 0x7F;
226 uint8_t code = static_cast<ValueTypeCode>(heap_index) & uint_7_mask;
227 bool is_shared = false;
228 if (code == kSharedFlagCode) {
229 if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_shared())) {
230 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
231 decoder, pc,
232 "invalid heap type 0x%x, enable with --experimental-wasm-shared",
233 kSharedFlagCode);
234 return {HeapType(HeapType::kBottom), length};
235 }
236 code = decoder->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc + length, "heap type");
237 length++;
238 is_shared = true;
239 }
240 switch (code) {
241 case kEqRefCode:
242 case kI31RefCode:
243 case kStructRefCode:
244 case kArrayRefCode:
245 case kAnyRefCode:
246 case kNoneCode:
247 case kNoExternCode:
248 case kNoFuncCode:
249 case kExternRefCode:
250 case kFuncRefCode:
251 return {HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared), length};
252 case kNoExnCode:
253 case kExnRefCode:
254 if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_exnref())) {
255 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
256 decoder, pc,
257 "invalid heap type '%s', enable with --experimental-wasm-exnref",
258 HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
259 }
260 return {HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared), length};
261 case kStringRefCode:
262 case kStringViewWtf8Code:
263 case kStringViewWtf16Code:
264 case kStringViewIterCode:
265 if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_stringref())) {
266 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
267 decoder, pc,
268 "invalid heap type '%s', enable with "
269 "--experimental-wasm-stringref",
270 HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
271 }
272 return {HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared), length};
273 default:
274 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Unknown heap type %" PRId64,
275 heap_index);
276 return {HeapType(HeapType::kBottom), length};
277 }
278 } else {
279 uint32_t type_index = static_cast<uint32_t>(heap_index);
280 if (!VALIDATE(type_index < kV8MaxWasmTypes)) {
281 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
282 decoder, pc,
283 "Type index %u is greater than the maximum number %zu "
284 "of type definitions supported by V8",
285 type_index, kV8MaxWasmTypes);
286 return {HeapType(HeapType::kBottom), length};
287 }
288 return {HeapType(ModuleTypeIndex{type_index}), length};
289 }
290}
291
292// Read a value type starting at address {pc} using {decoder}.
293// No bytes are consumed.
294// Returns the read value type and the number of bytes read (a.k.a. length).
295template <typename ValidationTag>
296std::pair<ValueType, uint32_t> read_value_type(Decoder* decoder,
297 const uint8_t* pc,
298 WasmEnabledFeatures enabled) {
299 uint8_t val = decoder->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc, "value type opcode");
300 if (!VALIDATE(decoder->ok())) {
301 return {kWasmBottom, 0};
302 }
303 ValueTypeCode code = static_cast<ValueTypeCode>(val);
304 switch (code) {
305 case kEqRefCode:
306 case kI31RefCode:
307 case kStructRefCode:
308 case kArrayRefCode:
309 case kAnyRefCode:
310 case kNoneCode:
311 case kNoExternCode:
312 case kNoFuncCode:
313 case kExternRefCode:
314 case kFuncRefCode:
315 return {ValueType::RefNull(HeapType::from_code(code, false)), 1};
316 case kNoExnCode:
317 case kExnRefCode:
318 if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_exnref())) {
319 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
320 decoder, pc,
321 "invalid value type '%s', enable with --experimental-wasm-exnref",
322 HeapType::from_code(code, false).name().c_str());
323 return {kWasmBottom, 0};
324 }
325 return {code == kExnRefCode ? kWasmExnRef : kWasmNullExnRef, 1};
326 case kStringRefCode:
327 case kStringViewWtf8Code:
328 case kStringViewWtf16Code:
329 case kStringViewIterCode: {
330 if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_stringref())) {
331 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
332 decoder, pc,
333 "invalid value type '%sref', enable with "
334 "--experimental-wasm-stringref",
335 HeapType::from_code(code, false).name().c_str());
336 return {kWasmBottom, 0};
337 }
338 // String views are not nullable, so interpret the shorthand accordingly.
339 ValueType type = code == kStringRefCode
340 ? kWasmStringRef
341 : ValueType::Ref(HeapType::from_code(code, false));
342 return {type, 1};
343 }
344 case kI32Code:
345 return {kWasmI32, 1};
346 case kI64Code:
347 return {kWasmI64, 1};
348 case kF32Code:
349 return {kWasmF32, 1};
350 case kF64Code:
351 return {kWasmF64, 1};
352 case kRefCode:
353 case kRefNullCode: {
354 Nullability nullability = code == kRefNullCode ? kNullable : kNonNullable;
355 auto [heap_type, length] =
356 read_heap_type<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc + 1, enabled);
357 if (!VALIDATE(!heap_type.is_string_view() ||
358 nullability == kNonNullable)) {
359 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc,
360 "nullable string views don't exist");
361 return {kWasmBottom, 0};
362 }
363 ValueType type = heap_type.is_bottom()
364 ? kWasmBottom
365 : ValueType::RefMaybeNull(heap_type, nullability);
366 return {type, length + 1};
367 }
368 case kS128Code: {
369 if (!VALIDATE(CheckHardwareSupportsSimd())) {
370 if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
371 FATAL("Aborting on missing Wasm SIMD support");
372 }
373 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Wasm SIMD unsupported");
374 return {kWasmBottom, 0};
375 }
376 return {kWasmS128, 1};
377 }
378 // Although these codes are included in ValueTypeCode, they technically
379 // do not correspond to value types and are only used in specific
380 // contexts. The caller of this function is responsible for handling them.
381 case kVoidCode:
382 case kI8Code:
383 case kI16Code:
384 case kF16Code:
385 // Fall through to the error reporting below.
386 break;
387 }
388 // Anything that doesn't match an enumeration value is an invalid type code.
389 if constexpr (!ValidationTag::validate) UNREACHABLE();
390 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "invalid value type 0x%x", code);
391 return {kWasmBottom, 0};
392}
393
394template <typename ValidationTag>
395bool ValidateHeapType(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
396 const WasmModule* module, HeapType type) {
397 if (!VALIDATE(!type.is_bottom())) return false;
398 if (!type.is_index()) return true;
399 // A {nullptr} module is accepted if we are not validating anyway (e.g. for
400 // opcode length computation).
401 if (!ValidationTag::validate && module == nullptr) return true;
402 if (!VALIDATE(type.ref_index().index < module->types.size())) {
403 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Type index %u is out of bounds",
404 type.ref_index());
405 return false;
406 }
407 return true;
408}
409
410template <typename ValidationTag>
411bool ValidateValueType(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
412 const WasmModule* module, ValueType type) {
413 if (!VALIDATE(!type.is_bottom())) return false;
414 if (V8_LIKELY(!type.is_object_reference())) return true;
415 return ValidateHeapType<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, module, type.heap_type());
416}

422// Helpers for decoding different kinds of immediates which follow bytecodes.
423struct ImmI32Immediate {
424 int32_t value;
425 uint32_t length;
426
427 template <typename ValidationTag>
428 ImmI32Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
429 std::tie(value, length) = decoder->read_i32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "immi32");
430 }
431};
432
433struct ImmI64Immediate {
434 int64_t value;
435 uint32_t length;
436
437 template <typename ValidationTag>
438 ImmI64Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
439 std::tie(value, length) = decoder->read_i64v<ValidationTag>(pc, "immi64");
440 }
441};
442
443struct ImmF32Immediate {
444 float value;
445 uint32_t length = 4;
446
447 template <typename ValidationTag>
448 ImmF32Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
449 // We can't use base::bit_cast here because calling any helper function
450 // that returns a float would potentially flip NaN bits per C++ semantics,
451 // so we have to inline the memcpy call directly.
452 uint32_t tmp = decoder->read_u32<ValidationTag>(pc, "immf32");
453 memcpy(&value, &tmp, sizeof(value));
454 }
455};
456
457struct ImmF64Immediate {
458 double value;
459 uint32_t length = 8;
460
461 template <typename ValidationTag>
462 ImmF64Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
463 // Avoid base::bit_cast because it might not preserve the signalling bit
464 // of a NaN.
465 uint64_t tmp = decoder->read_u64<ValidationTag>(pc, "immf64");
466 memcpy(&value, &tmp, sizeof(value));
467 }
468};

470struct BrOnCastFlags {
471 enum Values {
472 SRC_IS_NULL = 1,
473 RES_IS_NULL = 1 << 1,
474 };
475
476 bool src_is_null = false;
477 bool res_is_null = false;
478
479 BrOnCastFlags() = default;
480 explicit BrOnCastFlags(uint8_t value)
481 : src_is_null((value & BrOnCastFlags::SRC_IS_NULL) != 0),
482 res_is_null((value & BrOnCastFlags::RES_IS_NULL) != 0) {
483 DCHECK_LE(value, BrOnCastFlags::SRC_IS_NULL | BrOnCastFlags::RES_IS_NULL);
484 }
485};
486
487struct BrOnCastImmediate {
488 BrOnCastFlags flags;
489 uint8_t raw_value = 0;
490 uint32_t length = 1;
491
492 template <typename ValidationTag>
493 BrOnCastImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
494 raw_value = decoder->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc, "br_on_cast flags");
495 if (raw_value > (BrOnCastFlags::SRC_IS_NULL | BrOnCastFlags::RES_IS_NULL)) {
496 decoder->errorf(pc, "invalid br_on_cast flags %u", raw_value);
497 return;
498 }
499 flags = BrOnCastFlags(raw_value);
500 }
501};

601struct SelectTypeImmediate {
602 uint32_t length;
603 ValueType type;
604
605 template <typename ValidationTag>
606 SelectTypeImmediate(WasmEnabledFeatures enabled, Decoder* decoder,
607 const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
608 uint8_t num_types;
609 std::tie(num_types, length) =
610 decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "number of select types");
611 if (!VALIDATE(num_types == 1)) {
612 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
613 decoder, pc,
614 "Invalid number of types. Select accepts exactly one type");
615 return;
616 }
617 uint32_t type_length;
618 std::tie(type, type_length) =
619 value_type_reader::read_value_type<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc + length,
620 enabled);
621 length += type_length;
622 }
623};
624
625struct BlockTypeImmediate {
626 uint32_t length = 1;
627 // After decoding, either {sig_index} is set XOR {sig} points to
628 // {single_return_sig_storage}.
629 ModuleTypeIndex sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex::Invalid();
630 FunctionSig sig{0, 0, single_return_sig_storage};
631 // Internal field, potentially pointed to by {sig}. Do not access directly.
632 ValueType single_return_sig_storage[1];
633
634 // Do not copy or move, as {sig} might point to {single_return_sig_storage} so
635 // this cannot trivially be copied. If needed, define those operators later.
636 BlockTypeImmediate(const BlockTypeImmediate&) = delete;
637 BlockTypeImmediate(BlockTypeImmediate&&) = delete;
638 BlockTypeImmediate& operator=(const BlockTypeImmediate&) = delete;
639 BlockTypeImmediate& operator=(BlockTypeImmediate&&) = delete;
640
641 template <typename ValidationTag>
642 BlockTypeImmediate(WasmEnabledFeatures enabled, Decoder* decoder,
643 const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
644 int64_t block_type;
645 std::tie(block_type, length) =
646 decoder->read_i33v<ValidationTag>(pc, "block type");
647 if (block_type < 0) {
648 // All valid negative types are 1 byte in length, so we check against the
649 // minimum 1-byte LEB128 value.
650 constexpr int64_t min_1_byte_leb128 = -64;
651 if (!VALIDATE(block_type >= min_1_byte_leb128)) {
652 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "invalid block type %" PRId64,
653 block_type);
654 return;
655 }
656 if (static_cast<ValueTypeCode>(block_type & 0x7F) != kVoidCode) {
657 sig = FunctionSig{1, 0, single_return_sig_storage};
658 std::tie(single_return_sig_storage[0], length) =
659 value_type_reader::read_value_type<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc,
660 enabled);
661 }
662 } else {
663 sig = FunctionSig{0, 0, nullptr};
664 sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex{static_cast<uint32_t>(block_type)};
665 }
666 }
667
668 uint32_t in_arity() const {
669 return static_cast<uint32_t>(sig.parameter_count());
670 }
671 uint32_t out_arity() const {
672 return static_cast<uint32_t>(sig.return_count());
673 }
674 ValueType in_type(uint32_t index) const { return sig.GetParam(index); }
675 ValueType out_type(uint32_t index) const { return sig.GetReturn(index); }
676};
677
678struct BranchDepthImmediate {
679 uint32_t depth;
680 uint32_t length;
681
682 template <typename ValidationTag>
683 BranchDepthImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
684 ValidationTag = {}) {
685 std::tie(depth, length) =
686 decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "branch depth");
687 }
688};

696 FieldImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
697 ValidationTag validate = {})
698 : struct_imm(decoder, pc, validate),

704 SigIndexImmediate sig_imm;
705 TableIndexImmediate table_imm;

710 CallIndirectImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,

717struct BranchTableImmediate {
718 uint32_t table_count;
719 const uint8_t* start;
720 const uint8_t* table;
721
722 template <typename ValidationTag>
723 BranchTableImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
724 ValidationTag = {}) {
725 start = pc;
726 uint32_t len;
727 std::tie(table_count, len) =
728 decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "table count");
729 table = pc + len;
730 }
731};
732
733using TryTableImmediate = BranchTableImmediate;
734
735// A helper to iterate over a branch table.
736template <typename ValidationTag>
737class BranchTableIterator {
738 public:
739 uint32_t cur_index() const { return index_; }
740 bool has_next() const {
741 return VALIDATE(decoder_->ok()) && index_ <= table_count_;
742 }
743 uint32_t next() {
744 DCHECK(has_next());
745 index_++;
746 auto [result, length] =
747 decoder_->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc_, "branch table entry");
748 pc_ += length;
749 return result;
750 }
751 // length, including the length of the {BranchTableImmediate}, but not the
752 // opcode. This consumes the table entries, so it is invalid to call next()
753 // before or after this method.
754 uint32_t length() {
755 while (has_next()) next();
756 return static_cast<uint32_t>(pc_ - start_);
757 }
758 const uint8_t* pc() const { return pc_; }
759
760 BranchTableIterator(Decoder* decoder, const BranchTableImmediate& imm)
761 : decoder_(decoder),
762 start_(imm.start),
763 pc_(imm.table),
764 table_count_(imm.table_count) {}
765
766 private:
767 Decoder* const decoder_;
768 const uint8_t* const start_;
769 const uint8_t* pc_;
770 uint32_t index_ = 0; // the current index.
771 const uint32_t table_count_; // the count of entries, not including default.
772};
773
774struct CatchCase {
775 CatchKind kind;
776 // The union contains a TagIndexImmediate iff kind == kCatch or kind ==
777 // kCatchRef.
778 union MaybeTagIndex {
779 uint8_t empty;
780 TagIndexImmediate tag_imm;
781 } maybe_tag;
782 BranchDepthImmediate br_imm;
783};
784
785// A helper to iterate over a try table.
786template <typename ValidationTag>
787class TryTableIterator {
788 public:
789 uint32_t cur_index() const { return index_; }
790 bool has_next() const {
791 return VALIDATE(decoder_->ok()) && index_ < table_count_;
792 }
793
794 CatchCase next() {
795 uint8_t kind =
796 static_cast<CatchKind>(decoder_->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc_));
797 pc_ += 1;
798 CatchCase::MaybeTagIndex maybe_tag{0};
799 if (kind == kCatch || kind == kCatchRef) {
800 maybe_tag.tag_imm = TagIndexImmediate(decoder_, pc_, ValidationTag{});
801 pc_ += maybe_tag.tag_imm.length;
802 }
803 BranchDepthImmediate br_imm(decoder_, pc_, ValidationTag{});
804 pc_ += br_imm.length;
805 index_++;
806 return CatchCase{static_cast<CatchKind>(kind), maybe_tag, br_imm};
807 }
808
809 // length, including the length of the {TryTableImmediate}, but not the
810 // opcode. This consumes the table entries, so it is invalid to call next()
811 // before or after this method.
812 uint32_t length() {
813 while (has_next()) next();
814 return static_cast<uint32_t>(pc_ - start_);
815 }
816 const uint8_t* pc() const { return pc_; }
817
818 TryTableIterator(Decoder* decoder, const TryTableImmediate& imm)
819 : decoder_(decoder),
820 start_(imm.start),
821 pc_(imm.table),
822 table_count_(imm.table_count) {}
823
824 private:
825 Decoder* const decoder_;
826 const uint8_t* const start_;
827 const uint8_t* pc_;
828 uint32_t index_ = 0; // the current index.
829 const uint32_t table_count_; // the count of entries, not including default.
830};
831
832struct MemoryAccessImmediate {
833 uint32_t alignment;
834 uint32_t mem_index;
835 uint64_t offset;
836 const WasmMemory* memory = nullptr;
837
838 uint32_t length;
839
840 template <typename ValidationTag>
841 V8_INLINE MemoryAccessImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
842 uint32_t max_alignment, bool memory64_enabled,
843 ValidationTag = {}) {
844 // Check for the fast path (two single-byte LEBs, mem index 0).
845 const bool two_bytes = !ValidationTag::validate || decoder->end() - pc >= 2;
846 const bool use_fast_path = two_bytes && !(pc[0] & 0xc0) && !(pc[1] & 0x80);
847 if (V8_LIKELY(use_fast_path)) {
848 alignment = pc[0];
849 mem_index = 0;
850 offset = pc[1];
851 length = 2;
852 } else {
853 ConstructSlow<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, max_alignment,
854 memory64_enabled);
855 }
856 if (!VALIDATE(alignment <= max_alignment)) {
857 DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
858 decoder, pc,
859 "invalid alignment; expected maximum alignment is %u, "
860 "actual alignment is %u",
861 max_alignment, alignment);
862 }
863 }
864
865 private:
866 template <typename ValidationTag>
867 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void ConstructSlow(Decoder* decoder,
868 const uint8_t* pc,
869 uint32_t max_alignment,
870 bool memory64_enabled) {
871 uint32_t alignment_length;
872 std::tie(alignment, alignment_length) =
873 decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "alignment");
874 length = alignment_length;
875 if (alignment & 0x40) {
876 alignment &= ~0x40;
877 uint32_t mem_index_length;
878 std::tie(mem_index, mem_index_length) =
879 decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc + length, "memory index");
880 length += mem_index_length;
881 } else {
882 mem_index = 0;
883 }
884 uint32_t offset_length;
885 if (memory64_enabled) {
886 std::tie(offset, offset_length) =
887 decoder->read_u64v<ValidationTag>(pc + length, "offset");
888 } else {
889 std::tie(offset, offset_length) =
890 decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc + length, "offset");
891 }
892 length += offset_length;
893 }
894};
895
896// Immediate for SIMD lane operations.

995template <bool validate>
996struct PcForErrors {
997 static_assert(validate == false);
998 explicit PcForErrors(const uint8_t* /* pc */) {}
999
1000 const uint8_t* pc() const { return nullptr; }
1001};
1002
1003template <>
1004struct PcForErrors<true> {
1005 const uint8_t* pc_for_errors = nullptr;
1006
1007 explicit PcForErrors(const uint8_t* pc) : pc_for_errors(pc) {}
1008
1009 const uint8_t* pc() const { return pc_for_errors; }
1010};

1012// An entry on the value stack.
1013template <typename ValidationTag>
1014struct ValueBase : public PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate> {
1015 ValueType type = kWasmVoid;
1016
1017 ValueBase(const uint8_t* pc, ValueType type)
1018 : PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate>(pc), type(type) {}
1019};
1020
1021template <typename Value>
1022struct Merge {
1023 uint32_t arity = 0;
1024 union { // Either multiple values or a single value.
1025 Value* array;
1026 Value first;
1027 } vals = {nullptr}; // Initialize {array} with {nullptr}.
1028
1029 // Tracks whether this merge was ever reached. Uses precise reachability, like
1030 // Reachability::kReachable.
1031 bool reached;
1032
1033 explicit Merge(bool reached = false) : reached(reached) {}
1034
1035 Value& operator[](uint32_t i) {
1036 DCHECK_GT(arity, i);
1037 return arity == 1 ? vals.first : vals.array[i];
1038 }
1039};
1040
1041enum ControlKind : uint8_t {
1042 kControlIf,
1043 kControlIfElse,
1044 kControlBlock,
1045 kControlLoop,
1046 kControlTry,
1047 kControlTryTable,
1048 kControlTryCatch,
1049 kControlTryCatchAll,
1050};
1051
1052enum Reachability : uint8_t {
1053 // reachable code.
1054 kReachable,
1055 // reachable code in unreachable block (implies normal validation).
1056 kSpecOnlyReachable,
1057 // code unreachable in its own block (implies polymorphic validation).
1058 kUnreachable
1059};
1060
1061// An entry on the control stack (i.e. if, block, loop, or try).
1062template <typename Value, typename ValidationTag>
1063struct ControlBase : public PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate> {
1064 ControlKind kind = kControlBlock;
1065 Reachability reachability = kReachable;
1066
1067 // For try-table.
1068 base::Vector<CatchCase> catch_cases;
1069
1070 uint32_t stack_depth = 0; // Stack height at the beginning of the construct.
1071 uint32_t init_stack_depth = 0; // Height of "locals initialization" stack
1072 // at the beginning of the construct.
1073 int32_t previous_catch = -1; // Depth of the innermost catch containing this
1074 // 'try'.
1075
1076 // Values merged into the start or end of this control construct.
1077 Merge<Value> start_merge;
1078 Merge<Value> end_merge;
1079
1080 bool might_throw = false;
1081
1082 MOVE_ONLY_NO_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR(ControlBase);
1083
1084 ControlBase(Zone* zone, ControlKind kind, uint32_t stack_depth,
1085 uint32_t init_stack_depth, const uint8_t* pc,
1086 Reachability reachability)
1087 : PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate>(pc),
1088 kind(kind),
1089 reachability(reachability),
1090 stack_depth(stack_depth),
1091 init_stack_depth(init_stack_depth),
1092 start_merge(reachability == kReachable) {}
1093
1094 // Check whether the current block is reachable.
1095 bool reachable() const { return reachability == kReachable; }
1096
1097 // Check whether the rest of the block is unreachable.
1098 // Note that this is different from {!reachable()}, as there is also the
1099 // "indirect unreachable state", for which both {reachable()} and
1100 // {unreachable()} return false.
1101 bool unreachable() const { return reachability == kUnreachable; }
1102
1103 // Return the reachability of new control structs started in this block.
1104 Reachability innerReachability() const {
1105 return reachability == kReachable ? kReachable : kSpecOnlyReachable;
1106 }
1107
1108 bool is_if() const { return is_onearmed_if() || is_if_else(); }
1109 bool is_onearmed_if() const { return kind == kControlIf; }
1110 bool is_if_else() const { return kind == kControlIfElse; }
1111 bool is_block() const { return kind == kControlBlock; }
1112 bool is_loop() const { return kind == kControlLoop; }
1113 bool is_incomplete_try() const { return kind == kControlTry; }
1114 bool is_try_catch() const { return kind == kControlTryCatch; }
1115 bool is_try_catchall() const { return kind == kControlTryCatchAll; }
1116 bool is_try() const {
1117 return is_incomplete_try() || is_try_catch() || is_try_catchall();
1118 }
1119 bool is_try_table() { return kind == kControlTryTable; }
1120
1121 Merge<Value>* br_merge() {
1122 return is_loop() ? &this->start_merge : &this->end_merge;
1123 }
1124};
1125

1351// This is a global constant invalid instruction trace, to be pointed at by
1352// the current instruction trace pointer in the default case
1353const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t> invalid_instruction_trace = {0, 0};
