1355// A fast vector implementation, without implicit bounds checks (see
1356// https://crbug.com/1358853).
1357template <typename T>
1358class FastZoneVector {
1359 public:
1360 FastZoneVector() = default;
1361 explicit FastZoneVector(int initial_size, Zone* zone) {
1362 Grow(initial_size, zone);
1363 }
1364
1365#ifdef DEBUG
1366 ~FastZoneVector() {
1367 // Check that {Reset} was called on this vector.
1368 DCHECK_NULL(begin_);
1369 }
1370#endif
1371
1372 void Reset(Zone* zone) {
1373 if (begin_ == nullptr) return;
1374 if constexpr (!std::is_trivially_destructible_v<T>) {
1375 for (T* ptr = begin_; ptr != end_; ++ptr) {
1376 ptr->~T();
1377 }
1378 }
1379 zone->DeleteArray(begin_, capacity_end_ - begin_);
1380 begin_ = nullptr;
1381 end_ = nullptr;
1382 capacity_end_ = nullptr;
1383 }
1384
1385 T* begin() const { return begin_; }
1386 T* end() const { return end_; }
1387
1388 T& front() {
1389 DCHECK(!empty());
1390 return begin_[0];
1391 }
1392
1393 T& back() {
1394 DCHECK(!empty());
1395 return end_[-1];
1396 }
1397
1398 uint32_t size() const { return static_cast<uint32_t>(end_ - begin_); }
1399
1400 bool empty() const { return begin_ == end_; }
1401
1402 T& operator[](uint32_t index) {
1403 DCHECK_GE(size(), index);
1404 return begin_[index];
1405 }
1406
1407 void shrink_to(uint32_t new_size) {
1408 static_assert(std::is_trivially_destructible_v<T>);
1409 DCHECK_GE(size(), new_size);
1410 end_ = begin_ + new_size;
1411 }
1412
1413 void pop(uint32_t num = 1) {
1414 DCHECK_GE(size(), num);
1415 for (T* new_end = end_ - num; end_ != new_end;) {
1416 --end_;
1417 end_->~T();
1418 }
1419 }
1420
1421 void push(T value) {
1422 DCHECK_GT(capacity_end_, end_);
1423 *end_ = std::move(value);
1424 ++end_;
1425 }
1426
1427 template <typename... Args>
1428 void emplace_back(Args&&... args) {
1429 DCHECK_GT(capacity_end_, end_);
1430 new (end_) T{std::forward<Args>(args)...};
1431 ++end_;
1432 }
1433
1434 V8_INLINE void EnsureMoreCapacity(int slots_needed, Zone* zone) {
1435 if (V8_LIKELY(capacity_end_ - end_ >= slots_needed)) return;
1436 Grow(slots_needed, zone);
1437 }
1438
1439 private:
1440 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void Grow(int slots_needed, Zone* zone) {
1441 size_t new_capacity = std::max(
1442 size_t{8}, base::bits::RoundUpToPowerOfTwo(size() + slots_needed));
1443 CHECK_GE(kMaxUInt32, new_capacity);
1444 DCHECK_LT(capacity_end_ - begin_, new_capacity);
1445 T* new_begin = zone->template AllocateArray<T>(new_capacity);
1446 if (begin_) {
1447 for (T *ptr = begin_, *new_ptr = new_begin; ptr != end_;
1448 ++ptr, ++new_ptr) {
1449 new (new_ptr) T{std::move(*ptr)};
1450 ptr->~T();
1451 }
1452 zone->DeleteArray(begin_, capacity_end_ - begin_);
1453 }
1454 end_ = new_begin + (end_ - begin_);
1455 begin_ = new_begin;
1456 capacity_end_ = new_begin + new_capacity;
1457 }
1458
1459 // The array is zone-allocated inside {EnsureMoreCapacity}.
1460 T* begin_ = nullptr;
1461 T* end_ = nullptr;
1462 T* capacity_end_ = nullptr;
1463};
1464
1465// Generic Wasm bytecode decoder with utilities for decoding immediates,
1466// lengths, etc.
1467template <typename ValidationTag, DecodingMode decoding_mode = kFunctionBody>
1468class WasmDecoder : public Decoder {
1469 public:
1470 WasmDecoder(Zone* zone, const WasmModule* module, WasmEnabledFeatures enabled,
1471 WasmDetectedFeatures* detected, const FunctionSig* sig,
1472 bool is_shared, const uint8_t* start, const uint8_t* end,
1473 uint32_t buffer_offset = 0)
1474 : Decoder(start, end, buffer_offset),
1475 zone_(zone),
1476 module_(module),
1477 enabled_(enabled),
1478 detected_(detected),
1479 sig_(sig),
1480 is_shared_(is_shared) {
1481 current_inst_trace_ = &invalid_instruction_trace;
1482 if (V8_UNLIKELY(module_ && !module_->inst_traces.empty())) {
1483 auto last_trace = module_->inst_traces.end() - 1;
1484 auto first_inst_trace =
1485 std::lower_bound(module_->inst_traces.begin(), last_trace,
1486 std::make_pair(buffer_offset, 0),
1487 [](const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t>& a,
1488 const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t>& b) {
1489 return a.first < b.first;
1490 });
1491 if (V8_UNLIKELY(first_inst_trace != last_trace)) {
1492 current_inst_trace_ = &*first_inst_trace;
1493 }
1494 }
1495 }
1496
1497 Zone* zone() const { return zone_; }
1498
1499 uint32_t num_locals() const { return num_locals_; }
1500
1501 base::Vector<ValueType> local_types() const {
1502 return base::VectorOf(local_types_, num_locals_);
1503 }
1504 ValueType local_type(uint32_t index) const {
1505 DCHECK_GE(num_locals_, index);
1506 return local_types_[index];
1507 }
1508
1509 // Decodes local definitions in the current decoder.
1510 // The decoded locals will be appended to {this->local_types_}.
1511 // The decoder's pc is not advanced.
1512 // The total length of decoded locals is returned.
1513 uint32_t DecodeLocals(const uint8_t* pc) {
1514 DCHECK_NULL(local_types_);
1515 DCHECK_EQ(0, num_locals_);
1516
1517 // In a first step, count the number of locals and store the decoded
1518 // entries.
1519 num_locals_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(this->sig_->parameter_count());
1520
1521 // Decode local declarations, if any.
1522 auto [entries, entries_length] =
1523 read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "local decls count");
1524
1525 if (!VALIDATE(ok())) {
1526 DecodeError(pc, "invalid local decls count");
1527 return 0;
1528 }
1529 TRACE("local decls count: %u\n", entries);
1530
1531 // Do an early validity check, to avoid allocating too much memory below.
1532 // Every entry needs at least two bytes (count plus type); if that many are
1533 // not available any more, flag that as an error.
1534 if (available_bytes() / 2 < entries) {
1535 DecodeError(pc, "local decls count bigger than remaining function size");
1536 return 0;
1537 }
1538
1539 struct DecodedLocalEntry {
1540 uint32_t count;
1541 ValueType type;
1542 };
1543 base::SmallVector<DecodedLocalEntry, 8> decoded_locals(entries);
1544 uint32_t total_length = entries_length;
1545 for (uint32_t entry = 0; entry < entries; ++entry) {
1546 if (!VALIDATE(more())) {
1547 DecodeError(end(),
1548 "expected more local decls but reached end of input");
1549 return 0;
1550 }
1551
1552 auto [count, count_length] =
1553 read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc + total_length, "local count");
1554 if (!VALIDATE(ok())) {
1555 DecodeError(pc + total_length, "invalid local count");
1556 return 0;
1557 }
1558 DCHECK_LE(num_locals_, kV8MaxWasmFunctionLocals);
1559 if (!VALIDATE(count <= kV8MaxWasmFunctionLocals - num_locals_)) {
1560 DecodeError(pc + total_length, "local count too large");
1561 return 0;
1562 }
1563 total_length += count_length;
1564
1565 auto [type, type_length] =
1566 value_type_reader::read_value_type<ValidationTag>(
1567 this, pc + total_length, enabled_);
1568 ValidateValueType(pc + total_length, type);
1569 if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || IsShared(type, module_))) {
1570 DecodeError(pc + total_length, "local must have shared type");
1571 return 0;
1572 }
1573 if (!VALIDATE(ok())) return 0;
1574 total_length += type_length;
1575
1576 num_locals_ += count;
1577 decoded_locals[entry] = DecodedLocalEntry{count, type};
1578 }
1579 DCHECK(ok());
1580
1581 if (num_locals_ > 0) {
1582 // Now build the array of local types from the parsed entries.
1583 local_types_ = zone_->AllocateArray<ValueType>(num_locals_);
1584 ValueType* locals_ptr = local_types_;
1585
1586 if (sig_->parameter_count() > 0) {
1587 std::copy(sig_->parameters().begin(), sig_->parameters().end(),
1588 locals_ptr);
1589 locals_ptr += sig_->parameter_count();
1590 }
1591
1592 for (auto& entry : decoded_locals) {
1593 std::fill_n(locals_ptr, entry.count, entry.type);
1594 locals_ptr += entry.count;
1595 }
1596 DCHECK_EQ(locals_ptr, local_types_ + num_locals_);
1597 }
1598 return total_length;
1599 }
1600
1601 // Shorthand that forwards to the {DecodeError} functions above, passing our
1602 // {ValidationTag}.
1603 template <typename... Args>
1604 V8_INLINE void DecodeError(Args... args) {
1605 wasm::DecodeError<ValidationTag>(this, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1606 }
1607
1608 // Returns a BitVector of length {locals_count + 1} representing the set of
1609 // variables that are assigned in the loop starting at {pc}. The additional
1610 // position at the end of the vector represents possible assignments to
1611 // the instance cache.
1612 static BitVector* AnalyzeLoopAssignment(WasmDecoder* decoder,
1613 const uint8_t* pc,
1614 uint32_t locals_count, Zone* zone,
1615 bool* loop_is_innermost = nullptr) {
1616 if (pc >= decoder->end()) return nullptr;
1617 if (*pc != kExprLoop) return nullptr;
1618 // The number of locals_count is augmented by 1 so that the 'locals_count'
1619 // index can be used to track the instance cache.
1620 BitVector* assigned = zone->New<BitVector>(locals_count + 1, zone);
1621 int depth = -1; // We will increment the depth to 0 when we decode the
1622 // starting 'loop' opcode.
1623 if (loop_is_innermost) *loop_is_innermost = true;
1624 // Iteratively process all AST nodes nested inside the loop.
1625 while (pc < decoder->end() && VALIDATE(decoder->ok())) {
1626 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*pc);
1627 switch (opcode) {
1628 case kExprLoop:
1629 if (loop_is_innermost && depth >= 0) *loop_is_innermost = false;
1630 [[fallthrough]];
1631 case kExprIf:
1632 case kExprBlock:
1633 case kExprTry:
1634 case kExprTryTable:
1635 depth++;
1636 break;
1637 case kExprLocalSet:
1638 case kExprLocalTee: {
1639 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, "local index", validate);
1640 // Unverified code might have an out-of-bounds index.
1641 if (imm.index < locals_count) assigned->Add(imm.index);
1642 break;
1643 }
1644 case kExprMemoryGrow:
1645 case kExprCallFunction:
1646 case kExprCallIndirect:
1647 case kExprCallRef:
1648 // Add instance cache to the assigned set.
1649 assigned->Add(locals_count);
1650 break;
1651 case kExprEnd:
1652 depth--;
1653 break;
1654 default:
1655 break;
1656 }
1657 if (depth < 0) break;
1658 pc += OpcodeLength(decoder, pc);
1659 }
1660 return VALIDATE(decoder->ok()) ? assigned : nullptr;
1661 }
1662
1663 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, TagIndexImmediate& imm) {
1664 size_t num_tags = module_->tags.size();
1665 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_tags)) {
1666 DecodeError(pc, "Invalid tag index: %u", imm.index);
1667 return false;
1668 }
1669 V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_tags);
1670 imm.tag = &module_->tags[imm.index];
1671 return true;
1672 }
1673
1674 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, GlobalIndexImmediate& imm) {
1675 // We compare with the current size of the globals vector. This is important
1676 // if we are decoding a constant expression in the global section.
1677 size_t num_globals = module_->globals.size();
1678 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_globals)) {
1679 DecodeError(pc, "Invalid global index: %u", imm.index);
1680 return false;
1681 }
1682 V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_globals);
1683 imm.global = &module_->globals[imm.index];
1684 if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || imm.global->shared)) {
1685 DecodeError(pc, "Cannot access non-shared global %d in a shared %s",
1686 imm.index,
1687 decoding_mode == kConstantExpression ? "constant expression"
1688 : "function");
1689 return false;
1690 }
1691
1692 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) {
1693 if (!VALIDATE(!imm.global->mutability)) {
1694 this->DecodeError(pc,
1695 "mutable globals cannot be used in constant "
1696 "expressions");
1697 return false;
1698 }
1699 }
1700
1701 return true;
1702 }
1703
1704 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, SigIndexImmediate& imm) {
1705 if (!VALIDATE(module_->has_signature(imm.index))) {
1706 DecodeError(pc, "invalid signature index: %u", imm.index.index);
1707 return false;
1708 }
1709 imm.sig = module_->signature(imm.index);
1710 return true;
1711 }
1712
1713 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, StructIndexImmediate& imm) {
1714 if (!VALIDATE(module_->has_struct(imm.index))) {
1715 DecodeError(pc, "invalid struct index: %u", imm.index.index);
1716 return false;
1717 }
1718 imm.struct_type = module_->struct_type(imm.index);
1719 return true;
1720 }
1721
1722 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, FieldImmediate& imm) {
1723 if (!Validate(pc, imm.struct_imm)) return false;
1724 if (!VALIDATE(imm.field_imm.index <
1725 imm.struct_imm.struct_type->field_count())) {
1726 DecodeError(pc + imm.struct_imm.length, "invalid field index: %u",
1727 imm.field_imm.index);
1728 return false;
1729 }
1730 return true;
1731 }
1732
1733 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, ArrayIndexImmediate& imm) {
1734 if (!VALIDATE(module_->has_array(imm.index))) {
1735 DecodeError(pc, "invalid array index: %u", imm.index.index);
1736 return false;
1737 }
1738 imm.array_type = module_->array_type(imm.index);
1739 return true;
1740 }
1741
1742 bool CanReturnCall(const FunctionSig* target_sig) {
1743 if (sig_->return_count() != target_sig->return_count()) return false;
1744 auto target_sig_it = target_sig->returns().begin();
1745 for (ValueType ret_type : sig_->returns()) {
1746 if (!IsSubtypeOf(*target_sig_it++, ret_type, this->module_)) return false;
1747 }
1748 return true;
1749 }
1750
1751 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, CallFunctionImmediate& imm) {
1752 size_t num_functions = module_->functions.size();
1753 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_functions)) {
1754 DecodeError(pc, "function index #%u is out of bounds", imm.index);
1755 return false;
1756 }
1757 if (is_shared_ && !module_->function_is_shared(imm.index)) {
1758 DecodeError(pc, "cannot call non-shared function %u", imm.index);
1759 return false;
1760 }
1761 V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_functions);
1762 imm.sig = module_->functions[imm.index].sig;
1763 return true;
1764 }
1765
1766 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, CallIndirectImmediate& imm) {
1767 if (!Validate(pc, imm.sig_imm)) return false;
1768 if (!Validate(pc + imm.sig_imm.length, imm.table_imm)) return false;
1769 ValueType table_type = imm.table_imm.table->type;
1770 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(table_type, kWasmFuncRef, module_) ||
1771 IsSubtypeOf(table_type,
1772 ValueType::RefNull(HeapType::kFuncShared),
1773 module_))) {
1774 DecodeError(
1775 pc, "call_indirect: immediate table #%u is not of a function type",
1776 imm.table_imm.index);
1777 return false;
1778 }
1779 // The type specified by the immediate does not need to have any static
1780 // relation (neither sub nor super) to the type of the table. The type
1781 // of the function will be checked at runtime.
1782
1783 imm.sig = module_->signature(imm.sig_imm.index);
1784 return true;
1785 }
1786
1787 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, BranchDepthImmediate& imm,
1788 size_t control_depth) {
1789 if (!VALIDATE(imm.depth < control_depth)) {
1790 DecodeError(pc, "invalid branch depth: %u", imm.depth);
1791 return false;
1792 }
1793 return true;
1794 }
1795
1796 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, BranchTableImmediate& imm) {
1797 if (!VALIDATE(imm.table_count <= kV8MaxWasmFunctionBrTableSize)) {
1798 DecodeError(pc, "invalid table count (> max br_table size): %u",
1799 imm.table_count);
1800 return false;
1801 }
1802 return checkAvailable(imm.table_count);
1803 }
1804
1805 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, WasmOpcode opcode, SimdLaneImmediate& imm) {
1806 uint8_t num_lanes = 0;
1807 switch (opcode) {
1808 case kExprF64x2ExtractLane:
1809 case kExprF64x2ReplaceLane:
1810 case kExprI64x2ExtractLane:
1811 case kExprI64x2ReplaceLane:
1812 case kExprS128Load64Lane:
1813 case kExprS128Store64Lane:
1814 num_lanes = 2;
1815 break;
1816 case kExprF32x4ExtractLane:
1817 case kExprF32x4ReplaceLane:
1818 case kExprI32x4ExtractLane:
1819 case kExprI32x4ReplaceLane:
1820 case kExprS128Load32Lane:
1821 case kExprS128Store32Lane:
1822 num_lanes = 4;
1823 break;
1824 case kExprF16x8ExtractLane:
1825 case kExprF16x8ReplaceLane:
1826 case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneS:
1827 case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneU:
1828 case kExprI16x8ReplaceLane:
1829 case kExprS128Load16Lane:
1830 case kExprS128Store16Lane:
1831 num_lanes = 8;
1832 break;
1833 case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneS:
1834 case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneU:
1835 case kExprI8x16ReplaceLane:
1836 case kExprS128Load8Lane:
1837 case kExprS128Store8Lane:
1838 num_lanes = 16;
1839 break;
1840 default:
1841 UNREACHABLE();
1842 break;
1843 }
1844 if (!VALIDATE(imm.lane >= 0 && imm.lane < num_lanes)) {
1845 DecodeError(pc, "invalid lane index");
1846 return false;
1847 } else {
1848 return true;
1849 }
1850 }
1851
1852 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, Simd128Immediate& imm) {
1853 uint8_t max_lane = 0;
1854 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; ++i) {
1855 max_lane = std::max(max_lane, imm.value[i]);
1856 }
1857 // Shuffle indices must be in [0..31] for a 16 lane shuffle.
1858 if (!VALIDATE(max_lane < 2 * kSimd128Size)) {
1859 DecodeError(pc, "invalid shuffle mask");
1860 return false;
1861 }
1862 return true;
1863 }
1864
1865 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, BlockTypeImmediate& imm) {
1866 if (imm.sig.all().begin() == nullptr) {
1867 // Then use {sig_index} to initialize the signature.
1868 if (!VALIDATE(module_->has_signature(imm.sig_index))) {
1869 DecodeError(pc, "block type index %u is not a signature definition",
1870 imm.sig_index);
1871 return false;
1872 }
1873 imm.sig = *module_->signature(imm.sig_index);
1874 } else {
1875 // Then it's an MVP immediate with 0 parameters and 0-1 returns.
1876 DCHECK_EQ(0, imm.sig.parameter_count());
1877 DCHECK_GE(1, imm.sig.return_count());
1878 if (imm.sig.return_count()) {
1879 if (!ValidateValueType(pc, imm.sig.GetReturn(0))) return false;
1880 }
1881 }
1882 return true;
1883 }
1884
1885 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, MemoryIndexImmediate& imm) {
1886 size_t num_memories = module_->memories.size();
1887 if (imm.index > 0 || imm.length > 1) {
1888 this->detected_->add_multi_memory();
1889 if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
1890 DecodeError(pc, "Multiple memories not supported in Wasm jitless mode");
1891 return false;
1892 }
1893 }
1894
1895 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_memories)) {
1896 DecodeError(pc,
1897 "memory index %u exceeds number of declared memories (%zu)",
1898 imm.index, num_memories);
1899 return false;
1900 }
1901
1902 V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_memories);
1903 imm.memory = this->module_->memories.data() + imm.index;
1904
1905 return true;
1906 }
1907
1908 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, MemoryAccessImmediate& imm) {
1909 size_t num_memories = module_->memories.size();
1910 if (!VALIDATE(imm.mem_index < num_memories)) {
1911 DecodeError(pc,
1912 "memory index %u exceeds number of declared memories (%zu)",
1913 imm.mem_index, num_memories);
1914 return false;
1915 }
1916 if (!VALIDATE(this->module_->memories[imm.mem_index].is_memory64() ||
1917 imm.offset <= kMaxUInt32)) {
1918 this->DecodeError(pc, "memory offset outside 32-bit range: %" PRIu64,
1919 imm.offset);
1920 return false;
1921 }
1922
1923 V8_ASSUME(imm.mem_index < num_memories);
1924 imm.memory = this->module_->memories.data() + imm.mem_index;
1925
1926 return true;
1927 }
1928
1929 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, MemoryInitImmediate& imm) {
1930 return ValidateDataSegment(pc, imm.data_segment) &&
1931 Validate(pc + imm.data_segment.length, imm.memory);
1932 }
1933
1934 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, MemoryCopyImmediate& imm) {
1935 return Validate(pc, imm.memory_src) &&
1936 Validate(pc + imm.memory_src.length, imm.memory_dst);
1937 }
1938
1939 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, TableInitImmediate& imm) {
1940 if (!ValidateElementSegment(pc, imm.element_segment)) return false;
1941 if (!Validate(pc + imm.element_segment.length, imm.table)) {
1942 return false;
1943 }
1944 ValueType elem_type =
1945 module_->elem_segments[imm.element_segment.index].type;
1946 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(elem_type, imm.table.table->type, module_))) {
1947 DecodeError(pc, "table %u is not a super-type of %s", imm.table.index,
1948 elem_type.name().c_str());
1949 return false;
1950 }
1951 return true;
1952 }
1953
1954 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, TableCopyImmediate& imm) {
1955 if (!Validate(pc, imm.table_src)) return false;
1956 if (!Validate(pc + imm.table_src.length, imm.table_dst)) return false;
1957 ValueType src_type = imm.table_src.table->type;
1958 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(src_type, imm.table_dst.table->type, module_))) {
1959 DecodeError(pc, "table %u is not a super-type of %s", imm.table_dst.index,
1960 src_type.name().c_str());
1961 return false;
1962 }
1963 return true;
1964 }
1965
1966 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, StringConstImmediate& imm) {
1967 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < module_->stringref_literals.size())) {
1968 DecodeError(pc, "Invalid string literal index: %u", imm.index);
1969 return false;
1970 }
1971 return true;
1972 }
1973
1974 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, TableIndexImmediate& imm) {
1975 if (imm.index > 0 || imm.length > 1) {
1976 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
1977 }
1978 size_t num_tables = module_->tables.size();
1979 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_tables)) {
1980 DecodeError(pc, "table index %u exceeds number of tables (%zu)",
1981 imm.index, num_tables);
1982 return false;
1983 }
1984 imm.table = this->module_->tables.data() + imm.index;
1985
1986 if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || imm.table->shared)) {
1987 DecodeError(pc,
1988 "cannot reference non-shared table %u from shared function",
1989 imm.index);
1990 return false;
1991 }
1992
1993 return true;
1994 }
1995
1996 // The following Validate* functions all validate an `IndexImmediate`, albeit
1997 // differently according to context.
1998 bool ValidateElementSegment(const uint8_t* pc, IndexImmediate& imm) {
1999 size_t num_elem_segments = module_->elem_segments.size();
2000 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_elem_segments)) {
2001 DecodeError(pc, "invalid element segment index: %u", imm.index);
2002 return false;
2003 }
2004 V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_elem_segments);
2005 if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || module_->elem_segments[imm.index].shared)) {
2006 DecodeError(
2007 pc,
2008 "cannot reference non-shared element segment %u from shared function",
2009 imm.index);
2010 return false;
2011 }
2012 return true;
2013 }
2014
2015 bool ValidateLocal(const uint8_t* pc, IndexImmediate& imm) {
2016 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_locals())) {
2017 DecodeError(pc, "invalid local index: %u", imm.index);
2018 return false;
2019 }
2020 return true;
2021 }
2022
2023 bool ValidateFunction(const uint8_t* pc, IndexImmediate& imm) {
2024 size_t num_functions = module_->functions.size();
2025 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_functions)) {
2026 DecodeError(pc, "function index #%u is out of bounds", imm.index);
2027 return false;
2028 }
2029 V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_functions);
2030 if (decoding_mode == kFunctionBody &&
2031 !VALIDATE(module_->functions[imm.index].declared)) {
2032 DecodeError(pc, "undeclared reference to function #%u", imm.index);
2033 return false;
2034 }
2035 return true;
2036 }
2037
2038 bool ValidateDataSegment(const uint8_t* pc, IndexImmediate& imm) {
2039 if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < module_->num_declared_data_segments)) {
2040 DecodeError(pc, "invalid data segment index: %u", imm.index);
2041 return false;
2042 }
2043 // TODO(14616): Data segments aren't available during eager validation.
2044 // Discussion: github.com/WebAssembly/shared-everything-threads/issues/83
2045 if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || module_->data_segments[imm.index].shared)) {
2046 DecodeError(
2047 pc, "cannot refer to non-shared segment %u from a shared function",
2048 imm.index);
2049 return false;
2050 }
2051 return true;
2052 }
2053
2054 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, SelectTypeImmediate& imm) {
2055 return ValidateValueType(pc, imm.type);
2056 }
2057
2058 bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, HeapTypeImmediate& imm) {
2059 return ValidateHeapType(pc, imm.type);
2060 }
2061
2062 bool ValidateValueType(const uint8_t* pc, ValueType type) {
2063 return value_type_reader::ValidateValueType<ValidationTag>(this, pc,
2064 module_, type);
2065 }
2066
2067 bool ValidateHeapType(const uint8_t* pc, HeapType type) {
2068 return value_type_reader::ValidateHeapType<ValidationTag>(this, pc, module_,
2069 type);
2070 }
2071
2072 // Returns the length of the opcode under {pc}.
2073 template <typename... ImmediateObservers>
2074 static uint32_t OpcodeLength(WasmDecoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
2075 ImmediateObservers&... ios) {
2076 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*pc);
2077 // We don't have information about the module here, so we just assume that
2078 // memory64 and multi-memory are enabled when parsing memory access
2079 // immediates. This is backwards-compatible; decode errors will be detected
2080 // at another time when actually decoding that opcode.
2081 constexpr bool kConservativelyAssumeMemory64 = true;
2082 switch (opcode) {
2083 /********** Control opcodes **********/
2084 case kExprUnreachable:
2085 case kExprNop:
2086 case kExprNopForTestingUnsupportedInLiftoff:
2087 case kExprElse:
2088 case kExprEnd:
2089 case kExprReturn:
2090 return 1;
2091 case kExprTry:
2092 case kExprIf:
2093 case kExprLoop:
2094 case kExprBlock: {
2095 BlockTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder, pc + 1,
2096 validate);
2097 (ios.BlockType(imm), ...);
2098 return 1 + imm.length;
2099 }
2100 case kExprRethrow:
2101 case kExprBr:
2102 case kExprBrIf:
2103 case kExprBrOnNull:
2104 case kExprBrOnNonNull:
2105 case kExprDelegate: {
2106 BranchDepthImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2107 (ios.BranchDepth(imm), ...);
2108 return 1 + imm.length;
2109 }
2110 case kExprBrTable: {
2111 BranchTableImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2112 (ios.BranchTable(imm), ...);
2113 BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(decoder, imm);
2114 return 1 + iterator.length();
2115 }
2116 case kExprTryTable: {
2117 BlockTypeImmediate block_type_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder,
2118 pc + 1, validate);
2119 (ios.BlockType(block_type_imm), ...);
2120 TryTableImmediate try_table_imm(decoder, pc + 1 + block_type_imm.length,
2121 validate);
2122 (ios.TryTable(try_table_imm), ...);
2123 TryTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(decoder, try_table_imm);
2124 return 1 + block_type_imm.length + iterator.length();
2125 }
2126 case kExprThrow:
2127 case kExprCatch: {
2128 TagIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2129 (ios.TagIndex(imm), ...);
2130 return 1 + imm.length;
2131 }
2132 case kExprThrowRef:
2133 return 1;
2134
2135 /********** Misc opcodes **********/
2136 case kExprCallFunction:
2137 case kExprReturnCall: {
2138 CallFunctionImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2139 (ios.FunctionIndex(imm), ...);
2140 return 1 + imm.length;
2141 }
2142 case kExprCallIndirect:
2143 case kExprReturnCallIndirect: {
2144 CallIndirectImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2145 (ios.CallIndirect(imm), ...);
2146 return 1 + imm.length;
2147 }
2148 case kExprCallRef:
2149 case kExprReturnCallRef: {
2150 SigIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2151 (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2152 return 1 + imm.length;
2153 }
2154 case kExprDrop:
2155 case kExprSelect:
2156 case kExprCatchAll:
2157 case kExprRefEq:
2158 return 1;
2159 case kExprSelectWithType: {
2160 SelectTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder, pc + 1,
2161 validate);
2162 (ios.SelectType(imm), ...);
2163 return 1 + imm.length;
2164 }
2165
2166 case kExprLocalGet:
2167 case kExprLocalSet:
2168 case kExprLocalTee: {
2169 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, "local index", validate);
2170 (ios.LocalIndex(imm), ...);
2171 return 1 + imm.length;
2172 }
2173 case kExprGlobalGet:
2174 case kExprGlobalSet: {
2175 GlobalIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2176 (ios.GlobalIndex(imm), ...);
2177 return 1 + imm.length;
2178 }
2179 case kExprTableGet:
2180 case kExprTableSet: {
2181 TableIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2182 (ios.TableIndex(imm), ...);
2183 return 1 + imm.length;
2184 }
2185 case kExprI32Const: {
2186 ImmI32Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2187 (ios.I32Const(imm), ...);
2188 return 1 + imm.length;
2189 }
2190 case kExprI64Const: {
2191 ImmI64Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2192 (ios.I64Const(imm), ...);
2193 return 1 + imm.length;
2194 }
2195 case kExprF32Const:
2196 if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2197 ImmF32Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2198 (ios.F32Const(imm), ...);
2199 }
2200 return 5;
2201 case kExprF64Const:
2202 if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2203 ImmF64Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2204 (ios.F64Const(imm), ...);
2205 }
2206 return 9;
2207 case kExprRefNull: {
2208 HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder, pc + 1,
2209 validate);
2210 (ios.HeapType(imm), ...);
2211 return 1 + imm.length;
2212 }
2213 case kExprRefIsNull:
2214 case kExprRefAsNonNull:
2215 return 1;
2216 case kExprRefFunc: {
2217 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, "function index", validate);
2218 (ios.FunctionIndex(imm), ...);
2219 return 1 + imm.length;
2220 }
2221
2222#define DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE(name, ...) case kExpr##name:
2223 // clang-format off
2224 /********** Simple and memory opcodes **********/
2225 FOREACH_SIMPLE_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2226 FOREACH_SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2227 return 1;
2228 FOREACH_LOAD_MEM_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2229 FOREACH_STORE_MEM_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2230 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, UINT32_MAX,
2231 kConservativelyAssumeMemory64,
2232 validate);
2233 (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2234 return 1 + imm.length;
2235 }
2236 // clang-format on
2237 case kExprMemoryGrow:
2238 case kExprMemorySize: {
2239 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2240 (ios.MemoryIndex(imm), ...);
2241 return 1 + imm.length;
2242 }
2243
2244 /********** Prefixed opcodes **********/
2245 case kNumericPrefix: {
2246 uint32_t length;
2247 std::tie(opcode, length) =
2248 decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc);
2249 switch (opcode) {
2250 case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
2251 case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
2252 case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
2253 case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
2254 case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
2255 case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
2256 case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
2257 case kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
2258 return length;
2259 case kExprMemoryInit: {
2260 MemoryInitImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2261 (ios.MemoryInit(imm), ...);
2262 return length + imm.length;
2263 }
2264 case kExprDataDrop: {
2265 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, "data segment index",
2266 validate);
2267 (ios.DataSegmentIndex(imm), ...);
2268 return length + imm.length;
2269 }
2270 case kExprMemoryCopy: {
2271 MemoryCopyImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2272 (ios.MemoryCopy(imm), ...);
2273 return length + imm.length;
2274 }
2275 case kExprMemoryFill: {
2276 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2277 (ios.MemoryIndex(imm), ...);
2278 return length + imm.length;
2279 }
2280 case kExprTableInit: {
2281 TableInitImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2282 (ios.TableInit(imm), ...);
2283 return length + imm.length;
2284 }
2285 case kExprElemDrop: {
2286 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, "element segment index",
2287 validate);
2288 (ios.ElemSegmentIndex(imm), ...);
2289 return length + imm.length;
2290 }
2291 case kExprTableCopy: {
2292 TableCopyImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2293 (ios.TableCopy(imm), ...);
2294 return length + imm.length;
2295 }
2296 case kExprTableGrow:
2297 case kExprTableSize:
2298 case kExprTableFill: {
2299 TableIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2300 (ios.TableIndex(imm), ...);
2301 return length + imm.length;
2302 }
2303 case kExprF32LoadMemF16:
2304 case kExprF32StoreMemF16: {
2305 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2306 kConservativelyAssumeMemory64, validate);
2307 (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2308 return length + imm.length;
2309 }
2310 default:
2311 // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2312 V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2313 decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid numeric opcode");
2314 return length;
2315 }
2316 }
2317 case kSimdPrefix: {
2318 uint32_t length;
2319 std::tie(opcode, length) =
2320 decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc);
2321 switch (opcode) {
2322 // clang-format off
2323 FOREACH_SIMD_0_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2324 return length;
2325 FOREACH_SIMD_1_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2326 if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2327 SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2328 (ios.SimdLane(lane_imm), ...);
2329 }
2330 return length + 1;
2331 FOREACH_SIMD_MEM_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2332 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2333 kConservativelyAssumeMemory64,
2334 validate);
2335 (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2336 return length + imm.length;
2337 }
2338 FOREACH_SIMD_MEM_1_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2339 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(
2340 decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2341 kConservativelyAssumeMemory64,
2342 validate);
2343 if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2344 SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(decoder,
2345 pc + length + imm.length, validate);
2346 (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2347 (ios.SimdLane(lane_imm), ...);
2348 }
2349 // 1 more byte for lane index immediate.
2350 return length + imm.length + 1;
2351 }
2352 // clang-format on
2353 // Shuffles require a byte per lane, or 16 immediate bytes.
2354 case kExprS128Const:
2355 case kExprI8x16Shuffle:
2356 if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2357 Simd128Immediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2358 (ios.S128Const(imm), ...);
2359 }
2360 return length + kSimd128Size;
2361 default:
2362 // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2363 V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2364 decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid SIMD opcode");
2365 return length;
2366 }
2367 }
2368 case kAtomicPrefix: {
2369 uint32_t length;
2370 std::tie(opcode, length) =
2371 decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc, "atomic_index");
2372 switch (opcode) {
2373 FOREACH_ATOMIC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2374 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2375 kConservativelyAssumeMemory64, validate);
2376 (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2377 return length + imm.length;
2378 }
2379 FOREACH_ATOMIC_0_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2380 // One unused zero-byte.
2381 return length + 1;
2382 }
2383 default:
2384 // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2385 V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2386 decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid Atomics opcode");
2387 return length;
2388 }
2389 }
2390 case kGCPrefix: {
2391 uint32_t length;
2392 std::tie(opcode, length) =
2393 decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc, "gc_index");
2394 switch (opcode) {
2395 case kExprStructNew:
2396 case kExprStructNewDefault: {
2397 StructIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2398 (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2399 return length + imm.length;
2400 }
2401 case kExprStructGet:
2402 case kExprStructGetS:
2403 case kExprStructGetU:
2404 case kExprStructSet: {
2405 FieldImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2406 (ios.Field(imm), ...);
2407 return length + imm.length;
2408 }
2409 case kExprArrayNew:
2410 case kExprArrayNewDefault:
2411 case kExprArrayGet:
2412 case kExprArrayGetS:
2413 case kExprArrayGetU:
2414 case kExprArraySet: {
2415 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2416 (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2417 return length + imm.length;
2418 }
2419 case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
2420 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2421 IndexImmediate length_imm(decoder, pc + length + array_imm.length,
2422 "array length", validate);
2423 (ios.TypeIndex(array_imm), ...);
2424 (ios.Length(length_imm), ...);
2425 return length + array_imm.length + length_imm.length;
2426 }
2427 case kExprArrayCopy: {
2428 ArrayIndexImmediate dst_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2429 ArrayIndexImmediate src_imm(decoder, pc + length + dst_imm.length,
2430 validate);
2431 (ios.ArrayCopy(dst_imm, src_imm), ...);
2432 return length + dst_imm.length + src_imm.length;
2433 }
2434 case kExprArrayFill: {
2435 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2436 (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2437 return length + imm.length;
2438 }
2439 case kExprArrayNewData:
2440 case kExprArrayNewElem:
2441 case kExprArrayInitData:
2442 case kExprArrayInitElem: {
2443 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2444 IndexImmediate data_imm(decoder, pc + length + array_imm.length,
2445 "segment index", validate);
2446 (ios.TypeIndex(array_imm), ...);
2447 (ios.DataSegmentIndex(data_imm), ...);
2448 return length + array_imm.length + data_imm.length;
2449 }
2450 case kExprRefCast:
2451 case kExprRefCastNull:
2452 case kExprRefCastNop:
2453 case kExprRefTest:
2454 case kExprRefTestNull: {
2455 HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder,
2456 pc + length, validate);
2457 (ios.HeapType(imm), ...);
2458 return length + imm.length;
2459 }
2460 case kExprBrOnCast:
2461 case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
2462 BrOnCastImmediate flags_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2463 BranchDepthImmediate branch(decoder, pc + length + flags_imm.length,
2464 validate);
2465 HeapTypeImmediate source_imm(
2466 WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder,
2467 pc + length + flags_imm.length + branch.length, validate);
2468 HeapTypeImmediate target_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder,
2469 pc + length + flags_imm.length +
2470 branch.length + source_imm.length,
2471 validate);
2472 (ios.BrOnCastFlags(flags_imm), ...);
2473 (ios.BranchDepth(branch), ...);
2474 // This code has grown historically (while the GC proposal's design
2475 // evolved), but it's convenient: for the text format, we want to
2476 // pretend that we have two ValueTypes; whereas the mjsunit
2477 // module builder format cares only about the encapsulated
2478 // HeapTypes (and the raw flags value, see callback above).
2479 (ios.ValueType(source_imm, flags_imm.flags.src_is_null), ...);
2480 (ios.ValueType(target_imm, flags_imm.flags.res_is_null), ...);
2481 return length + flags_imm.length + branch.length +
2482 source_imm.length + target_imm.length;
2483 }
2484 case kExprRefI31:
2485 case kExprI31GetS:
2486 case kExprI31GetU:
2487 case kExprAnyConvertExtern:
2488 case kExprExternConvertAny:
2489 case kExprArrayLen:
2490 return length;
2491 case kExprStringNewUtf8:
2492 case kExprStringNewUtf8Try:
2493 case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8:
2494 case kExprStringNewWtf8:
2495 case kExprStringEncodeUtf8:
2496 case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8:
2497 case kExprStringEncodeWtf8:
2498 case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeUtf8:
2499 case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeLossyUtf8:
2500 case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeWtf8:
2501 case kExprStringNewWtf16:
2502 case kExprStringEncodeWtf16:
2503 case kExprStringViewWtf16Encode: {
2504 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2505 (ios.MemoryIndex(imm), ...);
2506 return length + imm.length;
2507 }
2508 case kExprStringConst: {
2509 StringConstImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2510 (ios.StringConst(imm), ...);
2511 return length + imm.length;
2512 }
2513 case kExprStringMeasureUtf8:
2514 case kExprStringMeasureWtf8:
2515 case kExprStringNewUtf8Array:
2516 case kExprStringNewUtf8ArrayTry:
2517 case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8Array:
2518 case kExprStringNewWtf8Array:
2519 case kExprStringEncodeUtf8Array:
2520 case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8Array:
2521 case kExprStringEncodeWtf8Array:
2522 case kExprStringMeasureWtf16:
2523 case kExprStringConcat:
2524 case kExprStringEq:
2525 case kExprStringIsUSVSequence:
2526 case kExprStringAsWtf8:
2527 case kExprStringViewWtf8Advance:
2528 case kExprStringViewWtf8Slice:
2529 case kExprStringAsWtf16:
2530 case kExprStringViewWtf16Length:
2531 case kExprStringViewWtf16GetCodeunit:
2532 case kExprStringViewWtf16Slice:
2533 case kExprStringAsIter:
2534 case kExprStringViewIterNext:
2535 case kExprStringViewIterAdvance:
2536 case kExprStringViewIterRewind:
2537 case kExprStringViewIterSlice:
2538 case kExprStringNewWtf16Array:
2539 case kExprStringEncodeWtf16Array:
2540 case kExprStringCompare:
2541 case kExprStringFromCodePoint:
2542 case kExprStringHash:
2543 return length;
2544 default:
2545 // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2546 V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2547 decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid gc opcode");
2548 return length;
2549 }
2550 }
2551
2552 // clang-format off
2553 /********** Asmjs opcodes **********/
2554 FOREACH_ASMJS_COMPAT_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2555 return 1;
2556
2557 // Prefixed opcodes (already handled, included here for completeness of
2558 // switch)
2559 FOREACH_SIMD_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2560 FOREACH_NUMERIC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2561 FOREACH_ATOMIC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2562 FOREACH_ATOMIC_0_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2563 FOREACH_GC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2564 UNREACHABLE();
2565 // clang-format on
2566#undef DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE
2567 }
2568 // Invalid modules will reach this point.
2569 if (ValidationTag::validate) {
2570 decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid opcode");
2571 }
2572 return 1;
2573 }
2574
2575 static constexpr ValidationTag validate = {};
2576
2577 Zone* const zone_;
2578
2579 ValueType* local_types_ = nullptr;
2580 uint32_t num_locals_ = 0;
2581
2582 const WasmModule* module_;
2583 const WasmEnabledFeatures enabled_;
2584 WasmDetectedFeatures* detected_;
2585 const FunctionSig* sig_;
2586 bool is_shared_;
2587 const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t>* current_inst_trace_;
2588};
2589
2590// Only call this in contexts where {current_code_reachable_and_ok_} is known to
2591// hold.
2592#define CALL_INTERFACE(name, ...) \
2593 do { \
2594 DCHECK(!control_.empty()); \
2595 DCHECK(current_code_reachable_and_ok_); \
2596 DCHECK_EQ(current_code_reachable_and_ok_, \
2597 this->ok() && control_.back().reachable()); \
2598 interface_.name(this, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
2599 } while (false)
2600#define CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(name, ...) \
2601 do { \
2602 DCHECK(!control_.empty()); \
2603 DCHECK_EQ(current_code_reachable_and_ok_, \
2604 this->ok() && control_.back().reachable()); \
2605 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) { \
2606 interface_.name(this, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
2607 } \
2608 } while (false)
2609#define CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(name, ...) \
2610 do { \
2611 DCHECK(!control_.empty()); \
2612 if (VALIDATE(this->ok()) && \
2613 (control_.size() == 1 || control_at(1)->reachable())) { \
2614 interface_.name(this, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
2615 } \
2616 } while (false)
2617
2618// An empty class used in place of a {base::SmallVector} for cases where the
2619// content is not needed afterwards.
2620// This is used for implementations which set {kUsesPoppedArgs} to {false}.
2621class NoVector {
2622 public:
2623 // Construct from anything; {NoVector} is always empty.
2624 template <typename... Ts>
2625 explicit NoVector(Ts&&...) V8_NOEXCEPT {}
2626
2627 constexpr std::nullptr_t data() const { return nullptr; }
2628};
2629
2630template <typename ValidationTag, typename Interface,
2631 DecodingMode decoding_mode = kFunctionBody>
2632class WasmFullDecoder : public WasmDecoder<ValidationTag, decoding_mode> {
2633 using Value = typename Interface::Value;
2634 using Control = typename Interface::Control;
2635 using ArgVector = base::Vector<Value>;
2636 using PoppedArgVector =
2637 std::conditional_t<Interface::kUsesPoppedArgs,
2638 base::SmallVector<Value, 8>, NoVector>;
2639 using ReturnVector = base::SmallVector<Value, 2>;
2640
2641 // All Value types should be trivially copyable for performance. We push, pop,
2642 // and store them in local variables.
2643 ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(Value);
2644
2645 public:
2646 template <typename... InterfaceArgs>
2647 WasmFullDecoder(Zone* zone, const WasmModule* module,
2648 WasmEnabledFeatures enabled, WasmDetectedFeatures* detected,
2649 const FunctionBody& body, InterfaceArgs&&... interface_args)
2650 : WasmDecoder<ValidationTag, decoding_mode>(
2651 zone, module, enabled, detected, body.sig, body.is_shared,
2652 body.start, body.end, body.offset),
2653 interface_(std::forward<InterfaceArgs>(interface_args)...),
2654 stack_(16, zone),
2655 control_(16, zone) {}
2656
2657 ~WasmFullDecoder() {
2658 control_.Reset(this->zone_);
2659 stack_.Reset(this->zone_);
2660 locals_initializers_stack_.Reset(this->zone_);
2661 }
2662
2663 Interface& interface() { return interface_; }
2664
2665 void Decode() {
2666 DCHECK(stack_.empty());
2667 DCHECK(control_.empty());
2668 DCHECK_LE(this->pc_, this->end_);
2669 DCHECK_EQ(this->num_locals(), 0);
2670
2671 locals_offset_ = this->pc_offset();
2672 uint32_t locals_length = this->DecodeLocals(this->pc());
2673 if (!VALIDATE(this->ok())) return TraceFailed();
2674 this->consume_bytes(locals_length);
2675 int non_defaultable = 0;
2676 uint32_t params_count =
2677 static_cast<uint32_t>(this->sig_->parameter_count());
2678 for (uint32_t index = params_count; index < this->num_locals(); index++) {
2679 if (!this->local_type(index).is_defaultable()) non_defaultable++;
2680 // We need this because reference locals are initialized with null, and
2681 // later we run a lowering step for null based on {detected_}.
2682 if (this->local_type(index).is_reference()) {
2683 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
2684 }
2685 }
2686 this->InitializeInitializedLocalsTracking(non_defaultable);
2687
2688 // Cannot use CALL_INTERFACE_* macros because control is empty.
2689 interface().StartFunction(this);
2690 DecodeFunctionBody();
2691 // Decoding can fail even without validation, e.g. due to missing Liftoff
2692 // support.
2693 if (this->failed()) return TraceFailed();
2694
2695 if (!VALIDATE(control_.empty())) {
2696 if (control_.size() > 1) {
2697 this->DecodeError(control_.back().pc(),
2698 "unterminated control structure");
2699 } else {
2700 this->DecodeError("function body must end with \"end\" opcode");
2701 }
2702 return TraceFailed();
2703 }
2704 // Cannot use CALL_INTERFACE_* macros because control is empty.
2705 interface().FinishFunction(this);
2706 if (this->failed()) return TraceFailed();
2707
2708 DCHECK(stack_.empty());
2709 TRACE("wasm-decode ok\n\n");
2710 }
2711
2712 void TraceFailed() {
2713 if (this->error_.offset()) {
2714 TRACE("wasm-error module+%-6d func+%d: %s\n\n", this->error_.offset(),
2715 this->GetBufferRelativeOffset(this->error_.offset()),
2716 this->error_.message().c_str());
2717 } else {
2718 TRACE("wasm-error: %s\n\n", this->error_.message().c_str());
2719 }
2720 }
2721
2722 const char* SafeOpcodeNameAt(const uint8_t* pc) {
2723 if (!pc) return "<null>";
2724 if (pc >= this->end_) return "<end>";
2725 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*pc);
2726 if (!WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)) {
2727 return WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(opcode));
2728 }
2729 opcode = this->template read_prefixed_opcode<Decoder::FullValidationTag>(pc)
2730 .first;
2731 return WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode);
2732 }
2733
2734 WasmCodePosition position() const {
2735 int offset = static_cast<int>(this->pc_ - this->start_);
2736 DCHECK_EQ(this->pc_ - this->start_, offset); // overflows cannot happen
2737 return offset;
2738 }
2739
2740 uint32_t control_depth() const {
2741 return static_cast<uint32_t>(control_.size());
2742 }
2743
2744 Control* control_at(uint32_t depth) {
2745 DCHECK_GT(control_.size(), depth);
2746 return control_.end() - 1 - depth;
2747 }
2748
2749 uint32_t stack_size() const { return stack_.size(); }
2750
2751 Value* stack_value(uint32_t depth) const {
2752 DCHECK_LT(0, depth);
2753 DCHECK_GE(stack_.size(), depth);
2754 return stack_.end() - depth;
2755 }
2756
2757 int32_t current_catch() const { return current_catch_; }
2758
2759 uint32_t control_depth_of_current_catch() const {
2760 return control_depth() - 1 - current_catch();
2761 }
2762
2763 uint32_t pc_relative_offset() const {
2764 return this->pc_offset() - locals_offset_;
2765 }
2766
2767 bool is_local_initialized(uint32_t local_index) {
2768 DCHECK_GT(this->num_locals_, local_index);
2769 if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return true;
2770 return initialized_locals_[local_index];
2771 }
2772
2773 void set_local_initialized(uint32_t local_index) {
2774 DCHECK_GT(this->num_locals_, local_index);
2775 if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return;
2776 // This implicitly covers defaultable locals too (which are always
2777 // initialized).
2778 if (is_local_initialized(local_index)) return;
2779 initialized_locals_[local_index] = true;
2780 locals_initializers_stack_.push(local_index);
2781 }
2782
2783 uint32_t locals_initialization_stack_depth() const {
2784 return static_cast<uint32_t>(locals_initializers_stack_.size());
2785 }
2786
2787 void RollbackLocalsInitialization(Control* c) {
2788 if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return;
2789 uint32_t previous_stack_height = c->init_stack_depth;
2790 while (locals_initializers_stack_.size() > previous_stack_height) {
2791 uint32_t local_index = locals_initializers_stack_.back();
2792 locals_initializers_stack_.pop();
2793 initialized_locals_[local_index] = false;
2794 }
2795 }
2796
2797 void InitializeInitializedLocalsTracking(int non_defaultable_locals) {
2798 has_nondefaultable_locals_ = non_defaultable_locals > 0;
2799 if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return;
2800 initialized_locals_ =
2801 this->zone_->template AllocateArray<bool>(this->num_locals_);
2802 // Parameters are always initialized.
2803 const size_t num_params = this->sig_->parameter_count();
2804 std::fill_n(initialized_locals_, num_params, true);
2805 // Locals are initialized if they are defaultable.
2806 for (size_t i = num_params; i < this->num_locals_; i++) {
2807 initialized_locals_[i] = this->local_types_[i].is_defaultable();
2808 }
2809 DCHECK(locals_initializers_stack_.empty());
2810 locals_initializers_stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(non_defaultable_locals,
2811 this->zone_);
2812 }
2813
2814 void DecodeFunctionBody() {
2815 TRACE("wasm-decode %p...%p (module+%u, %d bytes)\n", this->start(),
2816 this->end(), this->pc_offset(),
2817 static_cast<int>(this->end() - this->start()));
2818
2819 // Set up initial function block.
2820 {
2821 DCHECK(control_.empty());
2822 constexpr uint32_t kStackDepth = 0;
2823 constexpr uint32_t kInitStackDepth = 0;
2824 control_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
2825 control_.emplace_back(this->zone_, kControlBlock, kStackDepth,
2826 kInitStackDepth, this->pc_, kReachable);
2827 Control* c = &control_.back();
2828 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kFunctionBody) {
2829 InitMerge(&c->start_merge, 0, nullptr);
2830 InitMerge(&c->end_merge,
2831 static_cast<uint32_t>(this->sig_->return_count()),
2832 [this](uint32_t i) {
2833 return Value{this->pc_, this->sig_->GetReturn(i)};
2834 });
2835 } else {
2836 DCHECK_EQ(this->sig_->parameter_count(), 0);
2837 DCHECK_EQ(this->sig_->return_count(), 1);
2838 c->start_merge.arity = 0;
2839 c->end_merge.arity = 1;
2840 c->end_merge.vals.first = Value{this->pc_, this->sig_->GetReturn(0)};
2841 }
2842 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StartFunctionBody, c);
2843 }
2844
2845 if (V8_LIKELY(this->current_inst_trace_->first == 0)) {
2846 // Decode the function body.
2847 while (this->pc_ < this->end_) {
2848 // Most operations only grow the stack by at least one element (unary
2849 // and binary operations, local.get, constants, ...). Thus check that
2850 // there is enough space for those operations centrally, and avoid any
2851 // bounds checks in those operations.
2852 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
2853 uint8_t first_byte = *this->pc_;
2854 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(first_byte);
2855 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(NextInstruction, opcode);
2856 int len;
2857 // Allowing two of the most common decoding functions to get inlined
2858 // appears to be the sweet spot.
2859 // Handling _all_ opcodes via a giant switch-statement has been tried
2860 // and found to be slower than calling through the handler table.
2861 if (opcode == kExprLocalGet) {
2862 len = WasmFullDecoder::DecodeLocalGet(this, opcode);
2863 } else if (opcode == kExprI32Const) {
2864 len = WasmFullDecoder::DecodeI32Const(this, opcode);
2865 } else {
2866 OpcodeHandler handler = GetOpcodeHandler(first_byte);
2867 len = (*handler)(this, opcode);
2868 }
2869 this->pc_ += len;
2870 }
2871
2872 } else {
2873 // Decode the function body.
2874 while (this->pc_ < this->end_) {
2875 DCHECK(this->current_inst_trace_->first == 0 ||
2876 this->current_inst_trace_->first >= this->pc_offset());
2877 if (V8_UNLIKELY(this->current_inst_trace_->first ==
2878 this->pc_offset())) {
2879 TRACE("Emit trace at 0x%x with ID[0x%x]\n", this->pc_offset(),
2880 this->current_inst_trace_->second);
2881 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TraceInstruction,
2882 this->current_inst_trace_->second);
2883 this->current_inst_trace_++;
2884 }
2885
2886 // Most operations only grow the stack by at least one element (unary
2887 // and binary operations, local.get, constants, ...). Thus check that
2888 // there is enough space for those operations centrally, and avoid any
2889 // bounds checks in those operations.
2890 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
2891 uint8_t first_byte = *this->pc_;
2892 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(first_byte);
2893 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(NextInstruction, opcode);
2894 OpcodeHandler handler = GetOpcodeHandler(first_byte);
2895 int len = (*handler)(this, opcode);
2896 this->pc_ += len;
2897 }
2898 }
2899
2900 // Even without validation, compilation could fail because of bailouts,
2901 // e.g., unsupported operations in Liftoff or the decoder for Wasm-in-JS
2902 // inlining. In those cases, {pc_} did not necessarily advance until {end_}.
2903 if (this->pc_ != this->end_) {
2904 // `DecodeError` is only available when validating, hence this guard.
2905 if constexpr (ValidationTag::validate) {
2906 this->DecodeError("Beyond end of code");
2907 }
2908 }
2909 }
2910
2911 bool HasCatchAll(Control* block) const {
2912 DCHECK(block->is_try_table());
2913 return std::any_of(block->catch_cases.begin(), block->catch_cases.end(),
2914 [](const struct CatchCase& catch_case) {
2915 return catch_case.kind == kCatchAll ||
2916 catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef;
2917 });
2918 }
2919
2920 private:
2921 uint32_t locals_offset_ = 0;
2922 Interface interface_;
2923
2924 // The value stack, stored as individual pointers for maximum performance.
2925 FastZoneVector<Value> stack_;
2926
2927 // Indicates whether the local with the given index is currently initialized.
2928 // Entries for defaultable locals are meaningless; we have a byte for each
2929 // local because we expect that the effort required to densify this bit
2930 // vector would more than offset the memory savings.
2931 bool* initialized_locals_;
2932 // Keeps track of initializing assignments to non-defaultable locals that
2933 // happened, so they can be discarded at the end of the current block.
2934 // Contains no duplicates, so the size of this stack is bounded (and pre-
2935 // allocated) to the number of non-defaultable locals in the function.
2936 FastZoneVector<uint32_t> locals_initializers_stack_;
2937
2938 // Control stack (blocks, loops, ifs, ...).
2939 FastZoneVector<Control> control_;
2940
2941 // Controls whether code should be generated for the current block (basically
2942 // a cache for {ok() && control_.back().reachable()}).
2943 bool current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = true;
2944
2945 // Performance optimization: bail out of any functions dealing with non-
2946 // defaultable locals early when there are no such locals anyway.
2947 bool has_nondefaultable_locals_ = true;
2948
2949 // Depth of the current try block.
2950 int32_t current_catch_ = -1;
2951
2952 static Value UnreachableValue(const uint8_t* pc) {
2953 return Value{pc, kWasmBottom};
2954 }
2955
2956 void SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable() {
2957 Control* current = &control_.back();
2958 if (current->reachable()) {
2959 current->reachability = kSpecOnlyReachable;
2960 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = false;
2961 }
2962 }
2963
2964 // Mark that the current try-catch block might throw.
2965 // We only generate catch handlers for blocks that might throw.
2966 void MarkMightThrow() {
2967 if (!current_code_reachable_and_ok_ || current_catch() == -1) return;
2968 control_at(control_depth_of_current_catch())->might_throw = true;
2969 }
2970
2971 V8_INLINE ValueType TableAddressType(const WasmTable* table) {
2972 return table->is_table64() ? kWasmI64 : kWasmI32;
2973 }
2974
2975 V8_INLINE ValueType MemoryAddressType(const WasmMemory* memory) {
2976 return memory->is_memory64() ? kWasmI64 : kWasmI32;
2977 }
2978
2979 V8_INLINE MemoryAccessImmediate
2980 MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(uint32_t pc_offset, uint32_t max_alignment) {
2981 return MemoryAccessImmediate(this, this->pc_ + pc_offset, max_alignment,
2982 this->enabled_.has_memory64(), validate);
2983 }
2984
2985#ifdef DEBUG
2986 class TraceLine {
2987 public:
2988 explicit TraceLine(WasmFullDecoder* decoder) : decoder_(decoder) {
2989 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*decoder->pc());
2990 if (!WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)) AppendOpcode(opcode);
2991 }
2992
2993 void AppendOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode) {
2994 DCHECK(!WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode));
2995 Append(TRACE_INST_FORMAT, decoder_->startrel(decoder_->pc_),
2996 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
2997 }
2998
2999 ~TraceLine() {
3000 if (!v8_flags.trace_wasm_decoder) return;
3001 AppendStackState();
3002 PrintF("%.*s\n", len_, buffer_);
3003 }
3004
3005 // Appends a formatted string.
3006 PRINTF_FORMAT(2, 3)
3007 void Append(const char* format, ...) {
3008 if (!v8_flags.trace_wasm_decoder) return;
3009 va_list va_args;
3010 va_start(va_args, format);
3011 size_t remaining_len = kMaxLen - len_;
3012 base::Vector<char> remaining_msg_space(buffer_ + len_, remaining_len);
3013 int len = base::VSNPrintF(remaining_msg_space, format, va_args);
3014 va_end(va_args);
3015 len_ += len < 0 ? remaining_len : len;
3016 }
3017
3018 private:
3019 void AppendStackState() {
3020 DCHECK(v8_flags.trace_wasm_decoder);
3021 Append(" ");
3022 for (Control& c : decoder_->control_) {
3023 switch (c.kind) {
3024 case kControlIf:
3025 Append("I");
3026 break;
3027 case kControlBlock:
3028 Append("B");
3029 break;
3030 case kControlLoop:
3031 Append("L");
3032 break;
3033 case kControlTry:
3034 Append("T");
3035 break;
3036 case kControlTryTable:
3037 Append("T");
3038 break;
3039 case kControlIfElse:
3040 Append("E");
3041 break;
3042 case kControlTryCatch:
3043 Append("C");
3044 break;
3045 case kControlTryCatchAll:
3046 Append("A");
3047 break;
3048 }
3049 if (c.start_merge.arity) Append("%u-", c.start_merge.arity);
3050 Append("%u", c.end_merge.arity);
3051 if (!c.reachable()) Append("%c", c.unreachable() ? '*' : '#');
3052 }
3053 Append(" | ");
3054 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < decoder_->stack_.size(); ++i) {
3055 Value& val = decoder_->stack_[i];
3056 Append(" %c", val.type.short_name());
3057 }
3058 }
3059
3060 static constexpr int kMaxLen = 512;
3061
3062 char buffer_[kMaxLen];
3063 int len_ = 0;
3064 WasmFullDecoder* const decoder_;
3065 };
3066#else
3067 class TraceLine {
3068 public:
3069 explicit TraceLine(WasmFullDecoder*) {}
3070
3071 void AppendOpcode(WasmOpcode) {}
3072
3073 PRINTF_FORMAT(2, 3)
3074 void Append(const char* format, ...) {}
3075 };
3076#endif
3077
3078#define DECODE(name) \
3079 static int Decode##name(WasmFullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode) { \
3080 TraceLine trace_msg(decoder); \
3081 return decoder->Decode##name##Impl(&trace_msg, opcode); \
3082 } \
3083 V8_INLINE int Decode##name##Impl(TraceLine* trace_msg, WasmOpcode opcode)
3084
3085 DECODE(Nop) { return 1; }
3086
3087 DECODE(NopForTestingUnsupportedInLiftoff) {
3088 if (!VALIDATE(v8_flags.enable_testing_opcode_in_wasm)) {
3089 this->DecodeError("Invalid opcode 0x%x", opcode);
3090 return 0;
3091 }
3092 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(NopForTestingUnsupportedInLiftoff);
3093 // Return {0} if we failed, to not advance the pc past the end.
3094 if (this->failed()) {
3095 DCHECK_EQ(this->pc_, this->end_);
3096 return 0;
3097 }
3098 return 1;
3099 }

3101#define BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE(op, _, sig, ...) \
3102 DECODE(op) { return BuildSimpleOperator_##sig(kExpr##op); }
3103 FOREACH_SIMPLE_NON_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE)
3104#undef BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE
3105
3106#define BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE(op, _, sig, ...) \
3107 DECODE(op) { \
3108 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) { \
3109 this->detected_->add_extended_const(); \
3110 } \
3111 return BuildSimpleOperator_##sig(kExpr##op); \
3112 }
3113 FOREACH_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE)
3114#undef BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE

3116 DECODE(Block) {
3117 BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3118 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3119 Control* block = PushControl(kControlBlock, imm);
3120 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Block, block);
3121 return 1 + imm.length;
3122 }
3123
3124 DECODE(Rethrow) {
3125 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3126 BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3127 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3128 Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3129 if (!VALIDATE(c->is_try_catchall() || c->is_try_catch())) {
3130 this->error("rethrow not targeting catch or catch-all");
3131 return 0;
3132 }
3133 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Rethrow, c);
3134 MarkMightThrow();
3135 EndControl();
3136 return 1 + imm.length;
3137 }
3138
3139 DECODE(Throw) {
3140 // This instruction is the same for legacy EH and exnref.
3141 // Count it as exnref if exnref is enabled so that we have an accurate eh
3142 // count for the deprecation plans.
3143 this->detected_->Add(this->enabled_.has_exnref()
3144 ? WasmDetectedFeature::exnref
3145 : WasmDetectedFeature::legacy_eh);
3146 TagIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3147 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3148 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.tag->ToFunctionSig());
3149 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Throw, imm, args.data());
3150 MarkMightThrow();
3151 EndControl();
3152 return 1 + imm.length;
3153 }
3154
3155 DECODE(Try) {
3156 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3157 BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3158 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3159 Control* try_block = PushControl(kControlTry, imm);
3160 try_block->previous_catch = current_catch_;
3161 current_catch_ = static_cast<int>(control_depth() - 1);
3162 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Try, try_block);
3163 return 1 + imm.length;
3164 }
3165
3166 DECODE(Catch) {
3167 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3168 TagIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3169 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3170 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3171 Control* c = &control_.back();
3172 if (!VALIDATE(c->is_try())) {
3173 this->DecodeError("catch does not match a try");
3174 return 0;
3175 }
3176 if (!VALIDATE(!c->is_try_catchall())) {
3177 this->DecodeError("catch after catch-all for try");
3178 return 0;
3179 }
3180 FallThrough();
3181 c->kind = kControlTryCatch;
3182 stack_.shrink_to(c->stack_depth);
3183 c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3184 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3185 RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
3186 const WasmTagSig* sig = imm.tag->sig;
3187 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()),
3188 this->zone_);
3189 for (ValueType type : sig->parameters()) Push(type);
3190 base::Vector<Value> values(stack_.begin() + c->stack_depth,
3191 sig->parameter_count());
3192 current_catch_ = c->previous_catch; // Pop try scope.
3193 // If there is a throwing instruction in `c`, generate the header for a
3194 // catch block. Otherwise, the catch block is unreachable.
3195 if (c->might_throw) {
3196 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchException, imm, c, values);
3197 } else {
3198 SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
3199 }
3200 return 1 + imm.length;
3201 }
3202
3203 DECODE(Delegate) {
3204 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3205 BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3206 // -1 because the current try block is not included in the count.
3207 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_depth() - 1)) return 0;
3208 Control* c = &control_.back();
3209 if (!VALIDATE(c->is_incomplete_try())) {
3210 this->DecodeError("delegate does not match a try");
3211 return 0;
3212 }
3213 // +1 because the current try block is not included in the count.
3214 uint32_t target_depth = imm.depth + 1;
3215 while (target_depth < control_depth() - 1 &&
3216 (!control_at(target_depth)->is_try() ||
3217 control_at(target_depth)->is_try_catch() ||
3218 control_at(target_depth)->is_try_catchall())) {
3219 target_depth++;
3220 }
3221 FallThrough();
3222 if (c->might_throw) {
3223 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(Delegate, target_depth, c);
3224 // Delegate propagates the `might_throw` status to the delegated-to block.
3225 if (control_at(1)->reachable() && target_depth != control_depth() - 1) {
3226 control_at(target_depth)->might_throw = true;
3227 }
3228 }
3229 current_catch_ = c->previous_catch;
3230 EndControl();
3231 PopControl();
3232 return 1 + imm.length;
3233 }
3234
3235 DECODE(CatchAll) {
3236 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3237 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3238 Control* c = &control_.back();
3239 if (!VALIDATE(c->is_try())) {
3240 this->DecodeError("catch-all does not match a try");
3241 return 0;
3242 }
3243 if (!VALIDATE(!c->is_try_catchall())) {
3244 this->error("catch-all already present for try");
3245 return 0;
3246 }
3247 FallThrough();
3248 c->kind = kControlTryCatchAll;
3249 c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3250 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3251 RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
3252 current_catch_ = c->previous_catch; // Pop try scope.
3253 // If there is a throwing instruction in `c`, generate the header for a
3254 // catch block. Otherwise, the catch block is unreachable.
3255 if (c->might_throw) {
3256 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchAll, c);
3257 } else {
3258 SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
3259 }
3260 stack_.shrink_to(c->stack_depth);
3261 return 1;
3262 }
3263
3264 DECODE(TryTable) {
3265 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(exnref);
3266 BlockTypeImmediate block_imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3267 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, block_imm)) return 0;
3268 Control* try_block = PushControl(kControlTryTable, block_imm);
3269 TryTableImmediate try_table_imm(this, this->pc_ + 1 + block_imm.length,
3270 validate);
3271 if (try_table_imm.table_count > 0) {
3272 try_block->previous_catch = current_catch_;
3273 current_catch_ = static_cast<int>(control_depth() - 1);
3274 }
3275 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 2, try_table_imm)) return 0;
3276 TryTableIterator<ValidationTag> try_table_iterator(this, try_table_imm);
3277 try_block->catch_cases = this->zone_->template AllocateVector<CatchCase>(
3278 try_table_imm.table_count);
3279 int i = 0;
3280 while (try_table_iterator.has_next()) {
3281 CatchCase catch_case = try_table_iterator.next();
3282 if (!VALIDATE(catch_case.kind <= kLastCatchKind)) {
3283 this->DecodeError("invalid catch kind in try table");
3284 return 0;
3285 }
3286 if ((catch_case.kind == kCatch || catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) &&
3287 !this->Validate(this->pc_, catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm)) {
3288 return 0;
3289 }
3290 catch_case.br_imm.depth += 1;
3291 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_, catch_case.br_imm, control_.size())) {
3292 return 0;
3293 }
3294
3295 uint32_t stack_size = stack_.size();
3296 uint32_t push_count = 0;
3297 if (catch_case.kind == kCatch || catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) {
3298 const WasmTagSig* sig = catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig;
3299 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()),
3300 this->zone_);
3301 for (ValueType type : sig->parameters()) Push(type);
3302 push_count += sig->parameter_count();
3303 }
3304 if (catch_case.kind == kCatchRef || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3305 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
3306 Push(ValueType::Ref(HeapType::kExn));
3307 push_count += 1;
3308 }
3309 Control* target = control_at(catch_case.br_imm.depth);
3310 if (!VALIDATE(push_count == target->br_merge()->arity)) {
3311 this->DecodeError(
3312 "catch kind generates %d operand%s, target block expects %d",
3313 push_count, push_count != 1 ? "s" : "", target->br_merge()->arity);
3314 return 0;
3315 }
3316 if (!VALIDATE(
3317 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
3318 target)))) {
3319 return 0;
3320 }
3321 stack_.shrink_to(stack_size);
3322 DCHECK_LT(i, try_table_imm.table_count);
3323 try_block->catch_cases[i] = catch_case;
3324 ++i;
3325 }
3326 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TryTable, try_block);
3327 return 1 + block_imm.length + try_table_iterator.length();
3328 }
3329
3330 DECODE(ThrowRef) {
3331 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(exnref);
3332 Value value = Pop(kWasmExnRef);
3333 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ThrowRef, &value);
3334 MarkMightThrow();
3335 EndControl();
3336 return 1;
3337 }
3338
3339 DECODE(BrOnNull) {
3340 this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
3341 BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3342 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3343 Value ref_object = Pop();
3344 Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3345 if (!VALIDATE(
3346 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
3347 c)))) {
3348 return 0;
3349 }
3350 switch (ref_object.type.kind()) {
3351 case kBottom:
3352 // We are in a polymorphic stack. Leave the stack as it is.
3353 DCHECK(!current_code_reachable_and_ok_);
3354 [[fallthrough]];
3355 case kRef:
3356 // For a non-nullable value, we won't take the branch, and can leave
3357 // the stack as it is.
3358 Push(ref_object);
3359 break;
3360 case kRefNull: {
3361 Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(ref_object.type.heap_type()));
3362 // The result of br_on_null has the same value as the argument (but a
3363 // non-nullable type).
3364 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3365 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNull, ref_object, imm.depth, false, result);
3366 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3367 }
3368 break;
3369 }
3370 default:
3371 PopTypeError(0, ref_object, "object reference");
3372 return 0;
3373 }
3374 return 1 + imm.length;
3375 }
3376
3377 DECODE(BrOnNonNull) {
3378 this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
3379 BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3380 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3381 Value ref_object = Pop();
3382 if (!VALIDATE(ref_object.type.is_object_reference() ||
3383 ref_object.type.is_bottom())) {
3384 PopTypeError(
3385 0, ref_object,
3386 "subtype of ((ref null any), (ref null extern) or (ref null func))");
3387 return 0;
3388 }
3389 // Typechecking the branch and creating the branch merges requires the
3390 // non-null value on the stack, so we push it temporarily.
3391 Value* value_on_branch = Push(ref_object.type.AsNonNull());
3392 Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3393 if (!VALIDATE(
3394 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
3395 c)))) {
3396 return 0;
3397 }
3398 switch (ref_object.type.kind()) {
3399 case kBottom:
3400 // We are in unreachable code. Do nothing.
3401 DCHECK(!current_code_reachable_and_ok_);
3402 break;
3403 case kRef:
3404 // For a non-nullable value, we always take the branch.
3405 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3406 CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, ref_object, value_on_branch);
3407 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, imm.depth);
3408 // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
3409 // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
3410 SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
3411 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3412 }
3413 break;
3414 case kRefNull: {
3415 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3416 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNonNull, ref_object, value_on_branch, imm.depth,
3417 true);
3418 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3419 }
3420 break;
3421 }
3422 default:
3423 PopTypeError(0, ref_object, "object reference");
3424 return 0;
3425 }
3426 Drop(*value_on_branch);
3427 return 1 + imm.length;
3428 }
3429
3430 DECODE(Loop) {
3431 BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3432 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3433 Control* block = PushControl(kControlLoop, imm);
3434 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Loop, block);
3435 // Loops have a merge point at block entry, hence push the merge values
3436 // (Phis in case of TurboFan) after calling the interface.
3437 // TODO(clemensb): Can we skip this (and the related PushMergeValues in
3438 // PopControl) for Liftoff?
3439 PushMergeValues(block, &block->start_merge);
3440 return 1 + imm.length;
3441 }
3442
3443 DECODE(If) {
3444 BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3445 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3446 Value cond = Pop(kWasmI32);
3447 Control* if_block = PushControl(kControlIf, imm);
3448 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(If, cond, if_block);
3449 return 1 + imm.length;
3450 }
3451
3452 DECODE(Else) {
3453 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3454 Control* c = &control_.back();
3455 if (!VALIDATE(c->is_if())) {
3456 this->DecodeError("else does not match an if");
3457 return 0;
3458 }
3459 if (!VALIDATE(c->is_onearmed_if())) {
3460 this->DecodeError("else already present for if");
3461 return 0;
3462 }
3463 if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckFallThru())) return 0;
3464 c->kind = kControlIfElse;
3465 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(Else, c);
3466 if (c->reachable()) c->end_merge.reached = true;
3467 RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
3468 PushMergeValues(c, &c->start_merge);
3469 c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3470 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3471 return 1;
3472 }
3473
3474 DECODE(End) {
3475 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3476 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kFunctionBody) {
3477 Control* c = &control_.back();
3478 if (c->is_incomplete_try()) {
3479 // Catch-less try, fall through to the implicit catch-all.
3480 c->kind = kControlTryCatch;
3481 current_catch_ = c->previous_catch; // Pop try scope.
3482 }
3483 if (c->is_try_catch()) {
3484 // Emulate catch-all + re-throw.
3485 FallThrough();
3486 c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3487 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3488 // Cache `c->might_throw` so we can access it safely after `c`'s
3489 // destructor is called in `PopContol()`.
3490 bool might_throw = c->might_throw;
3491 if (might_throw) {
3492 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchAll, c);
3493 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Rethrow, c);
3494 }
3495 EndControl();
3496 PopControl();
3497 // We must mark the parent catch block as `might_throw`, since this
3498 // conceptually rethrows. Note that we do this regardless of whether
3499 // the code at this point is reachable.
3500 if (might_throw && current_catch() != -1) {
3501 control_at(control_depth_of_current_catch())->might_throw = true;
3502 }
3503 return 1;
3504 }
3505 if (c->is_onearmed_if()) {
3506 if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckOneArmedIf(c))) return 0;
3507 }
3508 if (c->is_try_table()) {
3509 // "Pop" the {current_catch_} index. We did not push it if the block has
3510 // no handler, so also skip it here in this case.
3511 if (c->catch_cases.size() > 0) {
3512 current_catch_ = c->previous_catch;
3513 }
3514 FallThrough();
3515 // Temporarily set the reachability for the catch handlers, and restore
3516 // it before we actually exit the try block.
3517 Reachability reachability_at_end = c->reachability;
3518 c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3519 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3520 for (CatchCase& catch_case : c->catch_cases) {
3521 uint32_t stack_size = stack_.size();
3522 size_t push_count = 0;
3523 if (catch_case.kind == kCatch || catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) {
3524 const WasmTagSig* sig = catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig;
3525 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()),
3526 this->zone_);
3527 for (ValueType type : sig->parameters()) Push(type);
3528 push_count = sig->parameter_count();
3529 }
3530 if (catch_case.kind == kCatchRef || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3531 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
3532 Push(ValueType::Ref(HeapType::kExn));
3533 push_count += 1;
3534 }
3535 base::Vector<Value> values(
3536 stack_.begin() + stack_.size() - push_count, push_count);
3537 if (c->might_throw) {
3538 // Already type checked on block entry.
3539 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchCase, c, catch_case,
3540 values);
3541 if (current_code_reachable_and_ok_) {
3542 Control* target = control_at(catch_case.br_imm.depth);
3543 target->br_merge()->reached = true;
3544 }
3545 }
3546 stack_.shrink_to(stack_size);
3547 if (catch_case.kind == kCatchAll || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3548 break;
3549 }
3550 }
3551 c->reachability = reachability_at_end;
3552 // If there is no catch-all case, we must mark the parent catch block as
3553 // `might_throw`, since this conceptually rethrows. Note that we do this
3554 // regardless of whether the code at this point is reachable.
3555 if (c->might_throw && !HasCatchAll(c) && current_catch() != -1) {
3556 control_at(control_depth_of_current_catch())->might_throw = true;
3557 }
3558 EndControl();
3559 PopControl();
3560 return 1;
3561 }
3562 }
3563
3564 if (control_.size() == 1) {
3565 // We need to call this first because the interface might set
3566 // {this->end_}, making the next check pass.
3567 DoReturn<kStrictCounting, decoding_mode == kFunctionBody
3568 ? kFallthroughMerge
3569 : kInitExprMerge>();
3570 // If at the last (implicit) control, check we are at end.
3571 if (!VALIDATE(this->pc_ + 1 == this->end_)) {
3572 this->DecodeError(this->pc_ + 1, "trailing code after function end");
3573 return 0;
3574 }
3575 // The result of the block is the return value.
3576 trace_msg->Append("\n" TRACE_INST_FORMAT, startrel(this->pc_),
3577 "(implicit) return");
3578 control_.pop();
3579 return 1;
3580 }
3581
3582 if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckFallThru())) return 0;
3583 PopControl();
3584 return 1;
3585 }
3586
3587 DECODE(Select) {
3588 auto [tval, fval, cond] = Pop(kWasmBottom, kWasmBottom, kWasmI32);
3589 ValueType result_type = tval.type;
3590 if (result_type == kWasmBottom) {
3591 result_type = fval.type;
3592 } else {
3593 ValidateStackValue(1, fval, result_type);
3594 }
3595 if (!VALIDATE(!result_type.is_reference())) {
3596 this->DecodeError(
3597 "select without type is only valid for value type inputs");
3598 return 0;
3599 }
3600 Value* result = Push(result_type);
3601 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Select, cond, fval, tval, result);
3602 return 1;
3603 }
3604
3605 DECODE(SelectWithType) {
3606 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
3607 SelectTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3608 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3609 auto [tval, fval, cond] = Pop(imm.type, imm.type, kWasmI32);
3610 Value* result = Push(imm.type);
3611 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Select, cond, fval, tval, result);
3612 return 1 + imm.length;
3613 }

3615 DECODE(Br) {
3616 BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3617 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3618 Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3619 if (!VALIDATE(
3620 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kNo, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
3621 c)))) {
3622 return 0;
3623 }
3624 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3625 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, imm.depth);
3626 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3627 }
3628 EndControl();
3629 return 1 + imm.length;
3630 }
3631
3632 DECODE(BrIf) {
3633 BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3634 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3635 Value cond = Pop(kWasmI32);
3636 Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3637 if (!VALIDATE(
3638 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
3639 c)))) {
3640 return 0;
3641 }
3642 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3643 CALL_INTERFACE(BrIf, cond, imm.depth);
3644 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3645 }
