3646 return 1 + imm.length;
3647 }
3648
3649 DECODE(BrTable) {
3650 BranchTableImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3651 BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(this, imm);
3652 Value key = Pop(kWasmI32);
3653 if (!VALIDATE(this->ok())) return 0;
3654 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3655
3656 // Cache the branch targets during the iteration, so that we can set
3657 // all branch targets as reachable after the {CALL_INTERFACE} call.
3658 SmallZoneVector<bool, 32> br_targets(control_.size(), this->zone());
3659 std::uninitialized_fill(br_targets.begin(), br_targets.end(), false);
3660
3661 uint32_t arity = 0;
3662
3663 while (iterator.has_next()) {
3664 const uint32_t index = iterator.cur_index();
3665 const uint8_t* pos = iterator.pc();
3666 const uint32_t target = iterator.next();
3667 if (!VALIDATE(target < control_depth())) {
3668 this->DecodeError(pos, "invalid branch depth: %u", target);
3669 return 0;
3670 }
3671 // Avoid redundant branch target checks.
3672 if (br_targets[target]) continue;
3673 br_targets[target] = true;
3674
3675 if (ValidationTag::validate) {
3676 if (index == 0) {
3677 arity = control_at(target)->br_merge()->arity;
3678 } else if (!VALIDATE(control_at(target)->br_merge()->arity == arity)) {
3679 this->DecodeError(
3680 pos, "br_table: label arity inconsistent with previous arity %d",
3681 arity);
3682 return 0;
3683 }
3684 if (!VALIDATE(
3685 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kNo, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
3686 control_at(target))))) {
3687 return 0;
3688 }
3689 }
3690 }
3691
3692 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3693 CALL_INTERFACE(BrTable, imm, key);
3694
3695 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < control_depth(); ++i) {
3696 control_at(i)->br_merge()->reached |= br_targets[i];
3697 }
3698 }
3699 EndControl();
3700 return 1 + iterator.length();
3701 }
3702
3703 DECODE(Return) {
3704 return DoReturn<kNonStrictCounting, kReturnMerge>() ? 1 : 0;
3705 }
3706
3707 DECODE(Unreachable) {
3708 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Trap, TrapReason::kTrapUnreachable);
3709 EndControl();
3710 return 1;
3711 }
3712
3713 DECODE(I32Const) {
3714 ImmI32Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3715 Value* value = Push(kWasmI32);
3716 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I32Const, value, imm.value);
3717 return 1 + imm.length;
3718 }
3719
3720 DECODE(I64Const) {
3721 ImmI64Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3722 Value* value = Push(kWasmI64);
3723 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I64Const, value, imm.value);
3724 return 1 + imm.length;
3725 }
3726
3727 DECODE(F32Const) {
3728 ImmF32Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3729 Value* value = Push(kWasmF32);
3730 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(F32Const, value, imm.value);
3731 return 1 + imm.length;
3732 }
3733
3734 DECODE(F64Const) {
3735 ImmF64Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3736 Value* value = Push(kWasmF64);
3737 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(F64Const, value, imm.value);
3738 return 1 + imm.length;
3739 }
3740
3741 DECODE(RefNull) {
3742 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
3743 HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3744 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3745 if (!VALIDATE(!this->enabled_.has_stringref() ||
3746 !imm.type.is_string_view())) {
3747 this->DecodeError(this->pc_ + 1, "cannot create null string view");
3748 return 0;
3749 }
3750 ValueType type = ValueType::RefNull(imm.type);
3751 Value* value = Push(type);
3752 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefNull, type, value);
3753 return 1 + imm.length;
3754 }
3755
3756 DECODE(RefIsNull) {
3757 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
3758 Value value = Pop();
3759 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
3760 switch (value.type.kind()) {
3761 case kRefNull:
3762 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, kExprRefIsNull, value, result);
3763 return 1;
3764 case kBottom:
3765 // We are in unreachable code, the return value does not matter.
3766 case kRef:
3767 // For non-nullable references, the result is always false.
3768 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Drop);
3769 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I32Const, result, 0);
3770 return 1;
3771 default:
3772 if constexpr (!ValidationTag::validate) UNREACHABLE();
3773 PopTypeError(0, value, "reference type");
3774 return 0;
3775 }
3776 }
3777
3778 DECODE(RefFunc) {
3779 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
3780 IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, "function index", validate);
3781 if (!this->ValidateFunction(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3782 Value* value =
3783 Push(ValueType::Ref(this->module_->functions[imm.index].sig_index));
3784 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefFunc, imm.index, value);
3785 return 1 + imm.length;
3786 }
3787
3788 DECODE(RefAsNonNull) {
3789 this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
3790 Value value = Pop();
3791 switch (value.type.kind()) {
3792 case kBottom:
3793 // We are in unreachable code. Forward the bottom value.
3794 case kRef:
3795 // A non-nullable value can remain as-is.
3796 Push(value);
3797 return 1;
3798 case kRefNull: {
3799 Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(value.type.heap_type()));
3800 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefAsNonNull, value, result);
3801 return 1;
3802 }
3803 default:
3804 if constexpr (!ValidationTag::validate) UNREACHABLE();
3805 PopTypeError(0, value, "reference type");
3806 return 0;
3807 }
3808 }
3809
3810 V8_INLINE DECODE(LocalGet) {
3811 IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, "local index", validate);
3812 if (!this->ValidateLocal(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3813 if (!VALIDATE(this->is_local_initialized(imm.index))) {
3814 this->DecodeError(this->pc_, "uninitialized non-defaultable local: %u",
3815 imm.index);
3816 return 0;
3817 }
3818 Value* value = Push(this->local_type(imm.index));
3819 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LocalGet, value, imm);
3820 return 1 + imm.length;
3821 }
3822
3823 DECODE(LocalSet) {
3824 IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, "local index", validate);
3825 if (!this->ValidateLocal(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3826 Value value = Pop(this->local_type(imm.index));
3827 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LocalSet, value, imm);
3828 this->set_local_initialized(imm.index);
3829 return 1 + imm.length;
3830 }
3831
3832 DECODE(LocalTee) {
3833 IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, "local index", validate);
3834 if (!this->ValidateLocal(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3835 ValueType local_type = this->local_type(imm.index);
3836 Value value = Pop(local_type);
3837 Value* result = Push(local_type);
3838 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LocalTee, value, result, imm);
3839 this->set_local_initialized(imm.index);
3840 return 1 + imm.length;
3841 }
3842
3843 DECODE(Drop) {
3844 Pop();
3845 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Drop);
3846 return 1;
3847 }
3848
3849 DECODE(GlobalGet) {
3850 GlobalIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3851 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3852 Value* result = Push(imm.global->type);
3853 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(GlobalGet, result, imm);
3854 return 1 + imm.length;
3855 }
3856
3857 DECODE(GlobalSet) {
3858 GlobalIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3859 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3860 if (!VALIDATE(imm.global->mutability)) {
3861 this->DecodeError("immutable global #%u cannot be assigned", imm.index);
3862 return 0;
3863 }
3864 Value value = Pop(imm.global->type);
3865 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(GlobalSet, value, imm);
3866 return 1 + imm.length;
3867 }
3868
3869 DECODE(TableGet) {
3870 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
3871 TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3872 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3873 Value index = Pop(TableAddressType(imm.table));
3874 Value* result = Push(imm.table->type);
3875 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableGet, index, result, imm);
3876 return 1 + imm.length;
3877 }
3878
3879 DECODE(TableSet) {
3880 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
3881 TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3882 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3883 ValueType table_address_type = TableAddressType(imm.table);
3884 auto [index, value] = Pop(table_address_type, imm.table->type);
3885 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableSet, index, value, imm);
3886 return 1 + imm.length;
3887 }
3888
3889 DECODE(LoadMem) { return DecodeLoadMem(GetLoadType(opcode)); }
3890
3891 DECODE(StoreMem) { return DecodeStoreMem(GetStoreType(opcode)); }
3892
3893 DECODE(MemoryGrow) {
3894 // This opcode will not be emitted by the asm translator.
3895 DCHECK_EQ(kWasmOrigin, this->module_->origin);
3896 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3897 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3898 ValueType mem_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
3899 Value value = Pop(mem_type);
3900 Value* result = Push(mem_type);
3901 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(MemoryGrow, imm, value, result);
3902 return 1 + imm.length;
3903 }
3904
3905 DECODE(MemorySize) {
3906 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3907 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3908 ValueType result_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
3909 Value* result = Push(result_type);
3910 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(CurrentMemoryPages, imm, result);
3911 return 1 + imm.length;
3912 }
3913
3914 DECODE(CallFunction) {
3915 CallFunctionImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3916 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3917 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.sig);
3918 Value* returns = PushReturns(imm.sig);
3919 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(CallDirect, imm, args.data(), returns);
3920 MarkMightThrow();
3921 return 1 + imm.length;
3922 }
3923
3924 DECODE(CallIndirect) {
3925 CallIndirectImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3926 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3927 Value index = Pop(TableAddressType(imm.table_imm.table));
3928 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.sig);
3929 Value* returns = PushReturns(imm.sig);
3930 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(CallIndirect, index, imm, args.data(),
3931 returns);
3932 MarkMightThrow();
3933 if (!this->module_->type(imm.sig_imm.index).is_final) {
3934 // In this case we emit an rtt.canon as part of the indirect call.
3935 this->detected_->add_gc();
3936 }
3937 return 1 + imm.length;
3938 }
3939
3940 DECODE(ReturnCall) {
3941 this->detected_->add_return_call();
3942 CallFunctionImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3943 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3944 if (!VALIDATE(this->CanReturnCall(imm.sig))) {
3945 this->DecodeError("%s: %s", WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(kExprReturnCall),
3946 "tail call type error");
3947 return 0;
3948 }
3949 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.sig);
3950 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ReturnCall, imm, args.data());
3951 EndControl();
3952 return 1 + imm.length;
3953 }
3954
3955 DECODE(ReturnCallIndirect) {
3956 this->detected_->add_return_call();
3957 CallIndirectImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3958 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3959 if (!VALIDATE(this->CanReturnCall(imm.sig))) {
3960 this->DecodeError("%s: %s",
3961 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(kExprReturnCallIndirect),
3962 "tail call return types mismatch");
3963 return 0;
3964 }
3965 Value index = Pop(TableAddressType(imm.table_imm.table));
3966 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.sig);
3967 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ReturnCallIndirect, index, imm,
3968 args.data());
3969 EndControl();
3970 if (!this->module_->type(imm.sig_imm.index).is_final) {
3971 // In this case we emit an rtt.canon as part of the indirect call.
3972 this->detected_->add_gc();
3973 }
3974 return 1 + imm.length;
3975 }
3976
3977 DECODE(CallRef) {
3978 this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
3979 SigIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3980 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3981 Value func_ref = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.index));
3982 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.sig);
3983 Value* returns = PushReturns(imm.sig);
3984 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(CallRef, func_ref, imm.sig, args.data(),
3985 returns);
3986 MarkMightThrow();
3987 return 1 + imm.length;
3988 }
3989
3990 DECODE(ReturnCallRef) {
3991 this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
3992 this->detected_->add_return_call();
3993 SigIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3994 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3995 if (!VALIDATE(this->CanReturnCall(imm.sig))) {
3996 this->DecodeError("%s: %s", WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(kExprReturnCallRef),
3997 "tail call return types mismatch");
3998 return 0;
3999 }
4000 Value func_ref = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.index));
4001 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.sig);
4002 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ReturnCallRef, func_ref, imm.sig,
4003 args.data());
4004 EndControl();
4005 return 1 + imm.length;
4006 }
4007
4008 DECODE(RefEq) {
4009 this->detected_->add_gc();
4010 Value lhs = Pop();
4011 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(lhs.type, kWasmEqRef, this->module_) ||
4012 IsSubtypeOf(lhs.type, ValueType::RefNull(HeapType::kEqShared),
4013 this->module_) ||
4014 control_.back().unreachable())) {
4015 this->DecodeError(this->pc_,
4016 "ref.eq[0] expected either eqref or (ref null shared "
4017 "eq), found %s of type %s",
4018 SafeOpcodeNameAt(lhs.pc()), lhs.type.name().c_str());
4019 }
4020 Value rhs = Pop();
4021 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(rhs.type, kWasmEqRef, this->module_) ||
4022 IsSubtypeOf(rhs.type, ValueType::RefNull(HeapType::kEqShared),
4023 this->module_) ||
4024 control_.back().unreachable())) {
4025 this->DecodeError(this->pc_,
4026 "ref.eq[0] expected either eqref or (ref null shared "
4027 "eq), found %s of type %s",
4028 SafeOpcodeNameAt(rhs.pc()), rhs.type.name().c_str());
4029 }
4030 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
4031 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(BinOp, kExprRefEq, lhs, rhs, result);
4032 return 1;
4033 }
4034
4035 DECODE(Numeric) {
4036 auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4037 this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_,
4038 "numeric index");
4039 if (full_opcode == kExprTableGrow || full_opcode == kExprTableSize ||
4040 full_opcode == kExprTableFill) {
4041 this->detected_->add_reftypes();
4042 }
4043 trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4044 return DecodeNumericOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4045 }
4046
4047 DECODE(Simd) {
4048 this->detected_->add_simd();
4049 if (!CheckHardwareSupportsSimd()) {
4050 if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
4051 FATAL("Aborting on missing Wasm SIMD support");
4052 }
4053 this->DecodeError("Wasm SIMD unsupported");
4054 return 0;
4055 }
4056 auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4057 this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_);
4058 if (!VALIDATE(this->ok())) return 0;
4059 trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4060 if (WasmOpcodes::IsFP16SimdOpcode(full_opcode)) {
4061 this->detected_->add_fp16();
4062 } else if (WasmOpcodes::IsRelaxedSimdOpcode(full_opcode)) {
4063 this->detected_->add_relaxed_simd();
4064 }
4065 return DecodeSimdOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4066 }
4067
4068 DECODE(Atomic) {
4069 this->detected_->add_threads();
4070 auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4071 this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_,
4072 "atomic index");
4073 trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4074 return DecodeAtomicOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4075 }
4076
4077 DECODE(GC) {
4078 auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4079 this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_,
4080 "gc index");
4081 trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4082 // If we are validating we could have read an illegal opcode. Handle that
4083 // separately.
4084 if (!VALIDATE(full_opcode != 0)) {
4085 DCHECK(this->failed());
4086 return 0;
4087 } else if (full_opcode >= kExprStringNewUtf8) {
4088 CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(stringref);
4089 return DecodeStringRefOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4090 } else {
4091 this->detected_->add_gc();
4092 return DecodeGCOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4093 }
4094 }
4095
4096#define SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_CASE(name, ...) \
4097 DECODE(name) { return BuildSimplePrototypeOperator(opcode); }
4098 FOREACH_SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_CASE)
4099#undef SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_CASE
4100
4101 DECODE(UnknownOrAsmJs) {
4102 // Deal with special asmjs opcodes.
4103 if (!VALIDATE(is_asmjs_module(this->module_))) {
4104 this->DecodeError("Invalid opcode 0x%x", opcode);
4105 return 0;
4106 }
4107 const FunctionSig* sig = WasmOpcodes::AsmjsSignature(opcode);
4108 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(sig);
4109 return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, sig);
4110 }
4111
4112#undef DECODE
4113
4114 static int NonConstError(WasmFullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode) {
4115 decoder->DecodeError("opcode %s is not allowed in constant expressions",
4116 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
4117 return 0;
4118 }
4119
4120 using OpcodeHandler = int (*)(WasmFullDecoder*, WasmOpcode);
4121
4122 // Ideally we would use template specialization for the different opcodes, but
4123 // GCC does not allow to specialize templates in class scope
4124 // (https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=85282), and specializing
4125 // outside the class is not allowed for non-specialized classes.
4126 // Hence just list all implementations explicitly here, which also gives more
4127 // freedom to use the same implementation for different opcodes.
4128#define DECODE_IMPL(opcode) DECODE_IMPL2(kExpr##opcode, opcode)
4129#define DECODE_IMPL2(opcode, name) \
4130 if (idx == opcode) { \
4131 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) { \
4132 return &WasmFullDecoder::NonConstError; \
4133 } else { \
4134 return &WasmFullDecoder::Decode##name; \
4135 } \
4136 }
4137#define DECODE_IMPL_CONST(opcode) DECODE_IMPL_CONST2(kExpr##opcode, opcode)
4138#define DECODE_IMPL_CONST2(opcode, name) \
4139 if (idx == opcode) return &WasmFullDecoder::Decode##name
4140
4141 static constexpr OpcodeHandler GetOpcodeHandlerTableEntry(size_t idx) {
4142 DECODE_IMPL(Nop);
4143#define BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE(op, ...) DECODE_IMPL(op);
4144 FOREACH_SIMPLE_NON_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE)
4145#undef BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE
4146#define BUILD_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE(op, ...) DECODE_IMPL_CONST(op);
4147 FOREACH_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE)
4148#undef BUILD_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE
4149 DECODE_IMPL(Block);
4150 DECODE_IMPL(Rethrow);
4151 DECODE_IMPL(Throw);
4152 DECODE_IMPL(Try);
4153 DECODE_IMPL(TryTable);
4154 DECODE_IMPL(ThrowRef);
4155 DECODE_IMPL(Catch);
4156 DECODE_IMPL(Delegate);
4157 DECODE_IMPL(CatchAll);
4158 DECODE_IMPL(BrOnNull);
4159 DECODE_IMPL(BrOnNonNull);
4160 DECODE_IMPL(Loop);
4161 DECODE_IMPL(If);
4162 DECODE_IMPL(Else);
4163 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(End);
4164 DECODE_IMPL(Select);
4165 DECODE_IMPL(SelectWithType);
4166 DECODE_IMPL(Br);
4167 DECODE_IMPL(BrIf);
4168 DECODE_IMPL(BrTable);
4169 DECODE_IMPL(Return);
4170 DECODE_IMPL(Unreachable);
4171 DECODE_IMPL(NopForTestingUnsupportedInLiftoff);
4172 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(I32Const);
4173 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(I64Const);
4174 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(F32Const);
4175 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(F64Const);
4176 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(RefNull);
4177 DECODE_IMPL(RefIsNull);
4178 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(RefFunc);
4179 DECODE_IMPL(RefAsNonNull);
4180 DECODE_IMPL(RefEq);
4181 DECODE_IMPL(LocalGet);
4182 DECODE_IMPL(LocalSet);
4183 DECODE_IMPL(LocalTee);
4184 DECODE_IMPL(Drop);
4185 DECODE_IMPL_CONST(GlobalGet);
4186 DECODE_IMPL(GlobalSet);
4187 DECODE_IMPL(TableGet);
4188 DECODE_IMPL(TableSet);
4189#define DECODE_LOAD_MEM(op, ...) DECODE_IMPL2(kExpr##op, LoadMem);
4190 FOREACH_LOAD_MEM_OPCODE(DECODE_LOAD_MEM)
4191#undef DECODE_LOAD_MEM
4192#define DECODE_STORE_MEM(op, ...) DECODE_IMPL2(kExpr##op, StoreMem);
4193 FOREACH_STORE_MEM_OPCODE(DECODE_STORE_MEM)
4194#undef DECODE_LOAD_MEM
4195 DECODE_IMPL(MemoryGrow);
4196 DECODE_IMPL(MemorySize);
4197 DECODE_IMPL(CallFunction);
4198 DECODE_IMPL(CallIndirect);
4199 DECODE_IMPL(ReturnCall);
4200 DECODE_IMPL(ReturnCallIndirect);
4201 DECODE_IMPL(CallRef);
4202 DECODE_IMPL(ReturnCallRef);
4203 DECODE_IMPL2(kNumericPrefix, Numeric);
4204 DECODE_IMPL_CONST2(kSimdPrefix, Simd);
4205 DECODE_IMPL2(kAtomicPrefix, Atomic);
4206 DECODE_IMPL_CONST2(kGCPrefix, GC);
4207#define SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_CASE(name, ...) DECODE_IMPL(name);
4208 FOREACH_SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_CASE)
4209#undef SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_CASE
4210 return &WasmFullDecoder::DecodeUnknownOrAsmJs;
4211 }
4212
4213#undef DECODE_IMPL
4214#undef DECODE_IMPL2
4215
4216 OpcodeHandler GetOpcodeHandler(uint8_t opcode) {
4217 static constexpr std::array<OpcodeHandler, 256> kOpcodeHandlers =
4218 base::make_array<256>(GetOpcodeHandlerTableEntry);
4219 return kOpcodeHandlers[opcode];
4220 }
4221
4222 void EndControl() {
4223 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
4224 Control* current = &control_.back();
4225 stack_.shrink_to(current->stack_depth);
4226 current->reachability = kUnreachable;
4227 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = false;
4228 }
4229
4230 template <typename func>
4231 V8_INLINE void InitMerge(Merge<Value>* merge, uint32_t arity, func get_val) {
4232 merge->arity = arity;
4233 if constexpr (std::is_null_pointer_v<func>) {
4234 DCHECK_EQ(0, arity);
4235 } else if (arity == 1) {
4236 merge->vals.first = get_val(0);
4237 } else if (arity > 1) {
4238 merge->vals.array = this->zone()->template AllocateArray<Value>(arity);
4239 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < arity; i++) {
4240 merge->vals.array[i] = get_val(i);
4241 }
4242 }
4243 }
4244
4245 // In reachable code, check if there are at least {count} values on the stack.
4246 // In unreachable code, if there are less than {count} values on the stack,
4247 // insert a number of unreachable values underneath the current values equal
4248 // to the difference, and return that number.
4249 V8_INLINE int EnsureStackArguments(int count) {
4250 uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
4251 if (V8_LIKELY(stack_.size() >= count + limit)) return 0;
4252 return EnsureStackArguments_Slow(count);
4253 }
4254
4255 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST int EnsureStackArguments_Slow(int count) {
4256 uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
4257 if (!VALIDATE(control_.back().unreachable())) {
4258 NotEnoughArgumentsError(count, stack_.size() - limit);
4259 }
4260 // Silently create unreachable values out of thin air underneath the
4261 // existing stack values. To do so, we have to move existing stack values
4262 // upwards in the stack, then instantiate the new Values as
4263 // {UnreachableValue}.
4264 int current_values = stack_.size() - limit;
4265 int additional_values = count - current_values;
4266 DCHECK_GT(additional_values, 0);
4267 // Ensure that after this operation there is still room for one more value.
4268 // Callers might not expect this operation to push values on the stack
4269 // (because it only does so in exceptional cases).
4270 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(additional_values + 1, this->zone_);
4271 Value unreachable_value = UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
4272 for (int i = 0; i < additional_values; ++i) stack_.push(unreachable_value);
4273 if (current_values > 0) {
4274 // Move the current values up to the end of the stack, and create
4275 // unreachable values below.
4276 Value* stack_base = stack_value(current_values + additional_values);
4277 for (int i = current_values - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4278 stack_base[additional_values + i] = stack_base[i];
4279 }
4280 for (int i = 0; i < additional_values; i++) {
4281 stack_base[i] = UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
4282 }
4283 }
4284 return additional_values;
4285 }
4286
4287 V8_INLINE void ValidateParameters(const FunctionSig* sig) {
4288 int num_params = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
4289 EnsureStackArguments(num_params);
4290 Value* param_base = stack_.end() - num_params;
4291 for (int i = 0; i < num_params; i++) {
4292 ValidateStackValue(i, param_base[i], sig->GetParam(i));
4293 }
4294 }
4295
4296 // Drops a number of stack elements equal to the {sig}'s parameter count (0 if
4297 // {sig} is null), or all of them if less are present.
4298 V8_INLINE void DropArgs(const FunctionSig* sig) {
4299 int count = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
4300 Drop(count);
4301 }
4302
4303 V8_INLINE PoppedArgVector PopArgs(const StructType* type) {
4304 int count = static_cast<int>(type->field_count());
4305 EnsureStackArguments(count);
4306 DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, stack_size());
4307 DCHECK_GE(stack_size() - control_.back().stack_depth, count);
4308 Value* args_base = stack_.end() - count;
4309 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
4310 ValidateStackValue(i, args_base[i], type->field(i).Unpacked());
4311 }
4312 // Note: Popping from the {FastZoneVector} does not invalidate the old (now
4313 // out-of-range) elements.
4314 stack_.pop(count);
4315 return PoppedArgVector{base::VectorOf(args_base, count)};
4316 }
4317 // Drops a number of stack elements equal to the struct's field count, or all
4318 // of them if less are present.
4319 V8_INLINE void DropArgs(const StructType* type) {
4320 Drop(static_cast<int>(type->field_count()));
4321 }
4322
4323 // Pops arguments as required by signature, returning them by copy as a
4324 // vector.
4325 V8_INLINE PoppedArgVector PopArgs(const FunctionSig* sig) {
4326 int count = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
4327 EnsureStackArguments(count);
4328 DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, stack_size());
4329 DCHECK_GE(stack_size() - control_.back().stack_depth, count);
4330 Value* args_base = stack_.end() - count;
4331 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
4332 ValidateStackValue(i, args_base[i], sig->GetParam(i));
4333 }
4334 // Note: Popping from the {FastZoneVector} does not invalidate the old (now
4335 // out-of-range) elements.
4336 stack_.pop(count);
4337 return PoppedArgVector{base::VectorOf(args_base, count)};
4338 }
4339
4340 Control* PushControl(ControlKind kind, const BlockTypeImmediate& imm) {
4341 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
4342 ValidateParameters(&imm.sig);
4343 uint32_t consumed_values = static_cast<uint32_t>(imm.sig.parameter_count());
4344 uint32_t stack_depth = stack_.size();
4345 DCHECK_LE(consumed_values, stack_depth);
4346 uint32_t inner_stack_depth = stack_depth - consumed_values;
4347 DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, inner_stack_depth);
4348
4349 uint32_t init_stack_depth = this->locals_initialization_stack_depth();
4350 Reachability reachability = control_.back().innerReachability();
4351 control_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
4352 control_.emplace_back(this->zone_, kind, inner_stack_depth,
4353 init_stack_depth, this->pc_, reachability);
4354 Control* new_block = &control_.back();
4355
4356 Value* arg_base = stack_.end() - consumed_values;
4357 // Update the type of input nodes to the more general types expected by the
4358 // block. In particular, in unreachable code, the input would have bottom
4359 // type otherwise.
4360 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < consumed_values; ++i) {
4361 DCHECK_IMPLIES(this->ok(), IsSubtypeOf(arg_base[i].type, imm.in_type(i),
4362 this->module_) ||
4363 arg_base[i].type == kWasmBottom);
4364 arg_base[i].type = imm.in_type(i);
4365 }
4366
4367 // Initialize start- and end-merges of {c} with values according to the
4368 // in- and out-types of {c} respectively.
4369 const uint8_t* pc = this->pc_;
4370 InitMerge(&new_block->end_merge, imm.out_arity(), [pc, &imm](uint32_t i) {
4371 return Value{pc, imm.out_type(i)};
4372 });
4373 InitMerge(&new_block->start_merge, imm.in_arity(),
4374 [arg_base](uint32_t i) { return arg_base[i]; });
4375 return new_block;
4376 }
4377
4378 void PopControl() {
4379 // This cannot be the outermost control block.
4380 DCHECK_LT(1, control_.size());
4381 Control* c = &control_.back();
4382 DCHECK_LE(c->stack_depth, stack_.size());
4383
4384 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(PopControl, c);
4385
4386 // - In non-unreachable code, a loop just leaves the values on the stack.
4387 // - In unreachable code, it is not guaranteed that we have Values of the
4388 // correct types on the stack, so we have to make sure we do. Their values
4389 // do not matter, so we might as well push the (uninitialized) values of
4390 // the loop's end merge.
4391 if (!c->is_loop() || c->unreachable()) {
4392 PushMergeValues(c, &c->end_merge);
4393 }
4394 RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
4395
4396 bool parent_reached =
4397 c->reachable() || c->end_merge.reached || c->is_onearmed_if();
4398 control_.pop();
4399 // If the parent block was reachable before, but the popped control does not
4400 // return to here, this block becomes "spec only reachable".
4401 if (!parent_reached) SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
4402 current_code_reachable_and_ok_ =
4403 VALIDATE(this->ok()) && control_.back().reachable();
4404 }
4405
4406 int DecodeLoadMem(LoadType type, int prefix_len = 1) {
4407 MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
4408 MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(prefix_len, type.size_log_2());
4409 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + prefix_len, imm)) return 0;
4410 ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
4411 Value index = Pop(address_type);
4412 Value* result = Push(type.value_type());
4413 if (V8_LIKELY(
4414 !CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset))) {
4415 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LoadMem, type, imm, index, result);
4416 }
4417 return prefix_len + imm.length;
4418 }
4419
4420 int DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType type, LoadTransformationKind transform,
4421 uint32_t opcode_length) {
4422 // Load extends always load 64-bits.
4423 uint32_t max_alignment =
4424 transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend ? 3 : type.size_log_2();
4425 MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
4426 MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, max_alignment);
4427 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
4428 ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
4429 Value index = Pop(address_type);
4430 Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
4431 uintptr_t op_size =
4432 transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend ? 8 : type.size();
4433 if (V8_LIKELY(
4434 !CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, op_size, imm.offset))) {
4435 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LoadTransform, type, transform, imm,
4436 index, result);
4437 }
4438 return opcode_length + imm.length;
4439 }
4440
4441 int DecodeLoadLane(WasmOpcode opcode, LoadType type, uint32_t opcode_length) {
4442 MemoryAccessImmediate mem_imm =
4443 MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, type.size_log_2());
4444 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, mem_imm)) return 0;
4445 SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + mem_imm.length,
4446 validate);
4447 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, lane_imm)) return 0;
4448 ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(mem_imm.memory);
4449 auto [index, v128] = Pop(address_type, kWasmS128);
4450
4451 Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
4452 if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(mem_imm.memory, type.size(),
4453 mem_imm.offset))) {
4454 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LoadLane, type, v128, index, mem_imm,
4455 lane_imm.lane, result);
4456 }
4457 return opcode_length + mem_imm.length + lane_imm.length;
4458 }
4459
4460 int DecodeStoreLane(WasmOpcode opcode, StoreType type,
4461 uint32_t opcode_length) {
4462 MemoryAccessImmediate mem_imm =
4463 MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, type.size_log_2());
4464 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, mem_imm)) return 0;
4465 SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + mem_imm.length,
4466 validate);
4467 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, lane_imm)) return 0;
4468 ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(mem_imm.memory);
4469 auto [index, v128] = Pop(address_type, kWasmS128);
4470
4471 if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(mem_imm.memory, type.size(),
4472 mem_imm.offset))) {
4473 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StoreLane, type, mem_imm, index, v128,
4474 lane_imm.lane);
4475 }
4476 return opcode_length + mem_imm.length + lane_imm.length;
4477 }
4478
4479 bool CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(const WasmMemory* memory, uint64_t size,
4480 uint64_t offset) {
4481 const bool statically_oob =
4482 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(offset, size, memory->max_memory_size);
4483 if (V8_UNLIKELY(statically_oob)) {
4484 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Trap, TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
4485 SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
4486 }
4487 return statically_oob;
4488 }
4489
4490 int DecodeStoreMem(StoreType store, int prefix_len = 1) {
4491 MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
4492 MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(prefix_len, store.size_log_2());
4493 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + prefix_len, imm)) return 0;
4494 ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
4495 auto [index, value] = Pop(address_type, store.value_type());
4496 if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, store.size(),
4497 imm.offset))) {
4498 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StoreMem, store, imm, index, value);
4499 }
4500 return prefix_len + imm.length;
4501 }
4502
4503 uint32_t SimdConstOp(uint32_t opcode_length) {
4504 Simd128Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4505 Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
4506 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(S128Const, imm, result);
4507 return opcode_length + kSimd128Size;
4508 }
4509
4510 uint32_t SimdExtractLane(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType type,
4511 uint32_t opcode_length) {
4512 SimdLaneImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4513 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, imm)) return 0;
4514 Value input = Pop(kWasmS128);
4515 Value* result = Push(type);
4516 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(SimdLaneOp, opcode, imm,
4517 base::VectorOf({input}), result);
4518 return opcode_length + imm.length;
4519 }
4520
4521 uint32_t SimdReplaceLane(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType type,
4522 uint32_t opcode_length) {
4523 SimdLaneImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4524 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, imm)) return 0;
4525 auto [v128, lane_val] = Pop(kWasmS128, type);
4526 Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
4527 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(
4528 SimdLaneOp, opcode, imm, base::VectorOf({v128, lane_val}), result);
4529 return opcode_length + imm.length;
4530 }
4531
4532 uint32_t Simd8x16ShuffleOp(uint32_t opcode_length) {
4533 Simd128Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4534 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
4535 auto [input0, input1] = Pop(kWasmS128, kWasmS128);
4536 Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
4537 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Simd8x16ShuffleOp, imm, input0, input1,
4538 result);
4539 return opcode_length + 16;
4540 }
4541
4542 uint32_t DecodeSimdOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
4543 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) {
4544 // Currently, only s128.const is allowed in constant expressions.
4545 if (opcode != kExprS128Const) {
4546 this->DecodeError("opcode %s is not allowed in constant expressions",
4547 this->SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc()));
4548 return 0;
4549 }
4550 return SimdConstOp(opcode_length);
4551 }
4552 // opcode_length is the number of bytes that this SIMD-specific opcode takes
4553 // up in the LEB128 encoded form.
4554 switch (opcode) {
4555 case kExprF64x2ExtractLane:
4556 return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmF64, opcode_length);
4557 case kExprF16x8ExtractLane: {
4558 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_fp16) {
4559 this->DecodeError(
4560 "invalid simd opcode: 0x%x, "
4561 "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
4562 opcode);
4563 return 0;
4564 }
4565 [[fallthrough]];
4566 }
4567 case kExprF32x4ExtractLane:
4568 return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmF32, opcode_length);
4569 case kExprI64x2ExtractLane:
4570 return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmI64, opcode_length);
4571 case kExprI32x4ExtractLane:
4572 case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneS:
4573 case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneU:
4574 case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneS:
4575 case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneU:
4576 return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmI32, opcode_length);
4577 case kExprF64x2ReplaceLane:
4578 return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmF64, opcode_length);
4579 case kExprF16x8ReplaceLane: {
4580 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_fp16) {
4581 this->DecodeError(
4582 "invalid simd opcode: 0x%x, "
4583 "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
4584 opcode);
4585 return 0;
4586 }
4587 [[fallthrough]];
4588 }
4589 case kExprF32x4ReplaceLane:
4590 return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmF32, opcode_length);
4591 case kExprI64x2ReplaceLane:
4592 return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmI64, opcode_length);
4593 case kExprI32x4ReplaceLane:
4594 case kExprI16x8ReplaceLane:
4595 case kExprI8x16ReplaceLane:
4596 return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmI32, opcode_length);
4597 case kExprI8x16Shuffle:
4598 return Simd8x16ShuffleOp(opcode_length);
4599 case kExprS128LoadMem:
4600 return DecodeLoadMem(LoadType::kS128Load, opcode_length);
4601 case kExprS128StoreMem:
4602 return DecodeStoreMem(StoreType::kS128Store, opcode_length);
4603 case kExprS128Load32Zero:
4604 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load,
4605 LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend,
4606 opcode_length);
4607 case kExprS128Load64Zero:
4608 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI64Load,
4609 LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend,
4610 opcode_length);
4611 case kExprS128Load8Splat:
4612 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load8S,
4613 LoadTransformationKind::kSplat,
4614 opcode_length);
4615 case kExprS128Load16Splat:
4616 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load16S,
4617 LoadTransformationKind::kSplat,
4618 opcode_length);
4619 case kExprS128Load32Splat:
4620 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(
4621 LoadType::kI32Load, LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, opcode_length);
4622 case kExprS128Load64Splat:
4623 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(
4624 LoadType::kI64Load, LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, opcode_length);
4625 case kExprS128Load8x8S:
4626 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load8S,
4627 LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
4628 opcode_length);
4629 case kExprS128Load8x8U:
4630 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load8U,
4631 LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
4632 opcode_length);
4633 case kExprS128Load16x4S:
4634 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load16S,
4635 LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
4636 opcode_length);
4637 case kExprS128Load16x4U:
4638 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load16U,
4639 LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
4640 opcode_length);
4641 case kExprS128Load32x2S:
4642 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI64Load32S,
4643 LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
4644 opcode_length);
4645 case kExprS128Load32x2U:
4646 return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI64Load32U,
4647 LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
4648 opcode_length);
4649 case kExprS128Load8Lane: {
4650 return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI32Load8S, opcode_length);
4651 }
4652 case kExprS128Load16Lane: {
4653 return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI32Load16S, opcode_length);
4654 }
4655 case kExprS128Load32Lane: {
4656 return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI32Load, opcode_length);
4657 }
4658 case kExprS128Load64Lane: {
4659 return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI64Load, opcode_length);
4660 }
4661 case kExprS128Store8Lane: {
4662 return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI32Store8, opcode_length);
4663 }
4664 case kExprS128Store16Lane: {
4665 return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI32Store16, opcode_length);
4666 }
4667 case kExprS128Store32Lane: {
4668 return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI32Store, opcode_length);
4669 }
4670 case kExprS128Store64Lane: {
4671 return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI64Store, opcode_length);
4672 }
4673 case kExprS128Const:
4674 return SimdConstOp(opcode_length);
4675 case kExprF16x8Splat:
4676 case kExprF16x8Abs:
4677 case kExprF16x8Neg:
4678 case kExprF16x8Sqrt:
4679 case kExprF16x8Ceil:
4680 case kExprF16x8Floor:
4681 case kExprF16x8Trunc:
4682 case kExprF16x8NearestInt:
4683 case kExprF16x8Eq:
4684 case kExprF16x8Ne:
4685 case kExprF16x8Lt:
4686 case kExprF16x8Gt:
4687 case kExprF16x8Le:
4688 case kExprF16x8Ge:
4689 case kExprF16x8Add:
4690 case kExprF16x8Sub:
4691 case kExprF16x8Mul:
4692 case kExprF16x8Div:
4693 case kExprF16x8Min:
4694 case kExprF16x8Max:
4695 case kExprF16x8Pmin:
4696 case kExprF16x8Pmax:
4697 case kExprI16x8SConvertF16x8:
4698 case kExprI16x8UConvertF16x8:
4699 case kExprF16x8SConvertI16x8:
4700 case kExprF16x8UConvertI16x8:
4701 case kExprF16x8DemoteF32x4Zero:
4702 case kExprF16x8DemoteF64x2Zero:
4703 case kExprF32x4PromoteLowF16x8:
4704 case kExprF16x8Qfma:
4705 case kExprF16x8Qfms: {
4706 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_fp16) {
4707 this->DecodeError(
4708 "invalid simd opcode: 0x%x, "
4709 "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
4710 opcode);
4711 return 0;
4712 }
4713 [[fallthrough]];
4714 }
4715 default: {
4716 const FunctionSig* sig = WasmOpcodes::Signature(opcode);
4717 if (!VALIDATE(sig != nullptr)) {
4718 this->DecodeError("invalid simd opcode");
4719 return 0;
4720 }
4721 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(sig);
4722 Value* results = sig->return_count() == 0 ? nullptr : PushReturns(sig);
4723 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(SimdOp, opcode, args.data(),
4724 results);
4725 return opcode_length;
4726 }
4727 }
4728 }
4729
4730 // Returns true if type checking will always fail, either because the types
4731 // are unrelated or because the target_type is one of the null sentinels and
4732 // conversion to null does not succeed.
4733 bool TypeCheckAlwaysFails(Value obj, HeapType expected_type,
4734 bool null_succeeds) {
4735 bool types_unrelated =
4736 !IsSubtypeOf(ValueType::Ref(expected_type), obj.type, this->module_) &&
4737 !IsSubtypeOf(obj.type, ValueType::RefNull(expected_type),
4738 this->module_);
4739 // For "unrelated" types the check can still succeed for the null value on
4740 // instructions treating null as a successful check.
4741 // TODO(12868): For string views, this implementation anticipates that
4742 // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40 will be resolved
4743 // by making the views standalone types.
4744 return (types_unrelated &&
4745 (!null_succeeds || !obj.type.is_nullable() ||
4746 obj.type.is_string_view() || expected_type.is_string_view())) ||
4747 ((!null_succeeds || !obj.type.is_nullable()) &&
4748 (expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNone ||
4749 expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoFunc ||
4750 expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExtern ||
4751 expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExn));
4752 }
4753
4754 // Checks if {obj} is a subtype of type, thus checking will always
4755 // succeed.
4756 bool TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(Value obj, HeapType type) {
4757 return IsSubtypeOf(obj.type, ValueType::RefNull(type), this->module_);
4758 }
4759
4760#define NON_CONST_ONLY \
4761 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) { \
4762 this->DecodeError("opcode %s is not allowed in constant expressions", \
4763 this->SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc())); \
4764 return 0; \
4765 }
4766
4767 int DecodeGCOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
4768 // Bigger GC opcodes are handled via {DecodeStringRefOpcode}, so we can
4769 // assume here that opcodes are within [0xfb00, 0xfbff].
4770 // This assumption might help the big switch below.
4771 V8_ASSUME(opcode >> 8 == kGCPrefix);
4772 switch (opcode) {
4773 case kExprStructNew: {
4774 StructIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4775 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
4776 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.struct_type);
4777 Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(imm.index));
4778 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructNew, imm, args.data(), value);
4779 return opcode_length + imm.length;
4780 }
4781 case kExprStructNewDefault: {
4782 StructIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4783 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
4784 if (ValidationTag::validate) {
4785 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < imm.struct_type->field_count(); i++) {
4786 ValueType ftype = imm.struct_type->field(i);
4787 if (!VALIDATE(ftype.is_defaultable())) {
4788 this->DecodeError(
4789 "%s: struct type %d has field %d of non-defaultable type %s",
4790 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index, i,
4791 ftype.name().c_str());
4792 return 0;
4793 }
4794 }
4795 }
4796 Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(imm.index));
4797 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructNewDefault, imm, value);
4798 return opcode_length + imm.length;
4799 }
4800 case kExprStructGet: {
4801 NON_CONST_ONLY
4802 FieldImmediate field(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4803 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, field)) return 0;
4804 ValueType field_type =
4805 field.struct_imm.struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
4806 if (!VALIDATE(!field_type.is_packed())) {
4807 this->DecodeError(
4808 "struct.get: Immediate field %d of type %d has packed type %s. "
4809 "Use struct.get_s or struct.get_u instead.",
4810 field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index,
4811 field_type.name().c_str());
4812 return 0;
4813 }
4814 Value struct_obj = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.index));
4815 Value* value = Push(field_type);
4816 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructGet, struct_obj, field, true,
4817 value);
4818 return opcode_length + field.length;
4819 }
4820 case kExprStructGetU:
4821 case kExprStructGetS: {
4822 NON_CONST_ONLY
4823 FieldImmediate field(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4824 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, field)) return 0;
4825 ValueType field_type =
4826 field.struct_imm.struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
4827 if (!VALIDATE(field_type.is_packed())) {
4828 this->DecodeError(
4829 "%s: Immediate field %d of type %d has non-packed type %s. Use "
4830 "struct.get instead.",
4831 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), field.field_imm.index,
4832 field.struct_imm.index, field_type.name().c_str());
4833 return 0;
4834 }
4835 Value struct_obj = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.index));
4836 Value* value = Push(field_type.Unpacked());
4837 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructGet, struct_obj, field,
4838 opcode == kExprStructGetS, value);
4839 return opcode_length + field.length;
4840 }
4841 case kExprStructSet: {
4842 NON_CONST_ONLY
4843 FieldImmediate field(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4844 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, field)) return 0;
4845 const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
4846 if (!VALIDATE(struct_type->mutability(field.field_imm.index))) {
4847 this->DecodeError("struct.set: Field %d of type %d is immutable.",
4848 field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index);
4849 return 0;
4850 }
4851 auto [struct_obj, field_value] =
4852 Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.index),
4853 struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).Unpacked());
4854 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructSet, struct_obj, field,
4855 field_value);
4856 return opcode_length + field.length;
4857 }
4858 case kExprArrayNew: {
4859 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4860 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
4861 auto [initial_value, length] =
4862 Pop(imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked(), kWasmI32);
4863 Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(imm.index));
4864 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNew, imm, length, initial_value,
4865 value);
4866 return opcode_length + imm.length;
4867 }
4868 case kExprArrayNewDefault: {
4869 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
4870 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
4871 if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->element_type().is_defaultable())) {
4872 this->DecodeError(
4873 "%s: array type %d has non-defaultable element type %s",
4874 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index,
4875 imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
4876 return 0;
4877 }
4878 Value length = Pop(kWasmI32);
4879 Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(imm.index));
4880 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewDefault, imm, length, value);
4881 return opcode_length + imm.length;
4882 }
4883 case kExprArrayNewData: {
4884 // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
4885 NON_CONST_ONLY
4886 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
4887 validate);
4888 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
4889 ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
4890 if (element_type.is_reference()) {
4891 this->DecodeError(
4892 "array.new_data can only be used with numeric-type arrays, found "
4893 "array type #%d instead",
4894 array_imm.index);
4895 return 0;
4896 }
4897 const uint8_t* data_index_pc =
4898 this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length;
4899 IndexImmediate data_segment(this, data_index_pc, "data segment",
4900 validate);
4901 if (!this->ValidateDataSegment(data_index_pc, data_segment)) return 0;
4902
4903 auto [offset, length] = Pop(kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
4904
4905 Value* array = Push(ValueType::Ref(array_imm.index));
4906 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewSegment, array_imm,
4907 data_segment, offset, length, array);
4908 return opcode_length + array_imm.length + data_segment.length;
4909 }
4910 case kExprArrayNewElem: {
4911 // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
4912 NON_CONST_ONLY
4913 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
4914 validate);
4915 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
4916 ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
4917 if (element_type.is_numeric()) {
4918 this->DecodeError(
4919 "array.new_elem can only be used with reference-type arrays, "
4920 "found array type #%d instead",
4921 array_imm.index);
4922 return 0;
4923 }
4924 const uint8_t* elem_index_pc =
4925 this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length;
4926 IndexImmediate elem_segment(this, elem_index_pc, "element segment",
4927 validate);
4928 if (!this->ValidateElementSegment(elem_index_pc, elem_segment)) {
4929 return 0;
4930 }
4931
4932 ValueType elem_segment_type =
4933 this->module_->elem_segments[elem_segment.index].type;
4934 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
4935 !IsSubtypeOf(elem_segment_type, element_type, this->module_))) {
4936 this->DecodeError(
4937 "array.new_elem: segment type %s is not a subtype of array "
4938 "element type %s",
4939 elem_segment_type.name().c_str(), element_type.name().c_str());
4940 return 0;
4941 }
4942
4943 auto [offset, length] = Pop(kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
4944 Value* array = Push(ValueType::Ref(array_imm.index));
4945 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewSegment, array_imm,
4946 elem_segment, offset, length, array);
4947 return opcode_length + array_imm.length + elem_segment.length;
4948 }
4949 case kExprArrayInitData: {
4950 NON_CONST_ONLY
4951 // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
4952 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
4953 validate);
4954 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
4955 if (!array_imm.array_type->mutability()) {
4956 this->DecodeError(
4957 "array.init_data can only be used with mutable arrays, found "
4958 "array type #%d instead",
4959 array_imm.index);
4960 return 0;
4961 }
4962 ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
4963 if (element_type.is_reference()) {
4964 this->DecodeError(
4965 "array.init_data can only be used with numeric-type arrays, "
4966 "found array type #%d instead",
4967 array_imm.index);
4968 return 0;
4969 }
4970 const uint8_t* data_index_pc =
4971 this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length;
4972 IndexImmediate data_segment(this, data_index_pc, "data segment",
4973 validate);
4974 if (!this->ValidateDataSegment(data_index_pc, data_segment)) return 0;
4975
4976 auto [array, array_index, data_offset, length] = Pop(
4977 ValueType::RefNull(array_imm.index), kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
4978 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayInitSegment, array_imm,
4979 data_segment, array, array_index,
4980 data_offset, length);
4981 return opcode_length + array_imm.length + data_segment.length;
4982 }
4983 case kExprArrayInitElem: {
4984 NON_CONST_ONLY
4985 // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
4986 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
4987 validate);
4988 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
4989 if (!array_imm.array_type->mutability()) {
4990 this->DecodeError(
4991 "array.init_elem can only be used with mutable arrays, found "
4992 "array type #%d instead",
4993 array_imm.index);
4994 return 0;
4995 }
4996 ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
4997 if (element_type.is_numeric()) {
4998 this->DecodeError(
4999 "array.init_elem can only be used with reference-type arrays, "
5000 "found array type #%d instead",
5001 array_imm.index);
5002 return 0;
5003 }
5004 const uint8_t* elem_index_pc =
5005 this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length;
5006 IndexImmediate elem_segment(this, elem_index_pc, "element segment",
5007 validate);
5008 if (!this->ValidateElementSegment(elem_index_pc, elem_segment)) {
5009 return 0;
5010 }
5011 ValueType segment_type =
5012 this->module_->elem_segments[elem_segment.index].type;
5013 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(segment_type, element_type, this->module_))) {
5014 this->DecodeError(
5015 "array.init_elem: segment type %s is not a subtype of array "
5016 "element type %s",
5017 segment_type.name().c_str(), element_type.name().c_str());
5018 return 0;
5019 }
5020
5021 auto [array, array_index, elem_offset, length] = Pop(
5022 ValueType::RefNull(array_imm.index), kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5023 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayInitSegment, array_imm,
5024 elem_segment, array, array_index,
5025 elem_offset, length);
5026 return opcode_length + array_imm.length + elem_segment.length;
5027 }
5028 case kExprArrayGetS:
5029 case kExprArrayGetU: {
5030 NON_CONST_ONLY
5031 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5032 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5033 if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->element_type().is_packed())) {
5034 this->DecodeError(
5035 "%s: Immediate array type %d has non-packed type %s. Use "
5036 "array.get instead.",
5037 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index,
5038 imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
5039 return 0;
5040 }
5041 auto [array_obj, index] = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.index), kWasmI32);
5042 Value* value = Push(imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked());
5043 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayGet, array_obj, imm, index,
5044 opcode == kExprArrayGetS, value);
5045 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5046 }
5047 case kExprArrayGet: {
5048 NON_CONST_ONLY
5049 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5050 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5051 if (!VALIDATE(!imm.array_type->element_type().is_packed())) {
5052 this->DecodeError(
5053 "array.get: Immediate array type %d has packed type %s. Use "
5054 "array.get_s or array.get_u instead.",
5055 imm.index, imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
5056 return 0;
5057 }
5058 auto [array_obj, index] = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.index), kWasmI32);
5059 Value* value = Push(imm.array_type->element_type());
5060 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayGet, array_obj, imm, index,
5061 true, value);
5062 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5063 }
5064 case kExprArraySet: {
5065 NON_CONST_ONLY
5066 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5067 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5068 if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->mutability())) {
5069 this->DecodeError("array.set: immediate array type %d is immutable",
5070 imm.index);
5071 return 0;
5072 }
5073 auto [array_obj, index, value] =
5074 Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.index), kWasmI32,
5075 imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked());
5076 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArraySet, array_obj, imm, index,
5077 value);
5078 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5079 }
5080 case kExprArrayLen: {
5081 NON_CONST_ONLY
5082 Value array_obj = Pop(kWasmArrayRef);
5083 Value* value = Push(kWasmI32);
5084 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayLen, array_obj, value);
5085 return opcode_length;
5086 }
5087 case kExprArrayCopy: {
5088 NON_CONST_ONLY
5089 ArrayIndexImmediate dst_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5090 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, dst_imm)) return 0;
5091 if (!VALIDATE(dst_imm.array_type->mutability())) {
5092 this->DecodeError(
5093 "array.copy: immediate destination array type #%d is immutable",
5094 dst_imm.index);
5095 return 0;
5096 }
5097 ArrayIndexImmediate src_imm(
5098 this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + dst_imm.length, validate);
5099 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + dst_imm.length,
5100 src_imm)) {
5101 return 0;
5102 }
5103 if (!IsSubtypeOf(src_imm.array_type->element_type(),
5104 dst_imm.array_type->element_type(), this->module_)) {
5105 this->DecodeError(
5106 "array.copy: source array's #%d element type is not a subtype of "
5107 "destination array's #%d element type",
5108 src_imm.index, dst_imm.index);
5109 return 0;
5110 }
5111 auto [dst, dst_index, src, src_index, length] =
5112 Pop(ValueType::RefNull(dst_imm.index), kWasmI32,
5113 ValueType::RefNull(src_imm.index), kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5114 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayCopy, dst, dst_index, src,
5115 src_index, src_imm, length);
5116 return opcode_length + dst_imm.length + src_imm.length;
5117 }
5118 case kExprArrayFill: {
5119 NON_CONST_ONLY
5120 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5121 validate);
5122 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5123 if (!VALIDATE(array_imm.array_type->mutability())) {
5124 this->DecodeError("array.init: immediate array type #%d is immutable",
5125 array_imm.index);
5126 return 0;
5127 }
5128
5129 auto [array, offset, value, length] =
5130 Pop(ValueType::RefNull(array_imm.index), kWasmI32,
5131 array_imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked(), kWasmI32);
5132 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayFill, array_imm, array, offset,
5133 value, length);
5134 return opcode_length + array_imm.length;
5135 }
5136 case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
5137 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5138 validate);
5139 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5140 IndexImmediate length_imm(this,
5141 this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length,
5142 "array.new_fixed length", validate);
5143 uint32_t elem_count = length_imm.index;
5144 if (!VALIDATE(elem_count <= kV8MaxWasmArrayNewFixedLength)) {
5145 this->DecodeError(
5146 "Requested length %u for array.new_fixed too large, maximum is "
5147 "%zu",
5148 length_imm.index, kV8MaxWasmArrayNewFixedLength);
5149 return 0;
5150 }
5151 ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
5152 std::vector<ValueType> element_types(elem_count,
5153 element_type.Unpacked());
5154 FunctionSig element_sig(0, elem_count, element_types.data());
5155 PoppedArgVector elements = PopArgs(&element_sig);
5156 Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(array_imm.index));
5157 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewFixed, array_imm, length_imm,
5158 elements.data(), result);
5159 return opcode_length + array_imm.length + length_imm.length;
5160 }
5161 case kExprRefI31: {
5162 Value input = Pop(kWasmI32);
5163 Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(HeapType::kI31));
5164 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefI31, input, value);
5165 return opcode_length;
5166 }
5167 case kExprI31GetS: {
5168 NON_CONST_ONLY
5169 Value i31 = Pop(kWasmI31Ref);
5170 Value* value = Push(kWasmI32);
5171 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I31GetS, i31, value);
5172 return opcode_length;
5173 }
5174 case kExprI31GetU: {
5175 NON_CONST_ONLY
5176 Value i31 = Pop(kWasmI31Ref);
5177 Value* value = Push(kWasmI32);
5178 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I31GetU, i31, value);
5179 return opcode_length;
5180 }
5181 case kExprRefCast:
5182 case kExprRefCastNull: {
5183 NON_CONST_ONLY
5184 HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5185 validate);
5186 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5187 opcode_length += imm.length;
5188
5189 Value obj = Pop();
5190
5191 HeapType target_type = imm.type;
5192
5193 if (!VALIDATE((obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
5194 IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type,
5195 this->module_)) ||
5196 obj.type.is_bottom())) {
5197 this->DecodeError(
5198 obj.pc(),
5199 "Invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
5200 "be in the same reference type hierarchy as (ref %s)",
5201 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()),
5202 obj.type.name().c_str(), target_type.name().c_str());
5203 return 0;
5204 }
5205 if (!VALIDATE(!target_type.is_string_view())) {
5206 // TODO(12868): This reflects the current state of discussion at
5207 // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40
5208 // It is suboptimal because it allows classifying a stringview_wtf16
5209 // as a stringref. This would be solved by making the views types
5210 // that aren't subtypes of anyref, which is one of the possible
5211 // resolutions of that discussion.
5212 this->DecodeError(
5213 this->pc_,
5214 "Invalid type for %s: string views are not classifiable",
5215 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
5216 return 0;
5217 }
5218
5219 bool null_succeeds = opcode == kExprRefCastNull;
5220 Value* value = Push(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5221 target_type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable));
5222 if (current_code_reachable_and_ok_) {
5223 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
5224 // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
5225 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type))) {
5226 if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
5227 CALL_INTERFACE(AssertNotNullTypecheck, obj, value);
5228 } else {
5229 CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, obj, value);
5230 }
5231 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type,
5232 null_succeeds))) {
5233 // Unrelated types. The only way this will not trap is if the object
5234 // is null.
5235 if (obj.type.is_nullable() && null_succeeds) {
5236 CALL_INTERFACE(AssertNullTypecheck, obj, value);
5237 } else {
5238 CALL_INTERFACE(Trap, TrapReason::kTrapIllegalCast);
5239 // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
5240 // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
5241 SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
5242 }
5243 } else {
5244 if (target_type.is_index()) {
5245 CALL_INTERFACE(RefCast, target_type.ref_index(), obj, value,
5246 null_succeeds);
5247 } else {
5248 CALL_INTERFACE(RefCastAbstract, obj, target_type, value,
5249 null_succeeds);
5250 }
5251 }
5252 }
5253 return opcode_length;
5254 }
5255 case kExprRefTestNull:
5256 case kExprRefTest: {
5257 NON_CONST_ONLY
5258 HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5259 validate);
5260 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5261 opcode_length += imm.length;
5262
5263 Value obj = Pop();
5264 HeapType target_type = imm.type;
5265 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5266
5267 if (!VALIDATE((obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
5268 IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type,
5269 this->module_)) ||
5270 obj.type.is_bottom())) {
5271 this->DecodeError(
5272 obj.pc(),
5273 "Invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
5274 "be in the same reference type hierarchy as (ref %s)",
5275 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()),
5276 obj.type.name().c_str(), target_type.name().c_str());
5277 return 0;
5278 }
5279 if (!VALIDATE(!target_type.is_string_view())) {
5280 // TODO(12868): This reflects the current state of discussion at
5281 // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40
5282 // It is suboptimal because it allows classifying a stringview_wtf16
5283 // as a stringref. This would be solved by making the views types
5284 // that aren't subtypes of anyref, which is one of the possible
5285 // resolutions of that discussion.
5286 this->DecodeError(
5287 this->pc_,
5288 "Invalid type for %s: string views are not classifiable",
5289 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
5290 return 0;
5291 }
5292 bool null_succeeds = opcode == kExprRefTestNull;
5293 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
5294 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
5295 // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
5296 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type))) {
5297 // Type checking can still fail for null.
5298 if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
5299 // We abuse ref.as_non_null, which isn't otherwise used as a unary
5300 // operator, as a sentinel for the negation of ref.is_null.
5301 CALL_INTERFACE(UnOp, kExprRefAsNonNull, obj, result);
5302 } else {
5303 CALL_INTERFACE(Drop);
5304 CALL_INTERFACE(I32Const, result, 1);
5305 }
5306 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type,
5307 null_succeeds))) {
5308 CALL_INTERFACE(Drop);
5309 CALL_INTERFACE(I32Const, result, 0);
5310 } else {
5311 if (imm.type.is_index()) {
5312 CALL_INTERFACE(RefTest, imm.type.ref_index(), obj, result,
5313 null_succeeds);
5314 } else {
5315 CALL_INTERFACE(RefTestAbstract, obj, target_type, result,
5316 null_succeeds);
5317 }
5318 }
5319 }
5320 return opcode_length;
5321 }
5322 case kExprRefCastNop: {
5323 NON_CONST_ONLY
5324 // Temporary non-standard instruction, for performance experiments.
5325 if (!VALIDATE(this->enabled_.has_ref_cast_nop())) {
5326 this->DecodeError(
5327 "Invalid opcode 0xfb4c (enable with "
5328 "--experimental-wasm-ref-cast-nop)");
5329 return 0;
5330 }
5331 HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5332 validate);
5333 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5334 opcode_length += imm.length;
5335 HeapType target_type = imm.type;
5336 Value obj = Pop();
5337 if (!VALIDATE((obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
5338 IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type,
5339 this->module_)) ||
5340 obj.type.is_bottom())) {
5341 this->DecodeError(
5342 obj.pc(),
5343 "Invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
5344 "be in the same reference type hierarchy as (ref %s)",
5345 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()),
5346 obj.type.name().c_str(), target_type.name().c_str());
5347 return 0;
5348 }
5349 Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(target_type));
5350 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Forward, obj, value);
5351 return opcode_length;
5352 }
5353 case kExprBrOnCast:
5354 case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
5355 NON_CONST_ONLY
5356 uint32_t pc_offset = opcode_length;
5357 BrOnCastImmediate flags_imm(this, this->pc_ + pc_offset, validate);
5358 pc_offset += flags_imm.length;
5359 return ParseBrOnCast(opcode, pc_offset, flags_imm.flags);
5360 }
5361 case kExprAnyConvertExtern: {
5362 Value extern_val = Pop(kWasmExternRef);
5363 ValueType intern_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5364 HeapType::kAny, Nullability(extern_val.type.is_nullable()));
5365 Value* intern_val = Push(intern_type);
5366 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, kExprAnyConvertExtern,
5367 extern_val, intern_val);
5368 return opcode_length;
5369 }
5370 case kExprExternConvertAny: {
5371 Value val = Pop(kWasmAnyRef);
5372 ValueType extern_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5373 HeapType::kExtern, Nullability(val.type.is_nullable()));
5374 Value* extern_val = Push(extern_type);
5375 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, kExprExternConvertAny, val,
5376 extern_val);
5377 return opcode_length;
5378 }
5379 default:
5380 this->DecodeError("invalid gc opcode: %x", opcode);
5381 return 0;
5382 }
5383 }
5384
5385 enum class WasmArrayAccess { kRead, kWrite };
5386
5387 int ParseBrOnCast(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length,
5388 BrOnCastFlags flags) {
5389 BranchDepthImmediate branch_depth(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5390 validate);
5391 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, branch_depth,
5392 control_.size())) {
5393 return 0;
5394 }
5395 uint32_t pc_offset = opcode_length + branch_depth.length;
5396
5397 Value obj = Pop();
5398
5399 HeapTypeImmediate src_imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + pc_offset,
5400 validate);
5401 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + pc_offset, src_imm)) return 0;
5402 pc_offset += src_imm.length;
5403 ValueType src_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5404 src_imm.type, flags.src_is_null ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
5405 ValidateStackValue(0, obj, src_type);
5406
5407 HeapTypeImmediate target_imm(this->enabled_, this, this->pc_ + pc_offset,
5408 validate);
5409 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + pc_offset, target_imm)) return 0;
5410 pc_offset += target_imm.length;
5411 bool null_succeeds = flags.res_is_null;
5412 ValueType target_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5413 target_imm.type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
5414
5415 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(target_type, src_type, this->module_))) {
5416 this->DecodeError("invalid types for %s: %s is not a subtype of %s",
5417 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
5418 target_type.name().c_str(), src_type.name().c_str());
5419 return 0;
5420 }
5421
5422 if (!VALIDATE(
5423 (obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
5424 IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type.heap_type(),
5425 this->module_)) ||
5426 obj.type.is_bottom())) {
5427 this->DecodeError(obj.pc(),
5428 "invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
5429 "be in the same reference type hierarchy as %s",
5430 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
5431 SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()), obj.type.name().c_str(),
5432 target_type.name().c_str());
5433 return 0;
5434 }
5435
5436 Control* c = control_at(branch_depth.depth);
5437 if (c->br_merge()->arity == 0) {
5438 this->DecodeError("%s must target a branch of arity at least 1",
5439 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
5440 return 0;
5441 }
5442
5443 if (opcode == kExprBrOnCast) {
5444 Value* value_on_branch = Push(target_type);
5445 if (!VALIDATE(
5446 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
5447 c)))) {
5448 return 0;
5449 }
5450 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
5451 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
5452 // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
5453 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5454 TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type.heap_type()))) {
5455 // The branch will still not be taken on null if not
5456 // {null_succeeds}.
5457 if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
5458 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNonNull, obj, value_on_branch,
5459 branch_depth.depth, false);
5460 } else {
5461 CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, obj, value_on_branch);
5462 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, branch_depth.depth);
5463 // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
5464 // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
5465 SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
5466 }
5467 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
5468 } else if (V8_LIKELY(!TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type.heap_type(),
5469 null_succeeds))) {
5470 if (target_imm.type.is_index()) {
5471 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCast, target_imm.type.ref_index(), obj,
5472 value_on_branch, branch_depth.depth, null_succeeds);
5473 } else {
5474 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastAbstract, obj, target_type.heap_type(),
5475 value_on_branch, branch_depth.depth, null_succeeds);
5476 }
5477 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
5478 }
5479 }
5480
5481 Drop(*value_on_branch);
5482 Push(obj); // Restore stack state on fallthrough.
5483 // The fallthrough type is the source type as specified in the br_on_cast
5484 // instruction. This can be a super type of the stack value. Furthermore
5485 // nullability gets refined to non-nullable if the cast target is
5486 // nullable, meaning the branch will be taken on null.
5487 DCHECK(!src_type.heap_type().is_bottom());
5488 bool fallthrough_nullable = flags.src_is_null && !flags.res_is_null;
5489 stack_value(1)->type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5490 src_type.heap_type(),
5491 fallthrough_nullable ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
5492 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Forward, obj, stack_value(1));
5493 return pc_offset;
5494
5495 } else {
5496 DCHECK_EQ(opcode, kExprBrOnCastFail);
5497 // The branch type is set based on the source type immediate (independent
5498 // of the actual stack value). If the target type is nullable, the branch
5499 // type is non-nullable.
5500 Push(flags.res_is_null ? src_type.AsNonNull() : src_type);
5501 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Forward, obj, stack_value(1));
5502
5503 if (!VALIDATE(
5504 (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
5505 c)))) {
5506 return 0;
5507 }
5508
5509 Value result_on_fallthrough = CreateValue(target_type);
5510 if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
5511 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
5512 // can only be cast between compatible types.
5513 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type.heap_type(),
5514 null_succeeds))) {
5515 // The types are incompatible (i.e. neither of the two types is a
5516 // subtype of the other). Always branch.
5517 CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, obj, stack_value(1));
5518 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, branch_depth.depth);
5519 // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
5520 // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
5521 SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
5522 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
5523 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5524 TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type.heap_type()))) {
5525 // The branch can still be taken on null.
5526 if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
5527 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNull, obj, branch_depth.depth, true,
5528 &result_on_fallthrough);
5529 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
5530 } else {
5531 // Otherwise, the type check always succeeds. Do not branch. Also,
5532 // make sure the object remains on the stack.
5533 result_on_fallthrough = obj;
5534 }
5535 } else {
5536 if (target_imm.type.is_index()) {
5537 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastFail, target_imm.type.ref_index(), obj,
5538 &result_on_fallthrough, branch_depth.depth,
5539 null_succeeds);
5540 } else {
5541 CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastFailAbstract, obj, target_type.heap_type(),
5542 &result_on_fallthrough, branch_depth.depth,
5543 null_succeeds);
5544 }
5545 c->br_merge()->reached = true;
5546 }
5547 }
5548 // Make sure the correct value is on the stack state on fallthrough.
5549 Drop(obj);
5550 Push(result_on_fallthrough);
5551 return pc_offset;
5552 }
5553 }
5554
5555 int DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5556 uint32_t opcode_length) {
5557 NON_CONST_ONLY
5558 bool null_on_invalid = variant == unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap;
5559 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5560 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5561 ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5562 auto [offset, size] = Pop(addr_type, kWasmI32);
5563 Value* result = Push(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5564 HeapType::kString, null_on_invalid ? kNullable : kNonNullable));
5565 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf8, imm, variant, offset,
5566 size, result);
5567 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5568 }
5569
5570 int DecodeStringMeasureWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5571 uint32_t opcode_length) {
5572 NON_CONST_ONLY
5573 Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
5574 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5575 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringMeasureWtf8, variant, str, result);
5576 return opcode_length;
5577 }
5578
5579 int DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5580 uint32_t opcode_length) {
5581 NON_CONST_ONLY
5582 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5583 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5584 ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5585 auto [str, addr] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, addr_type);
5586 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5587 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEncodeWtf8, imm, variant, str,
5588 addr, result);
5589 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5590 }
5591
5592 int DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5593 uint32_t opcode_length) {
5594 NON_CONST_ONLY
5595 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5596 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5597 ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5598 auto [view, addr, pos, bytes] =
5599 Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf8, addr_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5600 Value* next_pos = Push(kWasmI32);
5601 Value* bytes_out = Push(kWasmI32);
5602 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf8Encode, imm, variant, view,
5603 addr, pos, bytes, next_pos, bytes_out);
5604 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5605 }
5606
5607 int DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5608 uint32_t opcode_length) {
5609 NON_CONST_ONLY
5610 Value end = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
5611 Value start = Pop(1, kWasmI32);
5612 Value array = PopPackedArray(0, kWasmI8, WasmArrayAccess::kRead);
5613 bool null_on_invalid = variant == unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap;
5614 Value* result = Push(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
5615 HeapType::kString, null_on_invalid ? kNullable : kNonNullable));
5616 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf8Array, variant, array,
5617 start, end, result);
5618 return opcode_length;
5619 }
5620
5621 int DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
5622 uint32_t opcode_length) {
5623 NON_CONST_ONLY
5624 Value start = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
5625 Value array = PopPackedArray(1, kWasmI8, WasmArrayAccess::kWrite);
5626 Value str = Pop(0, kWasmStringRef);
5627 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5628 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEncodeWtf8Array, variant, str,
5629 array, start, result);
5630 return opcode_length;
5631 }
5632
5633 int DecodeStringRefOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
5634 // Fast check for out-of-range opcodes (only allow 0xfbXX).
5635 // This might help the big switch below.
5636 if (!VALIDATE((opcode >> 8) == kGCPrefix)) {
5637 this->DecodeError("invalid stringref opcode: %x", opcode);
5638 return 0;
5639 }
5640
5641 switch (opcode) {
5642 case kExprStringNewUtf8:
5643 return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8, opcode_length);
5644 case kExprStringNewUtf8Try:
5645 return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap,
5646 opcode_length);
5647 case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8:
5648 return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
5649 opcode_length);
5650 case kExprStringNewWtf8:
5651 return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8, opcode_length);
5652 case kExprStringNewWtf16: {
5653 NON_CONST_ONLY
5654 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5655 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5656 ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5657 auto [offset, size] = Pop(addr_type, kWasmI32);
5658 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5659 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf16, imm, offset, size,
5660 result);
5661 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5662 }
5663 case kExprStringConst: {
5664 StringConstImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5665 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5666 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5667 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringConst, imm, result);
5668 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5669 }
5670 case kExprStringMeasureUtf8:
5671 return DecodeStringMeasureWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
5672 opcode_length);
5673 case kExprStringMeasureWtf8:
5674 return DecodeStringMeasureWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
5675 opcode_length);
5676 case kExprStringMeasureWtf16: {
5677 NON_CONST_ONLY
5678 Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
5679 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5680 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringMeasureWtf16, str, result);
5681 return opcode_length;
5682 }
5683 case kExprStringEncodeUtf8:
5684 return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
5685 opcode_length);
