5686 case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8:
5687 return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
5688 opcode_length);
5689 case kExprStringEncodeWtf8:
5690 return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
5691 opcode_length);
5692 case kExprStringEncodeWtf16: {
5693 NON_CONST_ONLY
5694 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5695 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5696 ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5697 auto [str, addr] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, addr_type);
5698 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5699 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEncodeWtf16, imm, str, addr,
5700 result);
5701 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5702 }
5703 case kExprStringConcat: {
5704 NON_CONST_ONLY
5705 auto [head, tail] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, kWasmStringRef);
5706 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5707 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringConcat, head, tail, result);
5708 return opcode_length;
5709 }
5710 case kExprStringEq: {
5711 NON_CONST_ONLY
5712 auto [a, b] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, kWasmStringRef);
5713 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5714 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEq, a, b, result);
5715 return opcode_length;
5716 }
5717 case kExprStringIsUSVSequence: {
5718 NON_CONST_ONLY
5719 Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
5720 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5721 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringIsUSVSequence, str, result);
5722 return opcode_length;
5723 }
5724 case kExprStringAsWtf8: {
5725 NON_CONST_ONLY
5726 Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
5727 Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(HeapType::kStringViewWtf8));
5728 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringAsWtf8, str, result);
5729 return opcode_length;
5730 }
5731 case kExprStringViewWtf8Advance: {
5732 NON_CONST_ONLY
5733 auto [view, pos, bytes] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf8, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5734 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5735 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf8Advance, view, pos,
5736 bytes, result);
5737 return opcode_length;
5738 }
5739 case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeUtf8:
5740 return DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
5741 opcode_length);
5742 case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeLossyUtf8:
5743 return DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
5744 opcode_length);
5745 case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeWtf8:
5746 return DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
5747 opcode_length);
5748 case kExprStringViewWtf8Slice: {
5749 NON_CONST_ONLY
5750 auto [view, start, end] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf8, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5751 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5752 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf8Slice, view, start,
5753 end, result);
5754 return opcode_length;
5755 }
5756 case kExprStringAsWtf16: {
5757 NON_CONST_ONLY
5758 Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
5759 Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(HeapType::kStringViewWtf16));
5760 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringAsWtf16, str, result);
5761 return opcode_length;
5762 }
5763 case kExprStringViewWtf16Length: {
5764 NON_CONST_ONLY
5765 Value view = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16);
5766 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5767 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringMeasureWtf16, view, result);
5768 return opcode_length;
5769 }
5770 case kExprStringViewWtf16GetCodeunit: {
5771 NON_CONST_ONLY
5772 auto [view, pos] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16, kWasmI32);
5773 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5774 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf16GetCodeUnit, view,
5775 pos, result);
5776 return opcode_length;
5777 }
5778 case kExprStringViewWtf16Encode: {
5779 NON_CONST_ONLY
5780 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5781 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5782 ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5783 auto [view, addr, pos, codeunits] =
5784 Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16, addr_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5785 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5786 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf16Encode, imm, view,
5787 addr, pos, codeunits, result);
5788 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5789 }
5790 case kExprStringViewWtf16Slice: {
5791 NON_CONST_ONLY
5792 auto [view, start, end] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5793 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5794 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf16Slice, view, start,
5795 end, result);
5796 return opcode_length;
5797 }
5798 case kExprStringAsIter: {
5799 NON_CONST_ONLY
5800 Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
5801 Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(HeapType::kStringViewIter));
5802 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringAsIter, str, result);
5803 return opcode_length;
5804 }
5805 case kExprStringViewIterNext: {
5806 NON_CONST_ONLY
5807 Value view = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter);
5808 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5809 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterNext, view, result);
5810 return opcode_length;
5811 }
5812 case kExprStringViewIterAdvance: {
5813 NON_CONST_ONLY
5814 auto [view, codepoints] = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter, kWasmI32);
5815 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5816 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterAdvance, view,
5817 codepoints, result);
5818 return opcode_length;
5819 }
5820 case kExprStringViewIterRewind: {
5821 NON_CONST_ONLY
5822 auto [view, codepoints] = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter, kWasmI32);
5823 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5824 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterRewind, view,
5825 codepoints, result);
5826 return opcode_length;
5827 }
5828 case kExprStringViewIterSlice: {
5829 NON_CONST_ONLY
5830 auto [view, codepoints] = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter, kWasmI32);
5831 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5832 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterSlice, view,
5833 codepoints, result);
5834 return opcode_length;
5835 }
5836 case kExprStringNewUtf8Array:
5837 return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
5838 opcode_length);
5839 case kExprStringNewUtf8ArrayTry:
5840 return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap,
5841 opcode_length);
5842 case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8Array:
5843 return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
5844 opcode_length);
5845 case kExprStringNewWtf8Array:
5846 return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
5847 opcode_length);
5848 case kExprStringNewWtf16Array: {
5849 NON_CONST_ONLY
5850 Value end = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
5851 Value start = Pop(1, kWasmI32);
5852 Value array = PopPackedArray(0, kWasmI16, WasmArrayAccess::kRead);
5853 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5854 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf16Array, array, start,
5855 end, result);
5856 return opcode_length;
5857 }
5858 case kExprStringEncodeUtf8Array:
5859 return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
5860 opcode_length);
5861 case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8Array:
5862 return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
5863 opcode_length);
5864 case kExprStringEncodeWtf8Array:
5865 return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
5866 opcode_length);
5867 case kExprStringEncodeWtf16Array: {
5868 NON_CONST_ONLY
5869 Value start = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
5870 Value array = PopPackedArray(1, kWasmI16, WasmArrayAccess::kWrite);
5871 Value str = Pop(0, kWasmStringRef);
5872 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5873 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEncodeWtf16Array, str, array,
5874 start, result);
5875 return opcode_length;
5876 }
5877 case kExprStringCompare: {
5878 NON_CONST_ONLY
5879 auto [lhs, rhs] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, kWasmStringRef);
5880 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5881 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringCompare, lhs, rhs, result);
5882 return opcode_length;
5883 }
5884 case kExprStringFromCodePoint: {
5885 NON_CONST_ONLY
5886 Value code_point = Pop(kWasmI32);
5887 Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
5888 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringFromCodePoint, code_point,
5889 result);
5890 return opcode_length;
5891 }
5892 case kExprStringHash: {
5893 NON_CONST_ONLY
5894 Value string = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
5895 Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
5896 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringHash, string, result);
5897 return opcode_length;
5898 }
5899 default:
5900 this->DecodeError("invalid stringref opcode: %x", opcode);
5901 return 0;
5902 }
5903 }
5904#undef NON_CONST_ONLY
5905
5906 uint32_t DecodeAtomicOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
5907 // Fast check for out-of-range opcodes (only allow 0xfeXX).
5908 if (!VALIDATE((opcode >> 8) == kAtomicPrefix)) {
5909 this->DecodeError("invalid atomic opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
5910 return 0;
5911 }
5912
5913 MachineType memtype;
5914 switch (opcode) {
5915#define CASE_ATOMIC_STORE_OP(Name, Type) \
5916 case kExpr##Name: { \
5917 memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
5918 break; /* to generic mem access code below */ \
5919 }
5920 ATOMIC_STORE_OP_LIST(CASE_ATOMIC_STORE_OP)
5921#undef CASE_ATOMIC_STORE_OP
5922#define CASE_ATOMIC_OP(Name, Type) \
5923 case kExpr##Name: { \
5924 memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
5925 break; /* to generic mem access code below */ \
5926 }
5927 ATOMIC_OP_LIST(CASE_ATOMIC_OP)
5928#undef CASE_ATOMIC_OP
5929 case kExprAtomicFence: {
5930 uint8_t zero = this->template read_u8<ValidationTag>(
5931 this->pc_ + opcode_length, "zero");
5932 if (!VALIDATE(zero == 0)) {
5933 this->DecodeError(this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5934 "invalid atomic operand");
5935 return 0;
5936 }
5937 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(AtomicFence);
5938 return 1 + opcode_length;
5939 }
5940 default:
5941 // This path is only possible if we are validating.
5942 V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
5943 this->DecodeError("invalid atomic opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
5944 return 0;
5945 }
5946
5947 const uint32_t element_size_log2 =
5948 ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation());
5949 MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
5950 MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, element_size_log2);
5951 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return false;
5952 if (!VALIDATE(imm.alignment == element_size_log2)) {
5953 this->DecodeError(this->pc_,
5954 "invalid alignment for atomic operation; expected "
5955 "alignment is %u, actual alignment is %u",
5956 element_size_log2, imm.alignment);
5957 }
5958
5959 const FunctionSig* sig =
5960 WasmOpcodes::SignatureForAtomicOp(opcode, imm.memory->is_memory64());
5961 V8_ASSUME(sig != nullptr);
5962 PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(sig);
5963 Value* result = sig->return_count() ? Push(sig->GetReturn()) : nullptr;
5964 if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, memtype.MemSize(),
5965 imm.offset))) {
5966 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(AtomicOp, opcode, args.data(),
5967 sig->parameter_count(), imm, result);
5968 }
5969
5970 return opcode_length + imm.length;
5971 }
5972
5973 unsigned DecodeNumericOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
5974 // Fast check for out-of-range opcodes (only allow 0xfcXX).
5975 // This avoids a dynamic check in signature lookup, and might also help the
5976 // big switch below.
5977 if (!VALIDATE((opcode >> 8) == kNumericPrefix)) {
5978 this->DecodeError("invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
5979 return 0;
5980 }
5981
5982 const FunctionSig* sig = WasmOpcodes::Signature(opcode);
5983 switch (opcode) {
5984 case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
5985 case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
5986 case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
5987 case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
5988 case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
5989 case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
5990 case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
5991 case kExprI64UConvertSatF64: {
5992 BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, sig);
5993 return opcode_length;
5994 }
5995 case kExprMemoryInit: {
5996 MemoryInitImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5997 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5998 ValueType mem_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory.memory);
5999 auto [dst, offset, size] = Pop(mem_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
6000 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(MemoryInit, imm, dst, offset, size);
6001 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6002 }
6003 case kExprDataDrop: {
6004 IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6005 "data segment index", validate);
6006 if (!this->ValidateDataSegment(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) {
6007 return 0;
6008 }
6009 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(DataDrop, imm);
6010 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6011 }
6012 case kExprMemoryCopy: {
6013 MemoryCopyImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6014 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6015 ValueType dst_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory_dst.memory);
6016 ValueType src_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory_src.memory);
6017 // size_type = min(dst_type, src_type), where kI32 < kI64.
6018 ValueType size_type = dst_type == kWasmI32 ? kWasmI32 : src_type;
6019
6020 auto [dst, src, size] = Pop(dst_type, src_type, size_type);
6021 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(MemoryCopy, imm, dst, src, size);
6022 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6023 }
6024 case kExprMemoryFill: {
6025 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6026 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6027 ValueType mem_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
6028 auto [dst, value, size] = Pop(mem_type, kWasmI32, mem_type);
6029 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(MemoryFill, imm, dst, value, size);
6030 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6031 }
6032 case kExprTableInit: {
6033 TableInitImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6034 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6035 ValueType table_address_type = TableAddressType(imm.table.table);
6036 auto [dst, src, size] = Pop(table_address_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
6037 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableInit, imm, dst, src, size);
6038 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6039 }
6040 case kExprElemDrop: {
6041 IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6042 "element segment index", validate);
6043 if (!this->ValidateElementSegment(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) {
6044 return 0;
6045 }
6046 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ElemDrop, imm);
6047 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6048 }
6049 case kExprTableCopy: {
6050 TableCopyImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6051 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6052 ValueType dst_type = TableAddressType(imm.table_dst.table);
6053 ValueType src_type = TableAddressType(imm.table_src.table);
6054 // size_type = min(dst_type, src_type), where kI32 < kI64.
6055 ValueType size_type = dst_type == kWasmI32 ? kWasmI32 : src_type;
6056
6057 auto [dst, src, size] = Pop(dst_type, src_type, size_type);
6058 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableCopy, imm, dst, src, size);
6059 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6060 }
6061 case kExprTableGrow: {
6062 TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6063 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6064 ValueType table_address_type = TableAddressType(imm.table);
6065 auto [value, delta] = Pop(imm.table->type, table_address_type);
6066 Value* result = Push(table_address_type);
6067 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableGrow, imm, value, delta,
6068 result);
6069 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6070 }
6071 case kExprTableSize: {
6072 TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6073 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6074 Value* result = Push(TableAddressType(imm.table));
6075 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableSize, imm, result);
6076 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6077 }
6078 case kExprTableFill: {
6079 TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6080 if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6081 ValueType table_address_type = TableAddressType(imm.table);
6082 auto [start, value, count] =
6083 Pop(table_address_type, imm.table->type, table_address_type);
6084 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableFill, imm, start, value, count);
6085 return opcode_length + imm.length;
6086 }
6087 case kExprF32LoadMemF16: {
6088 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_fp16) {
6089 this->DecodeError(
6090 "invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x, "
6091 "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
6092 opcode);
6093 return 0;
6094 }
6095 return DecodeLoadMem(LoadType::kF32LoadF16, 2);
6096 }
6097 case kExprF32StoreMemF16: {
6098 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_fp16) {
6099 this->DecodeError(
6100 "invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x, "
6101 "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
6102 opcode);
6103 return 0;
6104 }
6105 return DecodeStoreMem(StoreType::kF32StoreF16, 2);
6106 }
6107 default:
6108 this->DecodeError("invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
6109 return 0;
6110 }
6111 }
6112
6113 V8_INLINE Value CreateValue(ValueType type) { return Value{this->pc_, type}; }
6114
6115 V8_INLINE Value* Push(Value value) {
6116 DCHECK_IMPLIES(this->ok(), value.type != kWasmVoid);
6117 if (!VALIDATE(!this->is_shared_ || IsShared(value.type, this->module_))) {
6118 this->DecodeError(value.pc(), "%s does not have a shared type",
6119 SafeOpcodeNameAt(value.pc()));
6120 return nullptr;
6121 }
6122 // {stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity} should have been called before, either in the
6123 // central decoding loop, or individually if more than one element is
6124 // pushed.
6125 stack_.push(value);
6126 return &stack_.back();
6127 }
6128
6129 V8_INLINE Value* Push(ValueType type) { return Push(CreateValue(type)); }
6130
6131 void PushMergeValues(Control* c, Merge<Value>* merge) {
6132 if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) return;
6133 DCHECK_EQ(c, &control_.back());
6134 DCHECK(merge == &c->start_merge || merge == &c->end_merge);
6135 stack_.shrink_to(c->stack_depth);
6136 if (merge->arity == 1) {
6137 // {stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity} should have been called before in the
6138 // central decoding loop.
6139 Push(merge->vals.first);
6140 } else {
6141 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(merge->arity, this->zone_);
6142 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < merge->arity; i++) {
6143 Push(merge->vals.array[i]);
6144 }
6145 }
6146 DCHECK_EQ(c->stack_depth + merge->arity, stack_.size());
6147 }
6148
6149 V8_INLINE void PushReturns(ReturnVector values) {
6150 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(values.size()), this->zone_);
6151 for (Value& value : values) Push(value);
6152 }
6153
6154 Value* PushReturns(const FunctionSig* sig) {
6155 size_t return_count = sig->return_count();
6156 stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(return_count), this->zone_);
6157 for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; ++i) {
6158 Push(sig->GetReturn(i));
6159 }
6160 return stack_.end() - return_count;
6161 }
6162
6163 // We do not inline these functions because doing so causes a large binary
6164 // size increase. Not inlining them should not create a performance
6165 // degradation, because their invocations are guarded by V8_LIKELY.
6166 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void PopTypeError(int index, Value val,
6167 const char* expected) {
6168 this->DecodeError(val.pc(), "%s[%d] expected %s, found %s of type %s",
6169 SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc_), index, expected,
6170 SafeOpcodeNameAt(val.pc()), val.type.name().c_str());
6171 }
6172
6173 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void PopTypeError(int index, Value val,
6174 std::string expected) {
6175 PopTypeError(index, val, expected.c_str());
6176 }
6177
6178 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void PopTypeError(int index, Value val,
6179 ValueType expected) {
6180 PopTypeError(index, val, ("type " + expected.name()).c_str());
6181 }
6182
6183 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void NotEnoughArgumentsError(int needed,
6184 int actual) {
6185 DCHECK_LT(0, needed);
6186 DCHECK_LE(0, actual);
6187 DCHECK_LT(actual, needed);
6188 this->DecodeError(
6189 "not enough arguments on the stack for %s (need %d, got %d)",
6190 SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc_), needed, actual);
6191 }
6192
6193 V8_INLINE Value Pop(int index, ValueType expected) {
6194 Value value = Pop();
6195 ValidateStackValue(index, value, expected);
6196 return value;
6197 }
6198
6199 V8_INLINE void ValidateStackValue(int index, Value value,
6200 ValueType expected) {
6201 if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(value.type, expected, this->module_) ||
6202 value.type == kWasmBottom || expected == kWasmBottom)) {
6203 PopTypeError(index, value, expected);
6204 }
6205 }
6206
6207 V8_INLINE Value Pop() {
6208 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
6209 uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
6210 if (V8_UNLIKELY(stack_size() <= limit)) {
6211 // Popping past the current control start in reachable code.
6212 if (!VALIDATE(control_.back().unreachable())) {
6213 NotEnoughArgumentsError(1, 0);
6214 }
6215 return UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
6216 }
6217 Value top_of_stack = stack_.back();
6218 stack_.pop();
6219 return top_of_stack;
6220 }
6221
6222 V8_INLINE Value Peek(int depth, int index, ValueType expected) {
6223 Value value = Peek(depth);
6224 ValidateStackValue(index, value, expected);
6225 return value;
6226 }
6227
6228 V8_INLINE Value Peek(int depth = 0) {
6229 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
6230 uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
6231 if (V8_UNLIKELY(stack_.size() <= limit + depth)) {
6232 // Peeking past the current control start in reachable code.
6233 if (!VALIDATE(decoding_mode == kFunctionBody &&
6234 control_.back().unreachable())) {
6235 NotEnoughArgumentsError(depth + 1, stack_.size() - limit);
6236 }
6237 return UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
6238 }
6239 DCHECK_LT(depth, stack_.size());
6240 return *(stack_.end() - depth - 1);
6241 }
6242
6243 V8_INLINE Value Peek(ValueType expected) { return Peek(0, 0, expected); }
6244
6245 // Pop multiple values at once; faster than multiple individual {Pop}s.
6246 // Returns an array of the popped values if there are multiple, or the popped
6247 // value itself if a single type is passed.
6248 template <typename... ValueTypes>
6249 // Pop is only allowed to be called with ValueType parameters.
6250 requires(std::is_same_v<ValueType, ValueTypes> && ...)
6251 V8_INLINE std::conditional_t<sizeof...(ValueTypes) == 1, Value,
6252 std::array<Value, sizeof...(ValueTypes)>>
6253 Pop(ValueTypes... expected_types) {
6254 constexpr int kCount = sizeof...(ValueTypes);
6255 EnsureStackArguments(kCount);
6256 DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, stack_size());
6257 DCHECK_GE(stack_size() - control_.back().stack_depth, kCount);
6258 // Note: Popping from the {FastZoneVector} does not invalidate the old (now
6259 // out-of-range) elements.
6260 stack_.pop(kCount);
6261 auto ValidateAndGetNextArg = [this, i = 0](ValueType type) mutable {
6262 ValidateStackValue(i, stack_.end()[i], type);
6263 return stack_.end()[i++];
6264 };
6265 return {ValidateAndGetNextArg(expected_types)...};
6266 }
6267
6268 Value PopPackedArray(uint32_t operand_index, ValueType expected_element_type,
6269 WasmArrayAccess access) {
6270 Value array = Pop();
6271 if (array.type.is_bottom()) {
6272 // We are in a polymorphic stack. Leave the stack as it is.
6273 DCHECK(!current_code_reachable_and_ok_);
6274 return array;
6275 }
6276 // Inputs of type "none" are okay due to implicit upcasting. The stringref
6277 // spec doesn't say this explicitly yet, but it's consistent with the rest
6278 // of Wasm. (Of course such inputs will trap at runtime.) See:
6279 // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/66
6280 if (array.type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kNone)) return array;
6281 if (VALIDATE(array.type.is_object_reference() && array.type.has_index())) {
6282 ModuleTypeIndex ref_index = array.type.ref_index();
6283 if (VALIDATE(this->module_->has_array(ref_index))) {
6284 const ArrayType* array_type = this->module_->array_type(ref_index);
6285 if (VALIDATE(array_type->element_type() == expected_element_type &&
6286 (access == WasmArrayAccess::kRead ||
6287 array_type->mutability()))) {
6288 return array;
6289 }
6290 }
6291 }
6292 PopTypeError(operand_index, array,
6293 (std::string("array of ") +
6294 (access == WasmArrayAccess::kWrite ? "mutable " : "") +
6295 expected_element_type.name())
6296 .c_str());
6297 return array;
6298 }
6299
6300 // Drop the top {count} stack elements, or all of them if less than {count}
6301 // are present.
6302 V8_INLINE void Drop(int count = 1) {
6303 DCHECK(!control_.empty());
6304 uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
6305 if (V8_UNLIKELY(stack_.size() < limit + count)) {
6306 // Pop what we can.
6307 count = std::min(count, static_cast<int>(stack_.size() - limit));
6308 }
6309 stack_.pop(count);
6310 }
6311 // Drop the top stack element if present. Takes a Value input for more
6312 // descriptive call sites.
6313 V8_INLINE void Drop(const Value& /* unused */) { Drop(1); }
6314
6315 enum StackElementsCountMode : bool {
6316 kNonStrictCounting = false,
6317 kStrictCounting = true
6318 };
6319
6320 enum MergeType {
6321 kBranchMerge,
6322 kReturnMerge,
6323 kFallthroughMerge,
6324 kInitExprMerge
6325 };
6326
6327 enum class PushBranchValues : bool {
6328 kNo = false,
6329 kYes = true,
6330 };
6331 enum class RewriteStackTypes : bool {
6332 kNo = false,
6333 kYes = true,
6334 };
6335
6336 // - If the current code is reachable, check if the current stack values are
6337 // compatible with {merge} based on their number and types. If
6338 // {strict_count}, check that #(stack elements) == {merge->arity}, otherwise
6339 // #(stack elements) >= {merge->arity}.
6340 // - If the current code is unreachable, check if any values that may exist on
6341 // top of the stack are compatible with {merge}. If {push_branch_values},
6342 // push back to the stack values based on the type of {merge} (this is
6343 // needed for conditional branches due to their typing rules, and
6344 // fallthroughs so that the outer control finds the expected values on the
6345 // stack). TODO(manoskouk): We expect the unreachable-code behavior to
6346 // change, either due to relaxation of dead code verification, or the
6347 // introduction of subtyping.
6348 template <StackElementsCountMode strict_count,
6349 PushBranchValues push_branch_values, MergeType merge_type,
6350 RewriteStackTypes rewrite_types>
6351 V8_INLINE bool TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge(Merge<Value>* merge) {
6352 uint32_t arity = merge->arity;
6353 uint32_t actual = stack_.size() - control_.back().stack_depth;
6354 // Handle trivial cases first. Arity 0 is the most common case.
6355 if (arity == 0 && (!strict_count || actual == 0)) return true;
6356 // Arity 1 is still common enough that we handle it separately (only doing
6357 // the most basic subtype check).
6358 if (arity == 1 && (strict_count ? actual == arity : actual >= arity)) {
6359 if (stack_.back().type == merge->vals.first.type) return true;
6360 }
6361 return TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge_Slow<strict_count, push_branch_values,
6362 merge_type, rewrite_types>(merge);
6363 }
6364
6365 // Slow path for {TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge}.
6366 template <StackElementsCountMode strict_count,
6367 PushBranchValues push_branch_values, MergeType merge_type,
6368 RewriteStackTypes rewrite_types>
6369 V8_PRESERVE_MOST V8_NOINLINE bool TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge_Slow(
6370 Merge<Value>* merge) {
6371 constexpr const char* merge_description =
6372 merge_type == kBranchMerge ? "branch"
6373 : merge_type == kReturnMerge ? "return"
6374 : merge_type == kInitExprMerge ? "constant expression"
6375 : "fallthru";
6376 uint32_t arity = merge->arity;
6377 uint32_t actual = stack_.size() - control_.back().stack_depth;
6378 // Here we have to check for !unreachable(), because we need to typecheck as
6379 // if the current code is reachable even if it is spec-only reachable.
6380 if (V8_LIKELY(decoding_mode == kConstantExpression ||
6381 !control_.back().unreachable())) {
6382 if (V8_UNLIKELY(strict_count ? actual != arity : actual < arity)) {
6383 this->DecodeError("expected %u elements on the stack for %s, found %u",
6384 arity, merge_description, actual);
6385 return false;
6386 }
6387 // Typecheck the topmost {merge->arity} values on the stack.
6388 Value* stack_values = stack_.end() - arity;
6389 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < arity; ++i) {
6390 Value& val = stack_values[i];
6391 Value& old = (*merge)[i];
6392 if (!IsSubtypeOf(val.type, old.type, this->module_)) {
6393 this->DecodeError("type error in %s[%u] (expected %s, got %s)",
6394 merge_description, i, old.type.name().c_str(),
6395 val.type.name().c_str());
6396 return false;
6397 }
6398 if constexpr (static_cast<bool>(rewrite_types)) {
6399 // Upcast type on the stack to the target type of the label.
6400 val.type = old.type;
6401 }
6402 }
6403 return true;
6404 }
6405 // Unreachable code validation starts here.
6406 if (V8_UNLIKELY(strict_count && actual > arity)) {
6407 this->DecodeError("expected %u elements on the stack for %s, found %u",
6408 arity, merge_description, actual);
6409 return false;
6410 }
6411 // TODO(manoskouk): Use similar code as above if we keep unreachable checks.
6412 for (int i = arity - 1, depth = 0; i >= 0; --i, ++depth) {
6413 Peek(depth, i, (*merge)[i].type);
6414 }
6415 if constexpr (static_cast<bool>(push_branch_values)) {
6416 uint32_t inserted_value_count =
6417 static_cast<uint32_t>(EnsureStackArguments(arity));
6418 if (inserted_value_count > 0) {
6419 // stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity() may have inserted unreachable values into
6420 // the bottom of the stack. If so, mark them with the correct type. If
6421 // drop values were also inserted, disregard them, as they will be
6422 // dropped anyway.
6423 Value* stack_base = stack_value(arity);
6424 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < std::min(arity, inserted_value_count); i++) {
6425 if (stack_base[i].type == kWasmBottom) {
6426 stack_base[i].type = (*merge)[i].type;
6427 }
6428 }
6429 }
6430 }
6431 return VALIDATE(this->ok());
6432 }
6433
6434 template <StackElementsCountMode strict_count, MergeType merge_type>
6435 bool DoReturn() {
6436 if (!VALIDATE(
6437 (TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge<strict_count, PushBranchValues::kNo,
6438 merge_type, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
6439 &control_.front().end_merge)))) {
6440 return false;
6441 }
6442 DCHECK_IMPLIES(current_code_reachable_and_ok_,
6443 stack_.size() >= this->sig_->return_count());
6444 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(DoReturn, 0);
6445 EndControl();
6446 return true;
6447 }
6448
6449 int startrel(const uint8_t* ptr) {
6450 return static_cast<int>(ptr - this->start_);
6451 }
6452
6453 void FallThrough() {
6454 Control* c = &control_.back();
6455 DCHECK_NE(c->kind, kControlLoop);
6456 if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckFallThru())) return;
6457 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(FallThruTo, c);
6458 if (c->reachable()) c->end_merge.reached = true;
6459 }
6460
6461 bool TypeCheckOneArmedIf(Control* c) {
6462 DCHECK(c->is_onearmed_if());
6463 if (c->end_merge.arity != c->start_merge.arity) {
6464 this->DecodeError(c->pc(),
6465 "start-arity and end-arity of one-armed if must match");
6466 return false;
6467 }
6468 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < c->start_merge.arity; ++i) {
6469 Value& start = c->start_merge[i];
6470 Value& end = c->end_merge[i];
6471 if (!IsSubtypeOf(start.type, end.type, this->module_)) {
6472 this->DecodeError("type error in merge[%u] (expected %s, got %s)", i,
6473 end.type.name().c_str(), start.type.name().c_str());
6474 return false;
6475 }
6476 }
6477 return true;
6478 }
6479
6480 bool TypeCheckFallThru() {
6481 return TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge<kStrictCounting, PushBranchValues::kYes,
6482 kFallthroughMerge,
6483 RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
6484 &control_.back().end_merge);
6485 }
6486
6487 // If the current code is reachable, check if the current stack values are
6488 // compatible with a jump to {c}, based on their number and types.
6489 // Otherwise, we have a polymorphic stack: check if any values that may exist
6490 // on top of the stack are compatible with {c}. If {push_branch_values},
6491 // push back to the stack values based on the type of {c} (this is needed for
6492 // conditional branches due to their typing rules, and fallthroughs so that
6493 // the outer control finds enough values on the stack).
6494 template <PushBranchValues push_branch_values,
6495 RewriteStackTypes rewrite_types>
6496 bool TypeCheckBranch(Control* c) {
6497 return TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge<kNonStrictCounting, push_branch_values,
6498 kBranchMerge, rewrite_types>(
6499 c->br_merge());
6500 }
6501
6502 void onFirstError() override {
6503 this->end_ = this->pc_; // Terminate decoding loop.
6504 this->current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = false;
6505 TRACE(" !%s\n", this->error_.message().c_str());
6506 // Cannot use CALL_INTERFACE_* macros because we emitted an error.
6507 interface().OnFirstError(this);
6508 }
6509
6510 // There are currently no simple prototype operators.
6511 int BuildSimplePrototypeOperator(WasmOpcode opcode) {
6512 const FunctionSig* sig = WasmOpcodes::Signature(opcode);
6513 return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, sig);
6514 }
6515
6516 int BuildSimpleOperator(WasmOpcode opcode, const FunctionSig* sig) {
6517 DCHECK_GE(1, sig->return_count());
6518 if (sig->parameter_count() == 1) {
6519 // All current simple unary operators have exactly 1 return value.
6520 DCHECK_EQ(1, sig->return_count());
6521 return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, sig->GetReturn(0), sig->GetParam(0));
6522 } else {
6523 DCHECK_EQ(2, sig->parameter_count());
6524 ValueType ret = sig->return_count() == 0 ? kWasmVoid : sig->GetReturn(0);
6525 return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, ret, sig->GetParam(0),
6526 sig->GetParam(1));
6527 }
6528 }
6529
6530 int BuildSimpleOperator(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType return_type,
6531 ValueType arg_type) {
6532 DCHECK_NE(kWasmVoid, return_type);
6533 Value val = Pop(arg_type);
6534 Value* ret = Push(return_type);
6535 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, opcode, val, ret);
6536 return 1;
6537 }
6538
6539 int BuildSimpleOperator(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType return_type,
6540 ValueType lhs_type, ValueType rhs_type) {
6541 auto [lval, rval] = Pop(lhs_type, rhs_type);
6542 Value* ret = return_type == kWasmVoid ? nullptr : Push(return_type);
6543 CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(BinOp, opcode, lval, rval, ret);
6544 return 1;
6545 }
6546
6547#define DEFINE_SIMPLE_SIG_OPERATOR(sig, ...) \
6548 int BuildSimpleOperator_##sig(WasmOpcode opcode) { \
6549 return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, __VA_ARGS__); \
6550 }
6551 FOREACH_SIGNATURE(DEFINE_SIMPLE_SIG_OPERATOR)
6552#undef DEFINE_SIMPLE_SIG_OPERATOR
6553
6554 static constexpr ValidationTag validate = {};
6555};
6556
6557class EmptyInterface {
6558 public:
6559 using ValidationTag = Decoder::FullValidationTag;
6560 static constexpr DecodingMode decoding_mode = kFunctionBody;
6561 static constexpr bool kUsesPoppedArgs = false;
6562 using Value = ValueBase<ValidationTag>;
6563 using Control = ControlBase<Value, ValidationTag>;
6564 using FullDecoder = WasmFullDecoder<ValidationTag, EmptyInterface>;
6565
6566#define DEFINE_EMPTY_CALLBACK(name, ...) \
6567 void name(FullDecoder* decoder, ##__VA_ARGS__) {}
6568 INTERFACE_FUNCTIONS(DEFINE_EMPTY_CALLBACK)
6569#undef DEFINE_EMPTY_CALLBACK
6570};
6571
6572#undef CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE
6573#undef CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE
6574#undef TRACE
6575#undef TRACE_INST_FORMAT
6576#undef VALIDATE
6577#undef CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE
6578
6579} // namespace v8::internal::wasm
